\h Leviticus
\toc1 Leviticus
\toc2 Leviticus
\toc3 Lev.
\mt2 The handbook of
\mt1 Sacred Living
\mt3 commonly known as
\mt1 Leviticus
\is1 Introduction
\ip The Latin word \bk Leviticus\bk* means вҖҳconcerning the LevitesвҖҷ, who were the tribe of workers and priests who God chose to serve him at the altar and in other religious ceremonies. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳVayikrДҒвҖҷ which is the first word in the Hebrew and means вҖҳAnd he calledвҖҷ (Yahweh called Mosheh/Moses). Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe third book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip It's presumed that Mosheh wrote this document down while they were all camped there at Mt. Sinai as mentioned in a few places: 1:1, 4:1, 6:1,24, and of 8:1.
\ip This document focuses on the proper values and behaviour that the Israelis should observe as Yahweh's chosen and sacred people. That involved staying вҖҳcleanвҖҷ as per Yahweh's values by carefully following his detailed instructions, and by avoiding wickedness.
\ip Some of the instructions apply particularly to the priests (Aharon's/Aaron's descendants) and to the remainder of their own tribe (the Levites that this document is often named after) who served the priests in their sacred ceremonies.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Instructions about offerings and sacrifices \ior 1:1вҖ“7:38\ior*
\io1 The dedication of Aharon and his sons as Yahweh's priests \ior 8:1вҖ“10:20\ior*
\io1 Instructions about вҖҳcleanвҖҷ and вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ \ior 11:1вҖ“15:33\ior*
\io1 The day for getting right with Yahweh \ior 16:1-34\ior*
\io1 Instructions for living and worshipping as a sacred people \ior 17:1вҖ“27:34\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Procedures for burnt sacrifices
\rem /s1 Sacrifices Burned Whole; The Burnt Offering; Offerings and sacrifices; Procedures for the Burnt Offering
\p
\v 1 YahwehВҰ46173 \add вүҲsummoned\add* MoshehВҰ46171 \add (MosesВҰ46171)\add* to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46175\add* tentВҰ46175 andВҰ46172 \add вүҲtold him\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTellВҰ46183 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ46182\add* that when anyoneВҰ46186 presents an offeringВҰ46205 to YahwehВҰ46192, it mustВҰ46184 be presented from their \add ?own\add* herd or flockВҰ46201.
\v 3 If it's from the herd, it must be a bull with noВҰ46215 defectsВҰ46215. It must be presentedВҰ46223 \add вүҲin frontВҰ46226 of\add* the entranceВҰ46219 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46221\add* tentВҰ46221 to be acceptableВҰ46225 to YahwehВҰ46227.
\v 4 \add @The owner\add* mustВҰ46229 place his handВҰ46230 on the headВҰ46232 of that offeringВҰ46233 to be burntВҰ46233, andВҰ46229 thenВҰ46229 it will be acceptedВҰ46234 \add вүҲmake him right with Yahweh\add*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ46239 he must slaughterВҰ46239 the \add вүҲbull in frontВҰ46244\add* of YahwehВҰ46245, and the priestsВҰ46249 (Aharon's \add (Aaron'sВҰ46248)\add* descendants), must presentВҰ46246 the blood and splash it all aroundВҰ46260 the altarВҰ46259 whichВҰ46261 is by the entranceВҰ46263 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46264\add* tent.
\v 6 ThenВҰ46267 \add @the presenter\add* mustВҰ46267 skin the \add вүҲbull\add* andВҰ46271 cut it into piecesВҰ46273,
\v 7 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the priestВҰ46278 Aharon's sons mustВҰ46275 put fire on the altarВҰ46282 andВҰ46275 arrangeВҰ46283 wood on the fire,
\v 8 and thenВҰ46289 \add *they\add* mustВҰ46289 arrangeВҰ46289 the piecesВҰ46294 (includingВҰ46298 the headВҰ46297 and the fat portions) on top of the burningВҰ46307 wood on the altarВҰ46311.
\v 9 ThenВҰ46313 \add @the presenter\add* must wash the innards and the feet withВҰ46316 waterВҰ46316, and the priestВҰ46318 must \add place it\add* onВҰ46316 the altarВҰ46322, \add вүҲensuring that everyВҰ46321 part is completely burntВҰ46323 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46327 aromaВҰ46325 for YahwehВҰ46328.
\p
\v 10 вҖңIf the offeringВҰ46344 is from the flockВҰ46335 (i.e., a sheepВҰ46339 or a goat), then itВҰ46347 mustВҰ46347 be a healthy maleВҰ46345 that's presentedВҰ46347,
\v 11 and thenВҰ46349 it must be slaughteredВҰ46349 on the northernВҰ46354 side of the altar facing YahwehВҰ46356, and Aharon'sВҰ46359 sonsВҰ46358, the priestsВҰ46360, must splash itsВҰ46363 bloodВҰ46363 on the altar, all aroundВҰ46367.
\v 12 ThenВҰ46369 \add @the presenter\add* must cut it into piecesВҰ46371 and they must arrangeВҰ46378 them (includingВҰ46372 the headВҰ46374 and fat portions) on top of the burningВҰ46387 wood on the altarВҰ46391.
\v 13 ThenВҰ46393 \add @the presenterВҰ46397\add* must wash the innards and the feet withВҰ46396 waterВҰ46396, and the priestВҰ46398 must \add place itВҰ46405\add* onВҰ46396 the altarВҰ46403, \add вүҲensuring that everyВҰ46401 part is completely burntВҰ46404 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46408 aromaВҰ46407 for YahwehВҰ46409.
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if his burntВҰ46416 offeringВҰ46416 to YahwehВҰ46418 will be a bird, then \add вүҲit mustВҰ46419 be either a doveВҰ46427 or a youngВҰ46426 pigeonВҰ46427\add*.
\v 15 The priestВҰ46433 mustВҰ46432 presentВҰ46432 it at the altar, and thenВҰ46432 twist its head off and burnВҰ46441 the head on the altar \add вүҲas he\add* drainsВҰ46443 the bloodВҰ46444 out onto the \add вүҲouter edge\add* of the altar.
\v 16 ThenВҰ46449 he mustВҰ46449 \add вүҲpull out\add* the crop withВҰ46453 its contentsВҰ46453, andВҰ46449 throwВҰ46454 it down onВҰ46453 the easternВҰ46458 side of the altarВҰ46457 where the ashesВҰ46462 are.
\v 17 He will thenВҰ46464 tear the bird \add mostly\add* apartВҰ46464 by its wingsВҰ46466 \add вүҲ(butВҰ46464 making sure that it stays as one piece)\add*, andВҰ46464 \add place it\add* onВҰ46466 the altarВҰ46472, \add вүҲensuring that every part is completely burntВҰ46480 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46484 aromaВҰ46483 for YahwehВҰ46485.
\c 2
\s1 Procedures for grain offerings
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Grain Offering; The Grain Offering; Grain Offerings
\p
\v 1 вҖңWhen someoneВҰ46488 presents a grainВҰ46493 offeringВҰ46493 to YahwehВҰ46494, it mustВҰ46491 be as fine, wheat flourВҰ46495 \add вүҲmixed with\add* \add olive\add*, and with frankincenseВҰ46503 added to the top of it.
\v 2 It mustВҰ46505 be taken to the priestВҰ46510 Aharon's sonsВҰ46508 who will take it \add from them\add*, thenВҰ46505 take a handfulВҰ46514 out, being sure to get flourВҰ46515, oilВҰ46516, and some frankincenseВҰ46520, and \add вүҲthrow that memorialВҰ46525 portionВҰ46525 onto\add* the altarВҰ46526 to get completely burnt up as a pleasingВҰ46529 aromaВҰ46528 for YahwehВҰ46530.
\v 3 ThenВҰ46532 the rest of that grainВҰ46535 offeringВҰ46535 will be for AharonВҰ46536 andВҰ46537 his sonsВҰ46537вҖ”it's a very sacredВҰ46538 part from the gifts for YahwehВҰ46541.
\p
\v 4 вҖңWhen someone presents something baked as their grainВҰ46547 offeringВҰ46547, it mustВҰ46545 be baked without leaven: either wheat flour mixedВҰ46553 with \add olive\add* oil and baked into flat buns, or else wheat flour biscuitsВҰ46555 with \add olive\add* oil \add вүҲspread onВҰ46554 top\add*.
\v 5 Or if yourВҰ46567 grainВҰ46563 offeringВҰ46563 is done onВҰ46570 the flat pan, itВҰ46572 mustВҰ46572 be wheat flourВҰ46568 mixedВҰ46569 withВҰ46570 \add olive\add* oilВҰ46570 \add вүҲandВҰ46561 made into flat biscuits\add*
\v 6 that should then be crumbledВҰ46574 andВҰ46577 have oilВҰ46579 poured over them as \add &your\add* grainВҰ46580 offeringВҰ46580.
\v 7 Or if yourВҰ46588 grainВҰ46586 offeringВҰ46586 is \add deep-fried\add* inВҰ46590 a pot, itВҰ46591 mustВҰ46591 be made from wheat flourВҰ46589 withВҰ46590 \add olive\add* oilВҰ46590.
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add Any of the above types of\add* grainВҰ46596 offeringВҰ46596 to YahwehВҰ46600 mustВҰ46593 be presentedВҰ46601 to the priestВҰ46604, andВҰ46593 he will takeВҰ46605 it to the altarВҰ46608.
\v 9 ThenВҰ46610 he mustВҰ46610 \add take a handful\add* as a memorialВҰ46617 portionВҰ46617 to the altarВҰ46619 to get completely burnt up as a pleasingВҰ46622 aromaВҰ46621 for YahwehВҰ46623.
\v 10 ThenВҰ46625 the rest of that grainВҰ46628 offeringВҰ46628 will be for AharonВҰ46629 andВҰ46630 his sonsВҰ46630вҖ”it's a very sacredВҰ46631 part from the gifts for YahwehВҰ46634.
\p
\v 11 вҖңAnything that's presentedВҰ46640 to Yahweh as a grainВҰ46638 offering mustВҰ46640 not be made with any rising agent, becauseВҰ46645 any leaven or honeyВҰ46651 mustn't be burnt as a gift to Yahweh.
\v 12 \add вүҲFoodsВҰ46663 containing those\add* can be presented as a first-fruits offering, butВҰ46664 theyВҰ46669 mustn't \add вүҲbe burnt\add* on the altarВҰ46666.
\v 13 \add вүҲHowever,\add* everyВҰ46687 grain offering must be saltedвҖ”the salt inВҰ46677 the grain offering is a reminder of our agreementВҰ46682, \add вүҲso it must always be present\add*.
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲFinally,\add* if you want to offer ripe grain as a grain offering to YahwehВҰ46699, then it mustВҰ46696 be a youngВҰ46700 ear of grain that's been roastedВҰ46701 over the fireВҰ46702 and presented as a grain offering of your firstВҰ46698 ripe grains
\v 15 \add вүҲwith\add* \add olive\add* oilВҰ46712 on itВҰ46717 andВҰ46713 some frankincenseВҰ46715 on top. That \add also becomes\add* a grainВҰ46716 offeringВҰ46716,
\v 16 and the priestВҰ46720 mustВҰ46719 burnВҰ46719 a memorialВҰ46723 portion from it with some of the crushedВҰ46724 grainsВҰ46724 and some of the oilВҰ46725 and some of the incense, \add to be burnt\add* to become smokeВҰ46719 as a gift to YahwehВҰ46731.
\c 3
\s1 Procedures for peace offerings
\rem /s1 The Fellowship Offering; Fellowship Offerings; Offerings of Well-Being; Procedures for the Peace Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖң\add вүҲNow\add* if it's a sacrificeВҰ46736 for a peaceВҰ46737 offeringВҰ46737, if it's from the \bd herd\bd*, then either a male or femaleВҰ46750 can be presentedВҰ46744 to YahwehВҰ46754 \add вүҲas long as it has noВҰ46751 defectsВҰ46751\add*.
\v 2 \add @The presenterВҰ46761\add* must lay their handВҰ46757 on the headВҰ46760 of the \add вүҲbull or cow\add*, thenВҰ46756 he must slaughterВҰ46762 it \add вүҲin front of\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46764\add* tentВҰ46764. ThenВҰ46756 the priestВҰ46769 Aharon'sВҰ46768 sonsВҰ46767 will splash the bloodВҰ46772 on the altarВҰ46775 \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 3 From thatВҰ46794 peaceВҰ46780 offeringВҰ46781, he mustВҰ46778 presentВҰ46778 the fat coveringВҰ46786 the innards andВҰ46778 whichВҰ46794 is part of the innards as a gift to YahwehВҰ46782,
\v 4 \add вүҲalong with bothВҰ46800\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ46816 (all of which need to be removedВҰ46820 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 5 ThenВҰ46822 Aharon'sВҰ46826 sonsВҰ46824 mustВҰ46822 burnВҰ46822 them on the wood \add вүҲthat's burningВҰ46838\add* on the altarВҰ46827 as a giftвҖ”to become smokeВҰ46822 as a pleasingВҰ46841 aromaВҰ46840 for YahwehВҰ46842.
\p
\v 6 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if the sacrificeВҰ46851 for a peaceВҰ46852 offeringВҰ46850 is from the \bd flockВҰ46849\bd*, then either a male or a femaleВҰ46856 can be presented to YahwehВҰ46853 \add вүҲas long as it has noВҰ46857 defectsВҰ46857\add*.
\v 7 When the offeringВҰ46868 is being presented, it mustВҰ46869 be presented \add вүҲin frontВҰ46871\add* of YahwehВҰ46872,
\v 8 and \add @the presenterВҰ46881\add* will put his handВҰ46877 on the headВҰ46880 of \add the animal being\add* offeredВҰ46881, and slaughterВҰ46882 it \add вүҲin frontВҰ46884\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46885\add* tentВҰ46885. ThenВҰ46874 Aharon'sВҰ46889 sonsВҰ46888 mustВҰ46874 splash its bloodВҰ46892 on the altarВҰ46895, \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 9 From thatВҰ46908 peaceВҰ46900 offeringВҰ46901, he mustВҰ46898 presentВҰ46898 the fat as a gift to YahwehВҰ46902, \add вүҲalong with\add* the entireВҰ46917 fatty tail (cut off near the backboneВҰ46907), the fat coveringВҰ46912 the innards andВҰ46898 which is part of the innards,
\v 10 \add вүҲbothВҰ46926\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ46942 (all of which need to be removedВҰ46946 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 11 ThenВҰ46948 the priestВҰ46949 mustВҰ46948 burnВҰ46948 them on the altarВҰ46950 as a food offeringВҰ46952 made to YahwehВҰ46953 by fireВҰ46952.
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲSimilarly,\add* if the offeringВҰ46958 is a \bd goatВҰ46957\bd*, then itВҰ46959 can be presented to YahwehВҰ46961.
\v 13 \add @The presenter\add* will put his handВҰ46966 on its headВҰ46969, andВҰ46963 slaughterВҰ46970 it \add вүҲin frontВҰ46972\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46973\add* tentВҰ46973. ThenВҰ46963 Aharon'sВҰ46977 sonsВҰ46976 mustВҰ46963 splash its bloodВҰ46980 on the altarВҰ46983, \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 14 From thatВҰ47002 peace offeringВҰ46989, he mustВҰ46986 presentВҰ46986 the fat as a gift to YahwehВҰ46990, \add вүҲalong with\add* the fat coveringВҰ46994 the innards andВҰ46986 whichВҰ47002 is part of the innards,
\v 15 \add вүҲbothВҰ47008\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ47024 (all of which need to be removedВҰ47028 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 16 ThenВҰ47030 the priestВҰ47031 mustВҰ47030 burnВҰ47030 them on the altarВҰ47032 as a food offeringВҰ47034 made to Yahweh by fireВҰ47034 as a pleasingВҰ47036 aromaВҰ47035. All the fat \add вүҲbelongs to\add* Yahweh.
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add This\add* regulationВҰ47042 must be permanentВҰ47043 for \add all\add* \add вүҲfuture\add* generationsВҰ47044: All of you must \add вүҲnever\add* eatВҰ47054 fat or bloodВҰ47052.вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 Procedures for sin offerings
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Sin Offering; Offerings for Unintentional Sins; Sin Offerings; The Sin Offering
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ47058 told MoshehВҰ47061 \add (MosesВҰ47061)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTellВҰ47068 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ47067\add* that if a person \add вүҲbreaks\add* any of Yahweh'sВҰ47078 regulations unintentionallyВҰ47075, or does anything that he said shouldn'tВҰ47080 be doneВҰ47081, \add then this is the procedure:\add*
\p
\v 3 вҖңIf it's \bd the \+add вүҲhigh\+add* priestВҰ47087\bd* \add вүҲwho's done it\add*, \add thatВҰ47095 causes\add* the \add вүҲnation\add* to be guiltyВҰ47090, and for hisВҰ47094 transgression he mustВҰ47089 presentВҰ47092 a bullВҰ47097 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47101 defectsВҰ47101\add* to YahwehВҰ47102 as a sin offeringВҰ47092.
\v 4 He must bringВҰ47105 the bull before Yahweh at the entranceВҰ47111 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47112\add* tent, thenВҰ47105 he must place his hand on \add *its\add* head andВҰ47105 slaughterВҰ47124 \add *it\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ47114\add* of Yahweh.
\v 5 ThenВҰ47131 the \add вүҲhigh\add* priestВҰ47132 mustВҰ47131 get some of the bull'sВҰ47135 bloodВҰ47134 andВҰ47131 bringingВҰ47136 it into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47140\add* tentВҰ47140,
\v 6 he must dip his fingerВҰ47147 into \add *it\add* andВҰ47143 sevenВҰ47153 timesВҰ47154 he must \add вүҲflick\add* the blood \add вүҲtowards\add* the \add вүҲfront\add* of the curtainВҰ47160 of the sanctuaryВҰ47161 \add вүҲinВҰ47148 front\add* of YahwehВҰ47156.
\v 7 Then the \add high\add* priestВҰ47164 must put some of the blood onВҰ47177 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the incense altar (\add вүҲlocated\add* inside the sacred tent \add вүҲinВҰ47177 frontВҰ47174\add* of YahwehВҰ47175 \add and\add* used for \add burning\add* fragrantВҰ47173 incense). Then \add he must go back outside and\add* pour \add вүҲthe rest\add* of the bull'sВҰ47184 blood out at the base of the altar for burntВҰ47190 offeringsВҰ47190 (which is \add out\add* at the entranceВҰ47193 to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent).
\v 8 ThenВҰ47197 \add @the high priest\add* mustВҰ47204 \add вүҲremove\add* all the fat from the bullВҰ47202 being offered as a sinВҰ47203 offeringВҰ47203, \add includingВҰ47213\add* the fat coveringВҰ47209 the innards andВҰ47213 whichВҰ47217 is a part of the innards,
\v 9 \add вүҲbothВҰ47223\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ47239 (all of which need to be removedВҰ47243 \add from the animal\add*)
\v 10 just \add вүҲlike you'd do\add* for the bullВҰ47247 of the peaceВҰ47249 offering. Then the priestВҰ47251 mustВҰ47250 burnВҰ47250 them on the altarВҰ47253 for the burntВҰ47254 offering.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the bull's hideВҰ47258 and its meatВҰ47264, plusВҰ47260 it's headВҰ47267 and feet, and innards and dung,
\v 12 must be taken outsideВҰ47282 the campВҰ47283 to the clean placeВҰ47286 where they pour out the ashes, and they must \add make\add* a fireВҰ47297 withВҰ47297 wood there onВҰ47297 top of the ashes and burnВҰ47292 it there.
\p
\v 13 вҖңIfВҰ47309 it's the \bd whole community\bd* that \add unintentionally\add* transgresses by doing something that YahwehВҰ47320 prohibited, then they'll be guiltyВҰ47325 even if the community didn'tВҰ47322 \add actually\add* noticeВҰ47313.\x + \xo 4:13-21: \xt Num 15:22-26.\x*
\v 14 \add вүҲWhenВҰ47327\add* they become aware of \add вүҲwhat they've done wrong\add*, thenВҰ47327 the community mustВҰ47327 presentВҰ47332 a \add вүҲyoungВҰ47335\add* bullВҰ47334 \add вүҲin frontВҰ47341\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47342\add* tent as a sin offeringВҰ47332.
\v 15 ThenВҰ47345 the communityВҰ47347 eldersВҰ47346 mustВҰ47345 place theirВҰ47350 handsВҰ47350 of the bull'sВҰ47354 headВҰ47353 \add вүҲin frontВҰ47355\add* of YahwehВҰ47356, andВҰ47357 slaughterВҰ47357 \add *it there\add*.
\v 16 The \add вүҲhigh\add* priestВҰ47365 mustВҰ47364 take some of the bull'sВҰ47368 bloodВҰ47367 into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47371\add* tentВҰ47371
\v 17 and sevenВҰ47381 timesВҰ47382 \add *he\add* mustВҰ47374 dip his fingerВҰ47376 in it and \add вүҲflick\add* the bloodВҰ47379 \add вүҲtowards\add* the \add вүҲfront\add* of the curtainВҰ47387 of the sanctuary \add вүҲin front\add* of YahwehВҰ47384.
\v 18 Then he must put some of the blood onВҰ47402 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the \add incense\add* altar (\add вүҲlocated\add* inside the sacred tent \add вүҲinВҰ47402 frontВҰ47399\add* of YahwehВҰ47400). Then \add he must go back outside andВҰ47389\add* pour \add вүҲthe rest of\add* the bull's blood out at the base of the altar for burntВҰ47413 offeringsВҰ47413 (which is \add out\add* at the entranceВҰ47416 to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent).
\v 19 ThenВҰ47420 he mustВҰ47424 \add вүҲremove\add* all the fat from \add @the slaughtered bull\add* andВҰ47420 burnВҰ47426 up \add @that fat\add* on the altarВҰ47427,
\v 20 and he should process the bull just the same as for a sin offeringВҰ47434. ThenВҰ47429 the priestВҰ47441 \add вүҲwill have made them right with God\add* and they'll be forgivenВҰ47442.
\v 21 ThenВҰ47445 he mustВҰ47445 take \add the remaining parts of\add* the bull outsideВҰ47451 the camp and burn it \add вүҲas described above\add* \add and\add* it will be the sin offeringВҰ47460 for the community.
\p
\v 22 вҖңIf it's \bd a leaderВҰ47466\bd* that \add unintentionallyВҰ47479\add* transgresses by doing something that his godВҰ47474 YahwehВҰ47473 prohibited, then he'll be guiltyВҰ47480.
\v 23 \add Alternatively, maybe someone else will point out his failing\add* to him. Then he mustВҰ47490 bringВҰ47490 an offeringВҰ47493 of a male goatВҰ47494 \add вүҲwithВҰ47489 noВҰ47497 defectsВҰ47497\add*.
\v 24 He mustВҰ47499 place his handВҰ47500 onВҰ47507 \add *its\add* headВҰ47503 andВҰ47499 slaughter it inВҰ47507 the place whereВҰ47508 \add the animals for\add* the burntВҰ47513 offering are slaughtered. It will be a sin offering,
\v 25 and the priestВҰ47520 mustВҰ47519 take some of the blood of that sin offering and withВҰ47523 his fingerВҰ47523, put some of the blood onВҰ47523 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burnt offerings.
\v 26 He mustВҰ47545 burn up all the fat on the altarВҰ47546 just like the fat from the peaceВҰ47549 offeringВҰ47549, and \add that way\add*, the priestВҰ47552 will make \add @that leader\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* and he'll be forgivenВҰ47554.
\p
\v 27 вҖңIf it's \bd an \+add ordinary\+add* personВҰ47560\bd* who \add unintentionallyВҰ47563\add* transgresses by doingВҰ47566 something thatВҰ47570 YahwehВҰ47569 prohibited, then they'll be guiltyВҰ47574.\x + \xo 4:27-31: \xt Num 15:27-28.\x*
\v 28 \add Alternatively, maybe someone else will point out their failing\add* to them. Then due to their transgression, \add @that person\add* mustВҰ47582 bringВҰ47582 an offeringВҰ47583 of a female goatВҰ47584 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47586 defectsВҰ47586\add*.
\v 29 He mustВҰ47594 place his handВҰ47597 onВҰ47605 the headВҰ47599 of the \add goat that's a\add* sin offering, andВҰ47594 slaughterВҰ47601 \add *it\add* atВҰ47605 the place for burntВҰ47606 offerings.
\v 30 ThenВҰ47608 the priestВҰ47609 mustВҰ47608 take some of the blood \add and\add* withВҰ47611 his fingerВҰ47611, put some of the blood onВҰ47611 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burntВҰ47617 offeringsВҰ47617, and thenВҰ47608 pour \add the rest of\add* the blood atВҰ47611 the altar's base.
\v 31 ThenВҰ47629 \add @the presenter\add* mustВҰ47634 pull out all the fat (just like it's done for the peaceВҰ47640 offeringВҰ47640), and the priestВҰ47642 will \add вүҲburnВҰ47641\add* it on the altarВҰ47643 to make a pleasingВҰ47645 aromaВҰ47644 for YahwehВҰ47646, and to \add вүҲmake that person right with God\add*, and they'll be forgivenВҰ47650.
\p
\v 32 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ47654\add* if it's a lambВҰ47656 that \add @the individual\add* wants to bring as their sinВҰ47659 offeringВҰ47659, then it mustВҰ47657 be a femaleВҰ47660 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47661 defectsВҰ47661\add*.
\v 33 \add @The presenter\add* mustВҰ47664 put their handВҰ47667 onВҰ47674 the headВҰ47669 of the \add вүҲlamb\add* andВҰ47664 slaughter it as a sin offering atВҰ47674 the placeВҰ47674 whereВҰ47675 burntВҰ47679 offerings are slaughtered.
\v 34 ThenВҰ47681 the priestВҰ47682 mustВҰ47681 take some of the blood \add and\add* withВҰ47685 his fingerВҰ47685, put some of the blood onВҰ47685 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burntВҰ47691 offerings, and thenВҰ47681 pour \add the rest of\add* the blood atВҰ47685 the altar's base.
\v 35 ThenВҰ47703 \add @the presenter\add* mustВҰ47708 pull out all the fat (just like it's done for the peaceВҰ47715 offeringВҰ47721), and the priestВҰ47717 will \add вүҲburnВҰ47716\add* it on the altarВҰ47719 to make a pleasing aroma for YahwehВҰ47722, and to \add вүҲmake thatВҰ47729 person right with God\add*, and they'll be forgivenВҰ47732.
\c 5
\s1 More needs for sin offerings
\rem /s1 Cases Requiring Sin Offerings; Sins Requiring a Sin Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖңIf someoneВҰ47736 is a witnessВҰ47744 to a case \add вүҲbecauseВҰ47737 of something they sawВҰ47746 or knewВҰ47748 about\add*, and hearsВҰ47740 an oath \add in court\add* butВҰ47736 doesn't \add вүҲtestify\add*, then they'll \add вүҲbecome guiltyВҰ47754\add*.
\p
\v 2 вҖңIf someoneВҰ47757 touchesВҰ47759 anything вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ (e.g., a dead domestic or wild animalВҰ47766, or some creature) \add вүҲwithout realising it\add*, they \add still\add* become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ and is guiltyВҰ47781.
\p
\v 3 вҖңIf someone touchesВҰ47785 anything вҖҳuncleanВҰ47791вҖҷ from \add another\add* person, even if they \add initially\add* \add вүҲdidn't realise what it was\add*, they become guiltyВҰ47797.
\p
\v 4 вҖңIf someoneВҰ47800 makes a rash promise, whether it's to do something goodВҰ47808 or something bad, and even if they were \add just\add* speakingВҰ47811 carelessly butВҰ47814 find out \add later\add*, they become guiltyВҰ47819.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ47823 thenВҰ47823\add* \add @the person\add* that became guiltyВҰ47826 from any of the above, mustВҰ47826 confessВҰ47829 their wrongdoing
\v 6 and present a penaltyВҰ47837 to YahwehВҰ47838 to address thatВҰ47841 wrongdoing, and mustВҰ47834 present a female lambВҰ47847 or young goatВҰ47850 as a sin offeringВҰ47852, and the priestВҰ47855 will \add act on their behalf\add* \add вүҲto make them right with God\add*.
\p
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲHowever if thatВҰ47870 person can'tВҰ47860 afford\add* a sheepВҰ47865, thenВҰ47858 for their guiltВҰ47869 offering because of \add вүҲtheir transgression\add*, they mustВҰ47861 bringВҰ47866 two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ47877\add* pigeons to YahwehВҰ47880вҖ”one for a sinВҰ47882 offering andВҰ47858 one for a burntВҰ47884 offering.
\v 8 \add @The presenter\add* mustВҰ47886 take them to the priestВҰ47890 who will present the sinВҰ47895 offeringВҰ47891 firstВҰ47896вҖ”twisting \add @the bird's\add* headВҰ47900 off from the neck, \add вүҲbutВҰ47886\add* not \add вүҲpulling\add* the body \add in half\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ47906 he mustВҰ47906 sprinkleВҰ47906 some of the blood from that sin offering onto the side of the altar, andВҰ47906 thenВҰ47906 drainВҰ47915 out the rest of the blood atВҰ47914 the altar's base. That will be the sin offering.
\v 10 The secondВҰ47925 \add >bird\add* will be for a burntВҰ47927 offeringВҰ47926 as per the regulationВҰ47928. The priestВҰ47931 will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* after their wrongdoing, andВҰ47923 they'll be forgivenВҰ47936.
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲHowever if thatВҰ47956 person still can'tВҰ47942 afford\add* those two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ47949\add* pigeons, then they can presentВҰ47955 a kilogram of fine wheat flourВҰ47960 for a sin offering. It mustn't have oilВҰ47966 or frankincenseВҰ47971 in it becauseВҰ47972 it's a sin offering.
\v 12 \add @The presenter\add* mustВҰ47976 take it to the priestВҰ47979 who will thenВҰ47976 take a handful of it, andВҰ47976 burnВҰ47989 that memorialВҰ47988 portionВҰ47988 on the altarВҰ47990 for burnt offeringsВҰ47992 to YahwehВҰ47993. That will be the sinВҰ47994 offering.
\v 13 The priest will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* after their wrongdoing as per one of the above, andВҰ47997 they'll be forgivenВҰ48008. \add The rest of\add* \add @the flour\add* will be for the priest, similar to a grainВҰ48012 offeringВҰ48012.вҖқ
\s1 More on guilt offerings
\rem /s1 Repayment Offerings; The Guilt Offering; Procedures for the Guilt Offering; Offerings with Restitution
\p
\v 14 Then YahwehВҰ48016 told MoshehВҰ48019 \add (MosesВҰ48019)\add*,
\v 15 вҖңIfВҰ48035 someone acts unfaithfullyВҰ48025 \add вүҲbutВҰ48027\add* unintentionallyВҰ48028 \add вүҲdesecrates something that's sacredВҰ48029\add* to YahwehВҰ48030, then becauseВҰ48023 of their guilt, \add @that person\add* mustВҰ48025 present ram \add вүҲwithВҰ48028 noВҰ48037 defectsВҰ48037\add* from the flockВҰ48040, or silverВҰ48042 \add вүҲcoins using the official valuationВҰ48041\add*, as a guilt offering.
\v 16 They must also compensate for the sacredВҰ48055 item, butВҰ48050 with an extra twentyВҰ48059 percentВҰ48060. That must all be given to the priest who will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* with thatВҰ48051 ram as the guiltВҰ48069 offeringВҰ48069, andВҰ48050 they'll be forgivenВҰ48070.
\p
\v 17 вҖңIf someoneВҰ48076 transgresses by violatingВҰ48079 \add even\add* one of Yahweh'sВҰ48084 \add вүҲregulations or prohibitions\add*, even if they didn'tВҰ48086 realise itВҰ48078, they become guilty and mustВҰ48078 bear responsibility for thatВҰ48085 guilt.
\v 18 ThenВҰ48095 \add @that person\add* mustВҰ48095 take a ram from the flockВҰ48100 that \add вүҲhas noВҰ48097 defectsВҰ48097\add* to the priest for a guiltВҰ48102 offeringВҰ48102. Then the priest will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright withВҰ48101 God\add* after that transgression (even if they weren't aware of it), andВҰ48095 they'll be forgivenВҰ48118.
\v 19 That's a guilt offeringВҰ48121, because they were clearly guilty before YahwehВҰ48125.вҖқ
\c 6
\rem /s1 Sins Requiring a Guilt Offering
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ48271 told MoshehВҰ48274 \add (MosesВҰ48274)\add*,\x + \xo 6:1-7: \xt Num 5:5-8.\x*
\v 2 вҖңSomeone who transgresses against Yahweh by \add вүҲcheating\add* with respect to a deposit or a pledge, or by theft or extortion,
\v 3 or by finding lost property and then denying itВҰ48324, or making an oath that was knowingly false, or by any other typical transgression that people do,
\v 4 then they've become guilty as a result of that transgression. \add @That person\add* mustВҰ48337 return what was stolen or extorted, or \add вүЎreturn\add* the deposit or the lost property,
\v 5 or \add вүҲmake amends for a false oath\add*. They mustВҰ48362 return the full value plusВҰ48358 an extra twenty percent \add вүҲas soon as the guilt is discovered\add*.
\v 6 Then \add @that person\add* mustВҰ48384 take a ram from the flock \add вүҲwith no defects\add* to the priest as a guilt offering to Yahweh,
\v 7 and the priest will make \add @the presenterВҰ48397\add* \add вүҲright with YahwehВҰ48403\add* after whatever that transgression was to make them guilty, and they'll be forgiven.
\s1 The fire and the ashes
\rem /s1 Further Instructions for the Burnt Offering; Sacrifices Burned Whole; The Burnt Offering; Instructions concerning Sacrifices
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ48429 told Mosheh,
\v 9 вҖңTell Aharon \add (AaronВҰ48435)\add* and his sonsВҰ48436 that these are the \add #regulations\add* for the burnt \add #offerings\add*: The burnt offering must remainВҰ48432 on the altar's hearth, on the altar all night until the morning and the fire \add вүҲmust be kept burning\add* on it.
\v 10 ThenВҰ48452 the priest mustВҰ48449 \add вүҲput on\add* his linen underwear and linen robe and \add вүҲremove\add* the fatty ashes from the burnt \add #offerings\add* on the altar, and pile them beside \add *it\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲAfter that\add*, he'll \add вүҲget changed again into his regular\add* clothes and take \add &those\add* ashes outside the camp to a вҖҳcleanвҖҷ place.
\v 12 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the fire on the altar must be kept burningвҖ”it must never go out. Every morning the priest must put more wood on the fire, then he must arrange more offerings on the fireвҖ”he should burn the fat of the fellowship offerings on that fire so the smoke rises.
\v 13 \add Yes,\add* the fire mustВҰ48497 burn continuallyВҰ48506 onВҰ48508 the altarвҖ”never going out.
\s1 Procedures for the grain offering
\rem /s1 Further Instructions for the Grain Offering; The Grain Offering; Grain Offerings
\p
\v 14 вҖңHere's the regulations for the grainВҰ48521 offeringВҰ48521: Aharon's sons mustВҰ48517 presentВҰ48523 it \add вүҲbefore\add* YahwehВҰ48527 \add вүҲinВҰ48516 front\add* of the altar.
\v 15 \add @The priestВҰ48530\add* mustВҰ48534 take a handful of the flour from that grain offeringВҰ48534, being sure it includes some of the oil and the incense, and burn it on the altar as a memorial portionВҰ48536 to become a pleasing aroma for YahwehВҰ48539.
\v 16 The remainder \add of that flour\add* will be \add вүҲused as food\add* for Aharon andВҰ48544 his sonsвҖ”they mustВҰ48549 eat the flat bread in a sacred place, i.e., in the courtyard of the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 17 It must not be baked with any rising agent. I give that to them from \add вүҲwhat's given to me\add*. It's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred just like the sin offering andВҰ48555 the guilt offering.
\v 18 Any of Aharon's male descendants can eat itвҖ”it'll be their portion from Yahweh's gifts throughout the generations. Anyone who touches \add @Yahweh's gifts\add* will become sacredВҰ48582 \add themself\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Procedures for the ordination offering
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Ordination Offering
\p
\v 19 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 20 вҖңOn the day when one of Aharon's male descendants is consecrated as a priest, this is what he mustВҰ48602 present to Yahweh: a continual grain offering of a kilogram of fine wheat flourвҖ”half for the morning and half for the evening.
\v 21 It must be mixed with \add olive\add* oil then cooked with oil onВҰ48629 a flat pan. It must then be brokenВҰ48626 into pieces and presented as a grain offering to make a pleasing aroma for Yahweh.
\v 22 The priest who's next inВҰ48640 line to become \add вүҲhigh\add* priest must offer it and it must be completely burnt for Yahweh. This is a permanent regulation.
\v 23 Any grain offeringВҰ48650 by a priest must be completely burntВҰ48663вҖ”it must not be eatenВҰ48661.вҖқ
\s1 Procedures for the sin offering
\rem /s1 Sin Offerings; Further Instructions for the Sin Offering; The Sin Offering
\p
\v 24 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 25 вҖңTell Aharon and his sons that these are the \add #regulations\add* for the sin \add #offerings\add*: The sin offering must be slaughtered \add вүҲin front\add* of Yahweh at the place where the burnt \add #offerings\add* are slaughtered. It's a \add вүҲvery\add* sacred \add activity\add*.
\v 26 The priest who offers the sin offering \add вүҲmust be the one to eat it\add*. It must be eaten in a sacred place, i.e., in the courtyard of the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 27 Everything that touches the \add animal's\add* body will become sacred. Anyone who \add вүҲgets the blood on their\add* clothes, must wash them in a sacred place.
\v 28 Any clay pot that it's been boiled in, must then be shattered, but if it's boiled in a bronze pot, then that must be scoured and rinsed with water.
\v 29 Any male in the priests' \add families\add* may eat itвҖ”it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred.
\v 30 \add вүҲHowever,\add* every sin offering that has its blood taken inside the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent to make \add вүҲsomeone right with God\add*, then that \add meat\add* mustn't be eatenвҖ”it must be completely burnt up.
\c 7
\s1 Procedures for the guilt offering
\rem /s1 Repayment Offerings; The Guilt Offering; Further Instructions for the Guilt Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖңThen these are the \add #regulations\add* for the \add вүҲvery\add* sacredВҰ48669 guiltВҰ48668 \add #offerings\add*:
\v 2 The guiltВҰ48682 offering must be slaughtered at the same placeВҰ48673 as the burntВҰ48678 \add #offerings\add*, andВҰ48683 the bloodВҰ48685 must be splashed on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ48689.
\v 3 \add @The presenter\add* mustВҰ48696 present all the fat \add includingВҰ48700\add* the fatty tail, the fat coveringВҰ48703 the innards,
\v 4 \add вүҲbothВҰ48709\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ48725 (\add вүҲall of which\add* need to be removedВҰ48729 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 5 ThenВҰ48731 the priestВҰ48733 mustВҰ48731 burnВҰ48731 those on the altarВҰ48734 as a guiltВҰ48737 offering to YahwehВҰ48736.
\v 6 Any maleВҰ48742 inВҰ48743 the priests' \add families\add* may eatВҰ48744 itвҖ”it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacredВҰ48746.
\v 7 The regulations are the same for the guilt offering as for the sinВҰ48752 offeringвҖ”the priestВҰ48757 who \add вүҲoffers the guilt offering\add* \add вүҲmustВҰ48759 be the one to eat it\add*.
\p
\v 8 вҖңWhenever a priest presents someone's burnt offering, the skinВҰ48771 of the animal that was presented belongsВҰ48777 to that priest.
\v 9 Any grainВҰ48781 offeringВҰ48781 that's bakedВҰ48783 in an oven, or cooked in a pan or onВҰ48784 a griddle, will belongВҰ48796 to the priestВҰ48792 who presentsВҰ48793 it.
\v 10 Any grainВҰ48800 offeringВҰ48800 that's either dry or mixedВҰ48801 withВҰ48803 oilВҰ48803, belongsВҰ48809 to all of Aharon's male descendants \add вүҲwithout any distinction\add*.
\s1 Procedures for the peace offering
\rem /s1 The Fellowship Offering; Further Instructions; Fellowship Offerings; Further Instructions for the Peace Offering
\p
\v 11 вҖңThen these are the \add #regulations\add* for sacrificingВҰ48816 peaceВҰ48817 offeringsВҰ48817 to presentВҰ48819 to YahwehВҰ48820:
\v 12 If it's presented \add вүҲfrom thankfulness\add*, then the sacrificeВҰ48831 \add вүҲmustВҰ48826 be accompanied by\add* thanksgiving flat bread buns (\add made from flour\add* mixed with \add olive\add* oil), and flat biscuitsВҰ48837 smearedВҰ48839 with oil, and buns \add made from\add* fine wheat flour mixed with oil,
\v 13 \add вүҲplus\add* risen breadВҰ48850 rolls. \add All that\add* mustВҰ48852 accompany the peaceВҰ48858 offeringВҰ48853 \add вүҲfrom thankfulnessВҰ48857\add*.
\v 14 ThenВҰ48860 he mustВҰ48860 present one of each \add kind of bread\add* as a contributionВҰ48866 to YahwehВҰ48867. Those will belongВҰ48875 to the priestВҰ48868 who splashes the bloodВҰ48872 for the peaceВҰ48873 offeringsВҰ48873.
\v 15 The meat of the thankfulnessВҰ48879 sacrificeВҰ48878 of those peaceВҰ48880 offeringsВҰ48880 mustВҰ48883 be eatenВҰ48883 the \add вүҲsame dayВҰ48881 that it's offeredвҖ”none of can be left\add* untilВҰ48888 morningВҰ48890.
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the sacrificed offering is a vow or freewillВҰ48897 offering, thenВҰ48892 it can be eaten that same day andВҰ48892 \add also\add* the next day,
\v 17 \add вүҲbutВҰ48911\add* any left-over meat mustВҰ48917 be burntВҰ48917 up on the fireВҰ48916 on the thirdВҰ48915 dayВҰ48914.
\v 18 If any of that meat from the sacrificeВҰ48924 was eaten on the thirdВҰ48927 dayВҰ48926, the presenterВҰ48930 won't be acceptedВҰ48929 and \add вүҲthey won't be forgiven\add*. It is spoilt, and anyoneВҰ48930 who eatsВҰ48938 any of it will bear their own \add вүҲguilt\add*.
\v 19 If any meat touchesВҰ48946 anything that's вҖҳuncleanВҰ48949вҖҷ, thenВҰ48943 it must not be eatenвҖ”it must be burntВҰ48953 up inВҰ48952 the fireВҰ48952. \add вүҲHowever,\add* any long as the meat remains вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, it can be eaten by any person who's вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 20 IfВҰ48969 a person who was вҖҳuncleanВҰ48970вҖҷ were to eat any of the meat from the sacrificeВҰ48966 for a peaceВҰ48967 offeringВҰ48967, thenВҰ48961 thatВҰ48968 \add >person\add* mustВҰ48964 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲSimilarly,\add* when a person touchesВҰ48980 anything вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ (e.g., humanВҰ48985 uncleanness, or an unclean animalВҰ48988, or a detestableВҰ48993 creatureВҰ49003), andВҰ48977 thenВҰ48977 they eat some of the meat of the sacrificeВҰ48998 for a peaceВҰ48999 offeringВҰ48999 that \add now\add* belongs to YahwehВҰ49001, that \add >person\add* mustВҰ48980 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\s1 Don't eat fat or blood
\rem /s1 Eating Fat and Blood Forbidden; The Forbidden Blood and Fat
\p
\v 22 Then YahwehВҰ49009 told MoshehВҰ49012,
\v 23 вҖңTellВҰ49019 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49018\add* that you all must not eatВҰ49028 the fat from \add #cattle or sheepВҰ49025 or goats\add*,
\v 24 вҮ”plus you all definitely mustВҰ49034 not eat the fat from an animal \add вүҲthat died naturally or was killed by wild animals although you can use it for other purposes\add*.
\v 25 AnyoneВҰ49045 who does eat the fat from an animal presentedВҰ49051 as a gift to YahwehВҰ49054 mustВҰ49051 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\p
\v 26 вҖң\add вүҲAlsoВҰ49060,\add* you all must not eatВҰ49064 bloodВҰ49062 from either a bird or an animalВҰ49068, \add вүҲno matter where you're livingВҰ49066\add*.\x + \xo 7:26-27: \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 17:10-14; 19:26; Deu 12:16,23; 15:23.\x*
\v 27 Any personВҰ49072 who does eatВҰ49075 bloodВҰ49078 mustВҰ49075 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The priests' portions
\rem /s1 The Priests' Share; A Portion for the Priests
\p
\v 28 Then YahwehВҰ49086 told MoshehВҰ49089,
\v 29 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49095\add* that anyoneВҰ49098 who offers a peace offering to Yahweh mustВҰ49104 take \add вүҲsome of it as\add* his peace offering to Yahweh.
\v 30 They mustВҰ49113 \add вүҲpersonally carry\add* Yahweh'sВҰ49116 gift \add which will be\add* the breast with its fat and raise it \add вүҲin frontВҰ49129\add* of Yahweh as a wave offeringВҰ49115,
\v 31 and the priestВҰ49133 mustВҰ49132 burnВҰ49132 that fat up on the altarВҰ49137 \add вүҲbutВҰ49132\add* the breastВҰ49139 will be for AharonВҰ49140 and his sonsВҰ49141.
\v 32 The rightВҰ49145 thighВҰ49144 from the sacrificesВҰ49149 of your peaceВҰ49150 offeringsВҰ49150 mustВҰ49146 be given to the priestВҰ49148вҖ”
\v 33 whichever \add вүҲpriest (Aharon'sВҰ49161 descendant) who handled\add* the bloodВҰ49155 of the peaceВҰ49156 offeringsВҰ49152 andВҰ49157 the fat, that rightВҰ49165 thighВҰ49164 will be his portionВҰ49166
\v 34 because I took the breastВҰ49171 from the wave offering and the thighВҰ49175 from the contributionВҰ49176 of the \add вүҲIsraelis'\add* peaceВҰ49183 offeringsВҰ49183, and I gaveВҰ49184 them to Aharon the priestВҰ49187 and his sons as an ongoing portionВҰ49189 from the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ49179 people\add*.
\v 35 That's the shareВҰ49197 for Aharon andВҰ49199 his sonsВҰ49200 from the gifts to Yahweh since Mosheh presentedВҰ49204 them to Yahweh as priestsВҰ49206.
\v 36 YahwehВҰ49211 commandedВҰ49210 them to be givenВҰ49212 to them \add back\add* on the dayВҰ49214 when he anointedВҰ49215 them out of all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ49218 peopleВҰ49218\add* \add and made it\add* a permanentВҰ49221 regulation for \add future\add* generationsВҰ49222.
\p
\v 37 \add #Those are the regulations\add* for the burntВҰ49226 \add #offerings\add*, the grainВҰ49227 \add #offerings\add*, the sinВҰ49228 \add #offerings\add*, the guiltВҰ49229 \add #offerings\add*, the ordinationВҰ49230 \add #offerings\add*, and the peaceВҰ49232 \add #offerings\add*
\v 38 that Yahweh \add вүҲgave to\add* MoshehВҰ49239 atВҰ49240 MtВҰ49240. Sinai onВҰ49240 the dayВҰ49242 when he orderedВҰ49235 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49246\add* to presentВҰ49248 theirВҰ49251 offeringsВҰ49251 to Yahweh \add when they were there\add* inВҰ49240 the Sinai wildernessВҰ49253.
\c 8
\s1 Ordination of Aharon and his sons
\rem /s1 The Rites of Ordination; Ordination of the Priests; The priesthood; The Ordination of Aaron and His Sons
\r (Exo. 29:1-37)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ49258 told MoshehВҰ49261 \add (MosesВҰ49261)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTake Aharon \add (AaronВҰ49267)\add* and his sonsВҰ49270 with their clothesВҰ49273 and the anointingВҰ49276 oilВҰ49275, and the bullВҰ49279 for the sinВҰ49280 offeringВҰ49280 and twoВҰ49282 rams, and a basketВҰ49285 of unleavenedВҰ49286 breadВҰ49286,
\v 3 andВҰ49288 assembleВҰ49292 the entireВҰ49289 \add вүҲcommunity\add* at the entranceВҰ49295 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49296\add* tentВҰ49296.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ49299\add* MoshehВҰ49300 did exactly has YahwehВҰ49303 had commandedВҰ49302 him, andВҰ49305 the \add вүҲpeople\add* assembledВҰ49305 at the entranceВҰ49309 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49310\add* tentВҰ49310.
\v 5 ThenВҰ49313 MoshehВҰ49314 told the \add вүҲassembled people\add*, вҖңThis \add ceremony\add* is what YahwehВҰ49323 has told us to do.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ49326 MoshehВҰ49327 presentedВҰ49326 AharonВҰ49330 and his sonsВҰ49333 and \add after\add* washing them with waterВҰ49336,
\v 7 he put the tunicВҰ49342 on \add @Aharon\add* and wrapped the sashВҰ49345 \add around\add* him, and thenВҰ49338 put the robeВҰ49350 on him. ThenВҰ49338 he put the sacred apron on him, tying \add *its\add* finely woven waistband to fasten it onto him.
\v 8 ThenВҰ49364 he \add вүҲattached\add* the chest pouch and put the Urim and Tummim into the pouch.
\v 9 \add вүҲFinally\add* he placed the turban on his headВҰ49386, andВҰ49380 fastened the goldenВҰ49397 flower-shaped plateВҰ49396 (that sacredВҰ49399 crownВҰ49398 that demonstrates that Aharon is set apart to only serve Yahweh) to the frontВҰ49393 of the turban, exactly as Yahweh had instructedВҰ49401 MoshehВҰ49405.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ49407 MoshehВҰ49408 tookВҰ49407 the anointing oilВҰ49411 and anointed \add &Yahweh's\add* residence and everything in it, thus consecratingВҰ49424 \add вүҲit all\add*.
\v 11 Seven timesВҰ49433 he flicked some of it onto the altarвҖ”anointingВҰ49434 the altar and all its utensilsВҰ49442 and the basin and its base, thus consecrating them.
\v 12 He pouredВҰ49451 some of the anointing oilВҰ49452 over Aharon's headВҰ49455, thus anointing him to consecrate him.
\v 13 ThenВҰ49461 Mosheh presentedВҰ49461 Aharon's sonsВҰ49465 and dressed them in tunicsВҰ49468 and wrapped sashes around each of them, and tied their headbands onto them, just as YahwehВҰ49477 had instructedВҰ49476 Mosheh.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ49482 he broughtВҰ49482 the bull for the sin offering, and AharonВҰ49487 and his sons placed theirВҰ49491 handsВҰ49491 on \add *its\add* head.
\v 15 Then \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:15 \ft It's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was still referring to Aharon here.\f* slaughtered it, and Mosheh took the blood and used his fingerВҰ49510 to put some on the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar, thus purifying the altar. Then he pouredВҰ49518 \add the rest of\add* the blood out at the altar's base, sanctifying it \add вүҲso it could be used for making people right with God\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ49548 \add @Mosheh\add* tookВҰ49527 all the far thatВҰ49533 was on the innards and the lobe of the liverВҰ49539, and the twoВҰ49542 kidneysВҰ49543 and theirВҰ49546 fat, and \add *he\add* burnt them up on the altarВҰ49549.
\v 17 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ49572,\add* he burntВҰ49563 up \add the rest of\add* the bullВҰ49553 \add вүҲincludingВҰ49554\add* its hideВҰ49556, fleshВҰ49559, andВҰ49551 dung, outsideВҰ49565 the campВҰ49566, just as YahwehВҰ49569 had toldВҰ49568 \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ49574 \add @Mosheh\add* presentedВҰ49574 the ram for the burntВҰ49577 offeringВҰ49577, and AharonВҰ49579 and his sonsВҰ49580 placed theirВҰ49583 handsВҰ49583 on its headВҰ49586.
\v 19 ThenВҰ49589 \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:19 \ft It's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was still referring to Aharon here.\f* slaughtered it, andВҰ49590 Mosheh splashed the bloodВҰ49594 on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ49597.
\v 20 ThenВҰ49600 \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:20 \ft Again it's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was referring to Aharon (and possibly including his sons) here.\f* cut the ram into pieces, and Mosheh burnt up the headВҰ49609, and the pieces and the fat.
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:20 \ft Again it's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was referring to Aharon here.\f* washedВҰ49623 the innards andВҰ49617 the legs, thenВҰ49617 Mosheh \add also\add* burnt \add *those\add* up on the altarВҰ49632 as a burnt offering that was pleasingВҰ49637 aromaВҰ49635 for Yahweh, just as Yahweh had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ49642\add* Mosheh.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ49648 \add ?@Mosheh\add* presentedВҰ49648 the secondВҰ49652 ram for the ordination offeringВҰ49654, and AharonВҰ49656 and his sonsВҰ49657 placed theirВҰ49660 handsВҰ49660 on the ram's headВҰ49663.
\v 23 ThenВҰ49666 \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:19 \ft It's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was still referring to Aharon here.\f* slaughtered it, and Mosheh tookВҰ49668 some of its bloodВҰ49670 and put it on the lobe of Aharon's right earВҰ49675, on his right thumbВҰ49681, and on his right bigВҰ49686 toeВҰ49686.
\v 24 Then he presentedВҰ49690 Aharon's sons and put some of the blood on their right earlobes, and their right thumbsВҰ49707, and their right big toes. Then Mosheh splashed the blood on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ49722.
\v 25 He \add вүҲcollected\add* the fat and the fatty tail, and all the fat thatВҰ49737 was on the innards and the lobe of the liverВҰ49743, and the twoВҰ49746 kidneysВҰ49747 with theirВҰ49750 fat, and the rightВҰ49753 thighВҰ49752,
\v 26 ThenВҰ49755 from the basketВҰ49755 of unleavened bread that was there \add вүҲin frontВҰ49759\add* of YahwehВҰ49760, he took one flat bread bun, and one flat bread that had been smeared with oil, and one flat biscuit, and placed them on \add top of\add* the fat and the rightВҰ49777 thighВҰ49776.
\v 27 He place \add вүҲall that\add* onto the \add вүҲopen hands\add* of Aharon andВҰ49779 his sonsВҰ49788 who raised them as a wave offering \add вүҲin frontВҰ49792\add* of YahwehВҰ49793.
\v 28 ThenВҰ49795 MoshehВҰ49796 took \add вүҲit all again\add*, andВҰ49795 burnt it all up on the altarВҰ49801 with the burnt offering. That ordination offering on the fireВҰ49809 became a pleasingВҰ49808 aromaВҰ49807 for YahwehВҰ49811.
\v 29 ThenВҰ49813 Mosheh took the breastВҰ49817 \add meat\add* from the ram for the ordination offering, andВҰ49813 raised it as a wave offering \add вүҲin frontВҰ49820\add* of Yahweh, just as Yahweh had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ49828\add* \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ49834 MoshehВҰ49835 took some of the anointingВҰ49837 oilВҰ49836 and some of the bloodВҰ49840 from on the altarВҰ49844, and he \add вүҲflicked\add* them onto Aharon and his clothes, his sons and \add *their\add* clothes, thus consecratingВҰ49860 Aharon and his clothes, and his sons and \add *their\add* clothes.
\p
\v 31 ThenВҰ49876 MoshehВҰ49877 toldВҰ49901 Aharon and his sons, вҖңBoil the meat at the entranceВҰ49888 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49889\add* tent and eat it, along with the \add flat\add* breadВҰ49896 that's in the basketВҰ49898 \add вүҲas part of\add* the ordination offeringВҰ49899, just as I \add вүҲhad instructedВҰ49901 that\add* Aharon and his sons should eat it.
\v 32 \add вүҲAny\add* meat or breadВҰ49909 \add вүҲthat's leftover\add* mustВҰ49911 be burnt in the fireВҰ49910.
\v 33 None of you may leave the entranceВҰ49913 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49914\add* tent for seven days. \add That's becauseВҰ49925\add* \add @Yahweh\add* will ordain you all over those seven days.
\v 34 What's been doneВҰ49934 today has been \add вүҲinitiated\add* by YahwehВҰ49938 in order to make \add вүҲyou all right with him\add*,
\v 35 \add вүҲso\add* remainВҰ49946 here dayВҰ49947 and nightВҰ49948 at the entranceВҰ49943 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49944\add* tentВҰ49944 for sevenВҰ49949 daysВҰ49950 as per Yahweh'sВҰ49955 \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ49961\add* and you all won'tВҰ49956 dieВҰ49957, becauseВҰ49958 that's what I'veВҰ49961 been commandedВҰ49961.вҖқ
\v 36 \add вүҲSoВҰ49963\add* AharonВҰ49964 andВҰ49963 his sonsВҰ49965 did everything thatВҰ49970 YahwehВҰ49973 had instructedВҰ49972 them via MoshehВҰ49976.
\c 9
\s1 The priests start their duties
\rem /s1 Aaron Offers Sacrifices; Aaron's Priesthood Inaugurated; The Priests Begin Their Work; The Priests Begin Their Ministry
\p
\v 1 On the eighthВҰ49981 dayВҰ49980, MoshehВҰ49983 summonedВҰ49982 Aharon and his sonsВҰ49985, along with Yisrael's eldersВҰ49986,
\v 2 and he told Aharon, вҖңGet a healthy, \add вүҲyoungВҰ49997\add*, male calf for a sin offering for yourselfВҰ49995, and a ram \add вүҲwithoutВҰ50003 defectsВҰ50003\add* for a burntВҰ50002 offering, and presentВҰ50004 them to YahwehВҰ50006.
\v 3 ThenВҰ50008 tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ50010 peopleВҰ50010\add* to take a male goatВҰ50015 for a sin offering, and a calf and a lambВҰ50020, both a year old and \add вүҲwithoutВҰ50024 defectsВҰ50024\add* for a burntВҰ50025 offering,
\v 4 as well as a bullВҰ50027 and a ram to sacrificeВҰ50030 to Yahweh as peaceВҰ50029 offeringsВҰ50029, and a grainВҰ50033 offeringВҰ50033 mixedВҰ50034 will oilВҰ50035, becauseВҰ50036 Yahweh will appearВҰ50039 to you all today.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ50042\add* they brought \add everything\add* to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ50050\add* tentВҰ50050 thatВҰ50044 MoshehВҰ50046 had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ50045\add* them, andВҰ50042 the whole assembly presented them as they stoodВҰ50056 \add вүҲbefore\add* YahwehВҰ50058,
\v 6 thenВҰ50060 MoshehВҰ50061 saidВҰ50060, вҖңYou'veВҰ50072 done what YahwehВҰ50067 toldВҰ50066 you, so now you'll all see his \add вүҲbrightness\add* appearВҰ50069.вҖқ
\v 7 Then \add *he\add* toldВҰ50102 Aharon, вҖң\add вүҲGo\add* to the altarВҰ50082 and make your sin offering and your burntВҰ50089 offering to make \add вүҲyourselfВҰ50091 and the people right with God\add*. Then make the people's offering to make \add вүҲthem right with God\add*, just as YahwehВҰ50103 commandedВҰ50102.вҖқ\x + \xo 9:7: \xt Heb 7:27.\x*
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ50105\add* AharonВҰ50106 approached the altarВҰ50109 andВҰ50110 slaughtered the calf for his own sinВҰ50114 offeringВҰ50114,
\v 9 andВҰ50119 \add *his\add* sons presentedВҰ50119 the blood to him. DippingВҰ50121 his fingerВҰ50127 into the blood, he \add вүҲsmeared\add* it on the altar's \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add*, thenВҰ50119 he pouredВҰ50137 \add the rest of\add* the blood out at the altar's base.
\v 10 He burnt up the fat and the kidneysВҰ50148, and the lobe from the liverВҰ50154 for the sinВҰ50157 offeringВҰ50157 on the altarВҰ50159, just as YahwehВҰ50162 had instructedВҰ50161 MoshehВҰ50165,
\v 11 \add вүҲbutВҰ50167\add* the meatВҰ50169 andВҰ50167 the skinВҰ50172, he burntВҰ50173 up in a fireВҰ50174 outsideВҰ50175 the campВҰ50176.
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ50184 \add ?@Aharon\add* slaughtered the burntВҰ50181 offeringВҰ50181, and \add *his\add* sonsВҰ50183 broughtВҰ50182 the bloodВҰ50188 to him and he splashed it on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ50192.
\v 13 ThenВҰ50195 they broughtВҰ50198 him the headВҰ50203 and the \add cut-up\add* piecesВҰ50200, and he burntВҰ50197 them up on the altarВҰ50207.
\v 14 He washedВҰ50209 the innards and the legs, and thenВҰ50209 \add also\add* burntВҰ50219 them up on the altarВҰ50220.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ50222 \add @Aharon\add* presentedВҰ50222 the people's offering. He took the goatВҰ50229 for the people's offering andВҰ50222 slaughtered it, thenВҰ50222 offered it as a sin offering like \add вүҲthe other one\add*.
\v 16 He presentedВҰ50237 the burntВҰ50240 offeringВҰ50240вҖ”following all the \add вүҲinstructions\add* when he did it.
\v 17 ThenВҰ50244 he presentedВҰ50244 the grainВҰ50247 offering, andВҰ50244 \add вүҲtaking a large handful\add*, he burnt it on the altarВҰ50254, in additionВҰ50244 to the morning'sВҰ50257 burnt offering.
\v 18 ThenВҰ50259 \add AharonВҰ50272\add* slaughtered the bullВҰ50262 and the ram \add whichВҰ50268\add* were the people'sВҰ50269 peaceВҰ50267 offeringВҰ50267, and \add *his\add* sonsВҰ50271 broughtВҰ50270 the bloodВҰ50275 to him and he splashed it on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ50280.\x + \xo 9:18: \xt Lev 3:1-11.\x*
\v 19 He took the fat from the bullВҰ50288 and the ram, includingВҰ50289 their fatty tails and \add @the fat\add* coveringВҰ50293 the innards, the kidneysВҰ50294, and the lobe of the liverВҰ50296,
\v 20 andВҰ50305 placedВҰ50298 it \add all\add* on top of \add &those animals\add* breastВҰ50304 \add meat\add*, thenВҰ50298 burnt up \add @the fat\add* on the altarВҰ50307.
\v 21 \add вүҲFinallyВҰ50315,\add* he raised the breastВҰ50310 \add meat\add* andВҰ50309 the rightВҰ50313 thighВҰ50312 as a wave offering \add in frontВҰ50317\add* of YahwehВҰ50318, just as MoshehВҰ50321 had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ50320\add*.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ50323 AharonВҰ50324 raised his \add вүҲarms\add* towards the peopleВҰ50331 and blessedВҰ50332 them, and thenВҰ50323 he \add вүҲstepped\add* down, \add having finished\add* making the sin offering, the burntВҰ50336 offering, and the peaceВҰ50337 offeringsВҰ50337.\x + \xo 9:22: \xt Num 6:22-26.\x*
\v 23 MoshehВҰ50340 and AharonВҰ50341 entered the \add вүҲsacredВҰ50344\add* tent, and \add when\add* they came \add back\add* out, they blessedВҰ50347 the people and Yahweh'sВҰ50354 \add вүҲbrilliance\add* appearedВҰ50351 to all the people.
\v 24 ThenВҰ50361 flamesВҰ50362 \add вүҲshot out\add* from Yahweh'sВҰ50364 front and \add вүҲevaporated\add* the burntВҰ50371 offeringВҰ50371 and the fat on the altarВҰ50368. They peopleВҰ50378 sawВҰ50375 that \add happen\add*, and they yelled out and fell down \add onto their knees\add* \add вүҲwith their facesВҰ50383 to the ground\add*.
\c 10
\s1 Nadav and Avihu get destroyed
\rem /s1 The Death of Nadab and Abihu; Nadab and Abihu; The Sin of Nadab and Abihu
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ50385 two of Aharon's sons, Nadav and Avihu each took their \add вүҲincense-burning pans\add* and put fire in them, and put incense on \add @the fire\add*, \add вүҲthus offering unauthorised\add* fire to YahwehВҰ50401 thatВҰ50404 he hadn't instructedВҰ50406 them to do.
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ50409\add* flamesВҰ50410 \add вүҲshot out\add* from Yahweh'sВҰ50412 front andВҰ50409 consumed thenВҰ50409 \add вүҲso\add* theyВҰ50415 diedВҰ50415 \add there\add* \add вүҲin front\add* of Yahweh.
\v 3 ThenВҰ50419 MoshehВҰ50420 told Aharon, вҖңThat's what YahwehВҰ50428 \add вүҲmeant when he saidВҰ50419\add*, вҖҳI will \add вүҲreveal\add* my holiness to thoseВҰ50431 who approach me, thenВҰ50419 I'llВҰ50432 be honoured \add вүҲin the sight of\add* all the peopleВҰ50438.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ50443 MoshehВҰ50444 \add вүҲsummoned\add* MishaelВҰ50447 and Elitsafan, the sons of Aharon's Uncle Uzziyel, and told them, вҖң\add вүҲCome and help by carryingВҰ50457\add* your cousins' \add bodies\add* from the sacredВҰ50464 place \add here\add* to a place outsideВҰ50467 the campВҰ50468.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ50470\add* they \add вүҲcame\add* andВҰ50470 carriedВҰ50471 the two corpses by theirВҰ50472 clothes to a place outsideВҰ50475 the campВҰ50476 just as MoshehВҰ50479 had told them to do.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ50481 MoshehВҰ50482 told Aharon and his sonsВҰ50489 EleazarВҰ50486 and ItamarВҰ50487, вҖңDon'tВҰ50491 \add вүҲleave your hair\add* loose, and don'tВҰ50491 tear your clothesВҰ50495, so that you won't dieВҰ50500 and \add вүЎso that\add* \add @Yahweh\add* won't be angry at the entireВҰ50502 community. ButВҰ50481 \add вүҲmeanwhile\add*, all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ50509\add* mustВҰ50500 \add вүҲmournВҰ50511\add* because Yahweh \add вүҲwas angry enough to burn\add* \add those two\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ50519,\add* don'tВҰ50522 leave the entranceВҰ50519 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ50520\add* tentВҰ50520, as you might dieВҰ50526 becauseВҰ50527 you all \add still\add* have Yahweh'sВҰ50531 anointingВҰ50530 oilВҰ50529 on you.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ50519\add* theyВҰ50533 didВҰ50533 \add вүҲeverything that MoshehВҰ50535 said\add*.
\s1 Instructions for priests
\rem /s1 Instructions for Priestly Conduct; Rules for Priests
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ50539 told Aharon,
\v 9 вҖң\add Neither\add* you or your sonsВҰ50553 should drink wine or strongВҰ50546 drink when you're \add going to\add* go into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ50558\add* tentВҰ50558 so that you won'tВҰ50547 dieВҰ50561. This regulationВҰ50562 is permanentВҰ50563 \add вүҲand for future\add* generationsВҰ50564.
\v 10 You must \add carefully\add* \add вүҲdistinguish\add* between what's sacredВҰ50568 and what's common, and what's вҖҳuncleanВҰ50572вҖҷ and вҖҳcleanВҰ50574вҖҷ.
\v 11 andВҰ50576 you must teachВҰ50576 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ50579\add* all the instructionsВҰ50584 thatВҰ50585 YahwehВҰ50587 has \add вүҲgiven\add* them \add вүҲvia\add* MoshehВҰ50591.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 Then MoshehВҰ50595 told Aharon and his \add вүҲremainingВҰ50606\add* sonsВҰ50605 EleazarВҰ50600 and ItamarВҰ50603, вҖңTake the remainder of the grainВҰ50610 offeringВҰ50610 after \add the memorial portion has been given\add* to YahwehВҰ50613, and eatВҰ50614 thatВҰ50611 \add вүҲflat breadВҰ50615\add* \add there\add* besideВҰ50616 the altarВҰ50617, becauseВҰ50618 it's \add вүҲvery sacredВҰ50619\add*.\x + \xo 10:12-13: \xt Lev 6:14-18.\x*
\v 13 You all mustВҰ50623 eatВҰ50623 it in a sacredВҰ50626 placeВҰ50625, because it's the portion for you andВҰ50623 your sonsВҰ50631 from the gifts to YahwehВҰ50634, because that's what I'veВҰ50638 been instructedВҰ50638.
\v 14 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ50640\add*, you all mustВҰ50647 eat the breastВҰ50641 \add meat\add* from the wave offering and the thighВҰ50645 from the contributionВҰ50646 \add offering\add* in a вҖҳcleanвҖҷ placeВҰ50648. YourВҰ50664 sons and daughtersВҰ50652 \add вүҲcan join you all for that\add*, becauseВҰ50654 \add @that food\add* has been givenВҰ50660 as the portion for you and your childrenВҰ50659 from the peaceВҰ50662 offering sacrificesВҰ50661 from the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ50663\add*.\x + \xo 10:14-15: \xt Lev 7:30-34.\x*
\v 15 \add Yes,\add* \add &those\add* \add #thighs\add* from the contributionВҰ50667 \add offering\add* and the breastВҰ50668 \add meat\add* from the wave offering, in addition to the gifts of the fat portions, mustВҰ50673 be brought before Yahweh as a raised offering, and then they'll alwaysВҰ50684 become the portion for you and your families, just as Yahweh instructedВҰ50686.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ50689 MoshehВҰ50695 looked for the goatВҰ50691 \add meat\add* from the sinВҰ50692 offeringВҰ50692, \add вүҲbutВҰ50689 was shocked to discover\add* that it had been burntВҰ50697 up \add on the altar\add*, \add вүҲso\add* he was angryВҰ50698 with Aharon'sВҰ50706 remainingВҰ50707 sonsВҰ50705 EleazarВҰ50701 andВҰ50689 ItamarВҰ50704, telling them,
\v 17 вҖңWhy didn'tВҰ50711 you eatВҰ50713 \add &that\add* sinВҰ50716 offeringВҰ50716 in the sacred placeВҰ50717, becauseВҰ50719 it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred and he gaveВҰ50725 it to you to bear the community's \add вүҲguilt\add* then to \add вүҲmake them right with\add* YahwehВҰ50735.\x + \xo 10:17: \xt Lev 6:24-26.\x*
\v 18 Listen here! Its bloodВҰ50743 \em wasn't\em* taken into the inner sacred place, \add so\add* you mustВҰ50749 eat it in the sacred place just like I toldВҰ50753 you to do!вҖқ
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ50755 Aharon \add вүҲexplained\add* to MoshehВҰ50759, вҖңListen, they presentedВҰ50762 their sin offering and their burntВҰ50768 offering to Yahweh today, and \add вүҲyet I lost two of my sons\add*. ButВҰ50755 if I'd eaten the sin offering today, would it have \add вүҲpleased\add* Yahweh?вҖқ
\v 20 \add вүҲWhenВҰ50781\add* MoshehВҰ50782 heard \add <that\add*, \add вүҲhe was satisfied\add*.
\c 11
\s1 Creatures that may be eaten
\rem /s1 Animals That May Be Eaten; Ceremonially Clean and Unclean Animals; Clean and Unclean Foods; Clean and Unclean Food; Purification and atonement
\r (Deu. 14:3-21)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ50788 told MoshehВҰ50791 and Aharon:
\p
\v 2 TellВҰ50802 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ50801\add* that \add вүҲthe following\add* creaturesВҰ50805 on the earthВҰ50814 are the ones that you all can eatВҰ50807:
\v 3 вҮ”You all can eatВҰ50827 any animalВҰ50825 that has hoovesВҰ50822 \add вүҲwhich are completely split in twoВҰ50818\add* andВҰ50820 that \add also\add* \add вүҲchew\add* the cud.
\v 4 However you mustn't eatВҰ50834 those \add вүҲwithout \+em bothВҰ50837\+em* traits\add*, for example camelsВҰ50841 \add вүҲchew\add* the cud \add вүҲbutВҰ50837\add* don'tВҰ50833 have dividedВҰ50837 hoovesВҰ50838, \add so\add* they are вҖҳuncleanВҰ50850вҖҷ for you.
\v 5 The rockВҰ50856 badgerВҰ50856 \add вүҲlikewise\add*, becauseВҰ50857 although it \add вүҲchews\add* the cud, it \add too\add* doesn't have dividedВҰ50864 hoovesВҰ50862,
\v 6 andВҰ50869 the rabbit is вҖҳuncleanВҰ50880вҖҷ for you all becauseВҰ50872 although it \add вүҲchews\add* the cud, it doesn't have dividedВҰ50879 hoovesВҰ50877.
\v 7 \add #Pigs\add* have dividedВҰ50889 \add #hooves\add* that are split completely, \add вүҲbutВҰ50884\add* don'tВҰ50897 \add вүҲchew\add* the cud, \add so\add* they're вҖҳuncleanВҰ50900вҖҷ for you allвҖ”
\v 8 you mustn't eat their meat or touchВҰ50909 their carcassesВҰ50907 \add because\add* they're вҖҳuncleanВҰ50910вҖҷ for you all.
\p
\v 9 вҮ”You all can eat everything that \add lives\add* in the water, \add whether\add* the oceans or rivers, as long as it has \add both\add* fins and scalesВҰ50926.
\v 10 \add вүҲIn contrast,\add* anything in the oceans or rivers without \add both\add* fins andВҰ50933 scalesВҰ50939, whether they're swarmingВҰ50943 creaturesВҰ50946 or otherwise, they'll \add all\add* be detestableВҰ50950 for you all.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ50954\add* anything that's detestable to you all, you mustn't eat their meat andВҰ50954 you mustВҰ50955 detestВҰ50954 their carcassesВҰ50962.
\v 12 Anything in the waterВҰ50972 that doesn't have \add both\add* fins andВҰ50971 scalesВҰ50971 will be detestableВҰ50973 for you all.
\p
\v 13 From the birds, the ones that you'll all detestВҰ50980 and avoid eating will include: the eagleВҰ50990 and \add вүҲany kind of\add* vulture,
\v 14 the kite andВҰ51000 any kind of falcon,
\v 15 any kind of crow,
\v 16 \add вүҲany kind of\add* owl, gull, or hawk,
\v 17 the cormorantВҰ51030,
\v 18 the osprey,
\v 19 the storkВҰ51046, any kind of heronВҰ51047, the hoopoeВҰ51051, andВҰ51045 bats.
\v 20 EverythingВҰ51056 thatВҰ51059 swarmsВҰ51057 with wings and walksВҰ51059 on fourВҰ51062 \add legs\add* must be detestableВҰ51063 for you all.
\v 21 However, you all can eatВҰ51072 anything that swarmsВҰ51074 with wings and walksВҰ51076 on fourВҰ51079 \add legs\add* that has its legs aboveВҰ51085 its feetВҰ51086 for hopping on the ground.
\v 22 You all can eat any kind of locust or cricket or grasshopperВҰ51112,
\v 23 \add вүҲbutВҰ51115\add* anything thatВҰ51118 swarmsВҰ51116 with wings andВҰ51115 walks on fourВҰ51121 \add legs\add* must be detestableВҰ51123 for you all.
\rem /s1 Unclean Animals
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲThe following\add* will make youВҰ51128 вҖҳuncleanвҖҷвҖ”anyoneВҰ51131 who touchesВҰ51131 theirВҰ51132 carcassesВҰ51132 will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ51134 the eveningВҰ51136,
\v 25 plusВҰ51144 anyoneВҰ51140 who carriesВҰ51140 their carcassВҰ51141 mustВҰ51142 wash their clothesВҰ51143 andВҰ51138 will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ51144вҖҷ untilВҰ51145 the eveningВҰ51147:
\v 26 Any animal with a dividedВҰ51154 hoofВҰ51155 butВҰ51156 not \add вүҲcompletely split in twoВҰ51154\add* or thatВҰ51152 doesn't \add вүҲchew\add* the cud will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for you allвҖ”anyoneВҰ51168 who touchesВҰ51168 them will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 27 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ51172,\add* any four-footed animal thatВҰ51174 walks on its paws is вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for youвҖ”anyoneВҰ51174 who touchesВҰ51190 theirВҰ51191 carcassВҰ51191 will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ51193 the eveningВҰ51195,
\v 28 plusВҰ51203 anyoneВҰ51197 who carriesВҰ51197 their carcassВҰ51200 mustВҰ51201 wash their clothesВҰ51202 andВҰ51197 will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ51204 the eveningВҰ51206 \add because\add* they're вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for you all.
\p
\v 29 These are the вҖҳuncleanВҰ51214вҖҷ creatures from the ones thatВҰ51216 swarmВҰ51216 on the ground: \add #rats, mice, lizardsВҰ51222\add*
\v 30 of any kind, \add #geckos, skinksВҰ51228, andВҰ51225 chameleonsВҰ51229\add*.
\v 31 Out of all the swarmingВҰ51236 thingsВҰ51236, those are вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for youвҖ”anyoneВҰ51239 who touchesВҰ51239 them when they've died will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ51243 the eveningВҰ51245.
\v 32 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ51247,\add* anything thatВҰ51272 \add вүҲtheirВҰ51255 dead bodies\add* fall on will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ, whether it's a wooden. cloth, leader, or sackclothВҰ51268 object, or any container used for workВҰ51275, \add so thenВҰ51247\add* it mustВҰ51250 be immersed in waterВҰ51277 andВҰ51247 it will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ51280 the eveningВҰ51282 when it will become вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add again\add*.
\v 33 \add If\add* one of \add @those creatures\add* falls into a clay container, everything in it will become вҖҳuncleanВҰ51300вҖҷ andВҰ51285 you mustВҰ51292 breakВҰ51302 \add @that container\add*.
\v 34 If waterВҰ51312 from \add that container\add* got onto any food, it will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ, and any drinkВҰ51316 \add вүҲtake\add* from that container will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 35 Anything that the dead body of one of \add @those creatures\add* falls onto will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷвҖ”any oven or stoveВҰ51333 mustВҰ51327 be smashed. They have become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ \add вүҲandВҰ51324 would always remain so\add*.
\v 36 However a springВҰ51342 or a cisternВҰ51343 for collectingВҰ51344 waterВҰ51346 will be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, \add вүҲbutВҰ51343\add* anyoneВҰ51349 touchingВҰ51349 that dead body will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ51351вҖҷ.
\v 37 If the dead body fell on some seeds that will be planted, \add @that seed\add* is still вҖҳcleanвҖҷ,
\v 38 \add вүҲbutВҰ51367\add* if the seeds \add вүҲare wet\add* when the dead body falls on it, thenВҰ51367 it's вҖҳuncleanВҰ51377вҖҷ for you.
\p
\v 39 If any animal thatВҰ51387 you all can eat dies, then any person touchesВҰ51392 itsВҰ51393 carcassВҰ51393 will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ51394вҖҷ untilВҰ51395 the eveningВҰ51397.
\v 40 AnyoneВҰ51399 who eatsВҰ51399 any \add part\add* of that dead body, and anyoneВҰ51399 who \add вүҲmoves\add* it, mustВҰ51401 wash their clothesВҰ51402 and will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ until the evening.
\p
\v 41 Every creature thatВҰ51421 swarmsВҰ51420 along the ground is detestableВҰ51425вҖ”it mustn't be eatenВҰ51428.
\v 42 Everything that \add moves\add* on its belly, and any swarming thing that moves along the ground on fourВҰ51441 or more feet mustn't be eaten because they're detestable.
\v 43 Don'tВҰ51461 make yourselves detestableВҰ51463 with any of those swarmingВҰ51469 creatures, and don'tВҰ51461 make yourselves вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ by \add touching or eating\add* them,
\v 44 because I am your godВҰ51480 YahwehВҰ51479. You all mustВҰ51481 keepВҰ51481 yourselves holy, and you're a holy people because I'm holy. \add вүҲSo\add* don'tВҰ51487 make yourselves вҖҳuncleanВҰ51488вҖҷ with any swarmingВҰ51494 creatures that creepВҰ51495 across the ground\x + \xo 11:44: \xt Lev 19:2; 1Pe 1:16.\x*
\v 45 because I am YahwehВҰ51503, the one who broughtВҰ51504 you all out of EgyptВҰ51507 to be your godВҰ51510, and you mustВҰ51511 be holy because I am holy.
\p
\v 46 The \add above\add* are the regulations about livestock, birds, creatures that move in the waterВҰ51525, and creatures that swarmВҰ51529 across the ground,
\v 47 to \add вүҲdistinguish\add* between the вҖҳuncleanВҰ51536вҖҷ and the вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, i.e., those that can be eaten and those that mustВҰ51546 not be eaten.
\c 12
\s1 Purification after giving birth
\rem /s1 The Purification of Women after Childbirth; Purification after Childbirth; Purification of Women after Childbirth; Purification After Childbirth
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ51550 told MoshehВҰ51553:
\p
\v 2 TellВҰ51560 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ51559\add* that when a womanВҰ51562 gets pregnant and then gives birth to a boy, she will then be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for sevenВҰ51568 days similar to how her impurityВҰ51571 during her \add вүҲmonthly period\add* makes her вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 3 ThenВҰ51575 on the eighthВҰ51576 dayВҰ51575, \add @the baby boy's\add* foreskinВҰ51579 mustВҰ51577 be circumcisedВҰ51577.\x + \xo 12:3: \xt Gen 17:12; Luk 2:21.\x*
\v 4 \add @The mother\add* will remainВҰ51585 impure from the bloodВҰ51586 for thirty-three daysвҖ”she mustВҰ51585 not touchВҰ51593 any sacredВҰ51590 thingВҰ51590 andВҰ51581 may not enter the sanctuaryВҰ51596 untilВҰ51599 herВҰ51602 purification timeВҰ51584 is completedВҰ51601.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if she gave birth to a \add вүҲgirl\add*, she'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ51609вҖҷ for twoВҰ51610 weeksВҰ51610 similar to how her impurityВҰ51611 during her \add вүҲmonthly period\add*, andВҰ51605 her purificationВҰ51620 timeВҰ51615 will be sixty-six daysВҰ51615.
\p
\v 6 WhenВҰ51622 \add @the mother's\add* purificationВҰ51625 timeВҰ51624 is completedВҰ51622 for either a son or a daughterВҰ51628, she mustВҰ51629 take a one-year-old lamb as a burntВҰ51634 offering andВҰ51622 a \add вүҲyoungВҰ51635\add* pigeon or dove as a sin offering to the priestВҰ51650 at the entranceВҰ51644 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ51645\add* tent.
\v 7 ThenВҰ51652 he mustВҰ51652 presentВҰ51652 them to YahwehВҰ51654 to \add вүҲmake her right with God\add*, andВҰ51652 thenВҰ51652 she'll be purified from her flow of bloodВҰ51659. That's the regulation for a woman who givesВҰ51662 birthВҰ51662 to either a male or a femaleВҰ51665.
\p
\v 8 If \add вүҲshe's unable to afford\add* a lamb, then she mustВҰ51670 take \em two\em* youngВҰ51680 pigeons or dovesвҖ”one for the burntВҰ51683 offering and one for the sin offering. ThenВҰ51667 the priestВҰ51688 will \add вүҲmake herВҰ51671 right with God\add*, and then she'll will have been purified.\x + \xo 12:8: \xt Luk 2:24.\x*
\c 13
\s1 Regulations about skin diseases
\rem /s1 Laws concerning Skin Diseases; Contagious Skin Diseases; Leprosy, Varieties and Symptoms; Regulations About Infectious Skin Diseases
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ51693 told MoshehВҰ51696 and Aharon:
\p
\v 2 If \add someone discovers\add* a raised area on their skin, or a scab or a brightВҰ51714 spot, and it seems like an infectious skin diseaseВҰ51720, then \add @that person\add* should be taken to a priestВҰ51725 (Aharon or one of his sonsВҰ51730),
\v 3 and the priest must \add вүҲexamine\add* their skin. If the hairВҰ51741 in the infected \add spot\add* has turnedВҰ51743 whiteВҰ51745 and the infection appearsВҰ51746 to be deeper under the skin, thenВҰ51733 it's \add confirmed as\add* an infectious skin diseaseВҰ51752 and \add вүҲso\add* the priest must pronounce the person as вҖҳuncleanВҰ51756вҖҷ.
\v 4 \add However,\add* if it's a white spot \add вүҲthat doesn't seem\add* to be deep, andВҰ51759 the hairВҰ51773 hasn't turnedВҰ51776 white, thenВҰ51759 the priestВҰ51779 \add mustВҰ51778 order\add* the person to be quarantined for sevenВҰ51783 daysВҰ51784.
\v 5 ThenВҰ51786 on the seventh dayВҰ51788, if the infection is still there butВҰ51786 hasn't spreadВҰ51796, thenВҰ51786 the priestВҰ51787 \add mustВҰ51786 order\add* a further sevenВҰ51801 daysВҰ51802 of quarantine.
\v 6 After that next sevenВҰ51809 days, if the infection has faded and not spreadВҰ51816, the priestВҰ51806 must pronounce the person as вҖҳcleanвҖҷвҖ”it was just a \add вүҲsore\add* so the person must wash their clothesВҰ51824 and thenВҰ51805 they'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the spot does spread across the skin \em afterВҰ51833\em* the priest has pronounced \add @the person\add* to be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, thenВҰ51827 they mustВҰ51830 \add вүҲreturn\add* to the priest a secondВҰ51840 time.
\v 8 The priest must re-examine \add @that person\add* andВҰ51845 if the spot on the skin has spreadВҰ51848, thenВҰ51845 the priest must pronounce them вҖҳuncleanВҰ51851вҖҷ because they have a skin diseaseВҰ51853.
\p
\v 9 Anyone who develops an infectious skin diseaseВҰ51858 mustВҰ51860 be taken to a priestВҰ51865
\v 10 \add вүҲto be examined\add*. If it's a white spot on the skin and the hairВҰ51876 has turnedВҰ51875 white, and there's raw fleshВҰ51879 \add visible\add* in the swelling,
\v 11 then it's a chronic skin diseaseВҰ51883, and the priestВҰ51889 mustВҰ51888 pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ and can'tВҰ51890 just be \add temporarily\add* \add вүҲquarantined\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the disease has broken out andВҰ51896 spread across the entireВҰ51905 \add вүҲbody\add* from headВҰ51909 to toe as far as can be observed by the priestВҰ51917,
\v 13 thenВҰ51919 \add after\add* the priest'sВҰ51920 confirmation that it coversВҰ51922 the entireВҰ51926 \add вүҲbodyВҰ51928\add*, \add @that person\add* can be pronounced as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add again\add* as all of it has turnedВҰ51934 whiteВҰ51935.
\v 14 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if any raw fleshВҰ51942 \add вүҲshows itself\add*, thenВҰ51939 they'll become вҖҳuncleanВҰ51944вҖҷ \add вүҲthat same\add* dayВҰ51939.
\v 15 The priestВҰ51947 must \add вүҲexamine\add* that raw flesh andВҰ51952 must pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ due to \add &their\add* skin diseaseВҰ51957.
\v 16 \add вүҲAfterwards, if it heals over\add* and goes whiteВҰ51966, then they can returnВҰ51962 to the priestВҰ51970
\v 17 \add вүҲto be reexamined\add*, and if the infection has indeed gone whiteВҰ51977, thenВҰ51972 the priestВҰ51973 can pronounce it as \add вүҲnot being infectious\add* and \add @the person\add* as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add again\add*.
\p
\v 18 When \add вүҲsomeone\add* has a boil on their skin, \add вүҲbutВҰ51987\add* it heals
\v 19 \add вүҲleaving behind\add* a white swellingВҰ52000 or a reddish-white brightВҰ52003 spot, thenВҰ51997 \add @that person\add* mustВҰ52006 show themself to the priestВҰ52009.
\v 20 The priest will \add вүҲexamine\add* it, and if it is indeed more than \add just\add* skin deep and its hairВҰ52019 has turnedВҰ52020 whiteВҰ52021, thenВҰ52011 the priest mustВҰ52011 pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanВҰ52022вҖҷ because an infectious skin diseaseВҰ52026 has brokenВҰ52029 out from the \add original\add* boil.
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the priest's examination finds not whiteВҰ52040 hairВҰ52039 on it, and it's not more than skin deep, and it's fading, thenВҰ52031 he will \add order\add* \add @that person\add* quarantined for sevenВҰ52050 daysВҰ52051,
\v 22 andВҰ52053 if it spreads further on \add &their\add* skin, thenВҰ52053 the priestВҰ52059 mustВҰ52056 declareВҰ52058 \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanВҰ52058вҖҷ because it's \add вүҲinfectious\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ52064\add* if the brightВҰ52068 spot \add вүҲhasn't spreadВҰ52070\add* \add during the quarantine\add*, thenВҰ52064 it's \add just\add* the scar from the boil andВҰ52074 the priestВҰ52075 can pronounce \add @the person\add* as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 24 If someone gets a burn on their skin, and the burn area becomes reddish-white or a white spot,
\v 25 then the priest must examine it, and if the hairВҰ52101 on the spot has turnedВҰ52100 whiteВҰ52102 and \add @the infection\add* looks more than skin deep, then a skin disease has brokenВҰ52112 out in the burnВҰ52111, and the priest must pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanВҰ52113вҖҷ because it's \add вүҲinfectious\add*.
\v 26 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the priestВҰ52123 sees that there'sВҰ52125 no whiteВҰ52129 hairВҰ52128 in the spot, and it's not more than skin deep, and it's fading, thenВҰ52120 \add *he\add* will \add order\add* \add @that person\add* quarantined for sevenВҰ52139 daysВҰ52140.
\v 27 On the seventhВҰ52145 dayВҰ52144, the priestВҰ52143 will re-examine \add @the person\add*, andВҰ52151 if it's spread further, \add *he\add* mustВҰ52142 pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanВҰ52151вҖҷ because it's an infectious skin diseaseВҰ52155.
\v 28 \add вүҲButВҰ52158\add* if the brightВҰ52162 spot hasn't spreadВҰ52165 on the skin, andВҰ52158 it faded \add more\add*, thenВҰ52158 it was \add just\add* swellingВҰ52169 from the burn. ThenВҰ52158 the priestВҰ52173 will pronounce \add @that person\add* to be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ becauseВҰ52174 it was \add just\add* the scar \add вүҲcaused by\add* \add &their\add* burn.
\p
\v 29 If a man or womanВҰ52183 has an infection in \add &their\add* \add вүҲscalp\add* or \add вүҲunder\add* \add &their\add* beardВҰ52191,
\v 30 then the priest should inspect the infection. If it appearsВҰ52199 to be more than skin deep, and there's any thin yellowВҰ52206 hairs in it, then the priest mustВҰ52193 pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳuncleanВҰ52208вҖҷ \add because\add* it's a \add вүҲitchy and infectious\add* skin infection on the \add вүҲscalp or face\add*.
\v 31 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the priestВҰ52222 notices an itchy infection yet it's only skin deep andВҰ52219 there'sВҰ52237 no blackВҰ52236 hairВҰ52235 on it, thenВҰ52219 he should quarantine that person for sevenВҰ52245 daysВҰ52246.
\v 32 On the seventhВҰ52254 dayВҰ52253, the priestВҰ52249 will re-examine \add вүҲthat person\add* and if the spot hasn't widened and \add still\add* only appearsВҰ52266 to be skin deep,
\v 33 then \add @that person\add* should shave \add their head\add*, andВҰ52274 then the priestВҰ52281 should quarantine them for a further sevenВҰ52285 daysВҰ52286.
\v 34 ThenВҰ52289 \add again\add* on the seventhВҰ52295 dayВҰ52294, the priest will inspect it, and if the spot hasn't widened after being shaved and it doesn't seem to be more than skin deep, thenВҰ52289 the priest can pronounce \add @that person\add* as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add вүҲonce\add* they've washed their clothesВҰ52312.
\v 35 \add вүҲHowever,\add* itВҰ52318 is did spread on their skin afterВҰ52321 \add *that\add*,
\v 36 then the priestВҰ52325 mustВҰ52324 inspect it again, andВҰ52324 if it's spreadВҰ52327 then \add @that person\add* is вҖҳuncleanВҰ52336вҖҷ (whether or not there's any yellowВҰ52335 hairВҰ52334).
\v 37 \add вүҲButВҰ52339\add* if it seems that the spot \add вүҲhasn't spread\add* and dark hairВҰ52344 is growing in it again, thenВҰ52339 \add @that person's\add* \add вүҲnot infectious\add* and the priestВҰ52354 can pronounce them as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 38 If a man or womanВҰ52360 \add вүҲfinds very\add* whiteВҰ52369 spots on theirВҰ52366 skin,
\v 39 then the priestВҰ52372 mustВҰ52371 examine \add <them\add*. If the spotsВҰ52377 on theirВҰ52376 skin are dull whiteВҰ52379, then it's a skin rash that's brokenВҰ52382 out andВҰ52373 they are вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 40 If a man's headВҰ52391 has becomeВҰ52390 bare, then he's \add gone\add* bald andВҰ52388 is \add still\add* вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 41 \add вүҲSimilarly, \add* if the hair \add вүҲis receding\add* from the front corners, he's \add вүҲgoing bald\add* andВҰ52397 is \add still\add* вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 42 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if there's a balding spot with a reddish-white infection, it's a skin diseaseВҰ52416 breakingВҰ52417 out via thatВҰ52417 spot
\v 43 andВҰ52426 the priestВҰ52425 mustВҰ52423 examine him. If it's a balding spot with a reddish-white infection that looks like a \add contagious\add* skin diseaseВҰ52436,
\v 44 then he's \add вүҲcontagious\add* and вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ. The priestВҰ52448 mustВҰ52447 pronounce his as вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ because of that infection on his headВҰ52449.
\p
\v 45 AnyoneВҰ52452 who's developed an infectious skin diseaseВҰ52452 must tear their clothesВҰ52457 and \add вүҲleave their hair loose\add*, and must \add вүҲcoverВҰ52466 their mouth\add* and call out, вҖҳUnclean, unclean.вҖҷ
\v 46 They will remain вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ as long as they \add still\add* have thatВҰ52475 infection, and mustВҰ52478 live aloneВҰ52481 outsideВҰ52483 the campВҰ52484.
\s1 Regulations about moulds and fungi
\rem /s1 Laws concerning Mildew; Regulations About Mildew; Treatment of Contaminated Clothing
\p
\v 47 When a \add piece of\add* clothing has a mould growing on it, whether it's made of wool or linenВҰ52499,
\v 48 or whether it's something woven from wool or linenВҰ52505, or something made from leather,
\v 49 if the growth is greenishВҰ52517 or reddishВҰ52520 in colour, thenВҰ52515 it's something that can spread andВҰ52515 it mustВҰ52539 be shownВҰ52539 to the priestВҰ52542.
\v 50 The priestВҰ52545 mustВҰ52544 examine the growth, andВҰ52549 quarantine the \add вүҲarticle\add* for sevenВҰ52553 daysВҰ52554.
\v 51 On the seventhВҰ52561 dayВҰ52560, if the growth has spread on that piece of material or leather equipment, and it's confirmed as spreadable and is вҖҳuncleanВҰ52584вҖҷ.
\v 52 \add ?@The owner\add* must burnВҰ52587 the piece of clothing or equipment thatВҰ52610 contains the infection becauseВҰ52615 it's contagious, so it must be completely burntВҰ52621 up.
\p
\v 53 \add вүҲHowever\add* if the priestВҰ52625 notices that the growth hasn't spreadВҰ52629 on the clothing or on the woven or leather \add вүҲmaterial\add*,
\v 54 then the priestВҰ52644 mustВҰ52643 order thatВҰ52647 the \add вүҲmaterial\add* be washed andВҰ52643 then quarantined for a \add вүҲfurther\add* sevenВҰ52652 daysВҰ52654.
\v 55 \add On the seventh day,\add* the priestВҰ52658 must inspect that washedВҰ52661 \add вүҲmaterial\add*, and if the growth hasn't \add вүҲchanged its appearance\add*, even if it hasn't spreadВҰ52676, thenВҰ52657 it's вҖҳuncleanВҰ52677вҖҷ and must be burnt in the fireВҰ52679вҖ”it's a mildewВҰ52681 that's on the frontВҰ52685 or back of the material.
\v 56 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the priestВҰ52689 notices that the growth has faded afterВҰ52693 being washedВҰ52694, thenВҰ52687 it can be torn out of the clothingВҰ52700 or piece of leather or woven material.
\v 57 If it \add then\add* reappears on that clothing or material, then it's breakingВҰ52731 out, so then that articleВҰ52728 mustВҰ52716 be burnt in the fireВҰ52733.
\v 58 \add вүҲOn the other hand,\add* if the growth \add вүҲvanished after being\add* washed, then it mustВҰ52755 be washed a secondВҰ52760 time andВҰ52741 then it will be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 59 \add @The above\add* are the regulations concerning any growth on a piece of woollen or linenВҰ52772 clothingВҰ52768 or fabric, or any leather articleВҰ52780, to pronounce it вҖҳcleanвҖҷ or вҖҳuncleanВҰ52785вҖҷ.
\c 14
\s1 Purification after a skin disease
\rem /s1 Purification after Having Skin Diseases; Cleansing from Skin Diseases; Purification of Lepers and Leprous Houses; Cleansing From Infectious Skin Diseases
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ52789 told MoshehВҰ52792:
\p
\v 2 These are the regulations for the purificationВҰ52800 of a person who had a skin diseaseВҰ52798. They mustВҰ52796 be taken to a priestВҰ52804\x + \xo 14:2: \xt Mat 8:4; Mrk 1:44; Luk 5:14; 17:14.\x*
\v 3 \add *who'll\add* goВҰ52806 outsideВҰ52810 the campВҰ52811 \add to meet them\add*. The priestВҰ52807 mustВҰ52806 inspect \add that person\add*, andВҰ52806 if the skin disease has indeed left them,
\v 4 thenВҰ52823 the priestВҰ52824 will order them to bring \add <him\add* twoВҰ52827 live, вҖҳcleanвҖҷ birdsВҰ52829, some cedarВҰ52833 \add wood\add*, some scarletВҰ52834 \add thread\add*, andВҰ52823 some hyssopВҰ52836 \add twigs\add*.
\v 5 The priestВҰ52839 mustВҰ52838 tell \add @the person\add* to slaughter one bird \add ?вүҲso the blood runs into\add* a clay jug \add ?вүҲcontaining\add* waterВҰ52852 \add вүҲfrom a spring or creek\add*.
\v 6 Then \add @the priest\add* will takeВҰ52859 the live bird, along with the cedarВҰ52864 wood, the scarletВҰ52867 \add thread\add*, and the hyssopВҰ52871 \add twigs\add*, and dip them \add вүҲall\add* into thatВҰ52880 bloodВҰ52878 of the slaughtered bird (\add ?вүҲmixed with\add* the \add вүҲfresh\add* waterВҰ52882),
\v 7 and \add вүҲflick\add* it sevenВҰ52891 timesВҰ52892 onto the person who's being purifiedВҰ52887 from the skin diseaseВҰ52890. ThenВҰ52885 \add @the priest\add* can pronounce them as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add enough to re-enter the community\add*, and \add вүҲrelease\add* the live bird \add to fly\add* into the countrysideВҰ52902.
\v 8 The person who's being purifiedВҰ52905 must then wash their clothesВҰ52908, shaveВҰ52909 all their hairВҰ52914, andВҰ52904 then bathe in \add flowing\add* waterВҰ52916. After that, they can re-enter the campВҰ52922 \add вүҲbutВҰ52904\add* must live outsideВҰ52924 their tentВҰ52925 for sevenВҰ52926 \add more\add* daysВҰ52927.
\v 9 On the seventhВҰ52931 dayВҰ52930, \add @that person\add* mustВҰ52932 shave off all their hair (includingВҰ52941 eyebrowsВҰ52945 and beardВҰ52943 \add if appropriate\add*), wash their clothesВҰ52956 and bathe themself in \add flowing\add* waterВҰ52961, thenВҰ52929 they'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ52964 on the eighthВҰ52965 dayВҰ52964, \add @that person\add* mustВҰ52966 \add вүҲget\add* two one-year-old \add male\add* lambsВҰ52969, andВҰ52964 one female lamb, \add all\add* \add вүҲwith no defects\add*, along with threeВҰ52977 kilograms of fine flourВҰ52979 mixedВҰ52981 with oil as a grainВҰ52980 offeringВҰ52980, as well as \add вүҲhalf a litre\add* of \add olive\add* oil.
\v 11 \add That mustВҰ52987 be taken to\add* the priestВҰ52988 who'd pronounced them as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add вүҲwill accompany them\add* andВҰ52993 all those offerings to stand \add вүҲin frontВҰ52994\add* of YahwehВҰ52995 at the entranceВҰ52996 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ52997\add* tentВҰ52997.
\v 12 ThenВҰ53000 the priestВҰ53001 mustВҰ53000 take one of the male lambs and the \add вүҲcontainer\add* of oil and presentВҰ53006 it as a guiltВҰ53008 offering, thenВҰ53000 he'll raise them as a wave offering \add вүҲin frontВҰ53016\add* of YahwehВҰ53017.
\v 13 ThenВҰ53019 \add @that person\add* mustВҰ53019 slaughter that lambВҰ53022 in the sacred place whereВҰ53024 sin offerings andВҰ53019 burntВҰ53031 offerings are slaughtered, becauseВҰ53034 this guiltВҰ53036 offering is like a sin offering in that it's for the priestВҰ53038вҖ”it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred.
\v 14 ThenВҰ53043 the priestВҰ53044 mustВҰ53043 takeВҰ53043 some of the bloodВҰ53045 from that guiltВҰ53046 offeringВҰ53046, and put it on the lobe of the right earВҰ53052 of the person being purifiedВҰ53053, and on their right thumbВҰ53057 and right bigВҰ53062 toeВҰ53062.
\v 15 ThenВҰ53066 the priestВҰ53067 mustВҰ53066 takeВҰ53066 \add вүҲthe container\add* of olive oilВҰ53069 andВҰ53070 pour some into his left hand.
\v 16 ThenВҰ53077 he'll dip his rightВҰ53082 finger into that oil on his left palm, andВҰ53077 with that \add same\add* finger, \add вүҲflick\add* it sevenВҰ53096 timesВҰ53097 \add вүҲtowards\add* YahwehВҰ53099.
\v 17 ThenВҰ53101 the priestВҰ53108 mustВҰ53107 put some of the remainingВҰ53101 oilВҰ53102 on his palmВҰ53106 onto the lobe of the right earВҰ53112 of the person being purifiedВҰ53113, and on their right thumbВҰ53117 and right bigВҰ53122 toeВҰ53122вҖ”on top of the bloodВҰ53126 from the guiltВҰ53127 offeringВҰ53127.
\v 18 ThenВҰ53129 the priest will put \add all\add* the remainingВҰ53129 oilВҰ53130 from his palmВҰ53134 onto the headВҰ53139 of the person being purifiedВҰ53140, andВҰ53141 the priest \add вүҲwill thenВҰ53129 make thatВҰ53131 person right with\add* YahwehВҰ53145.
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ53147 the priestВҰ53148 mustВҰ53147 make the sin offering andВҰ53147 \add вүҲmake that person right\add* afterВҰ53157 being purifiedВҰ53155 from their вҖҳuncleannessВҰ53156вҖҷ. After that \add ?@that person\add* will slaughter \add lamb for\add* the burntВҰ53161 offering.
\v 20 ThenВҰ53163 the priestВҰ53164 mustВҰ53163 offer \add &that\add* burntВҰ53167 offering and the grainВҰ53170 offering \add вүҲon the fire\add* on the altarВҰ53171 and he will make \add вүҲthat person right again\add* and he will be вҖҳcleanВҰ53175вҖҷ.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add @that person\add* is poor and \add вүҲcannot afford\add* \add the multiple lambs\add*, then they mustВҰ53185 take \em one\em* lambВҰ53186 to wave as the guiltВҰ53188 offering and to make \add вүҲthem right again\add*, along with \em one\em* kilogram of fine flourВҰ53193 mixedВҰ53195 with oil for the grainВҰ53197 offering, and the half litre of oil,
\v 22 plusВҰ53210 two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ53205\add* pigeonsвҖ”whicheverВҰ53207 they can affordвҖ”one for a sin offering andВҰ53201 the other for the burntВҰ53214 offering.
\v 23 ThenВҰ53216 on \add &that\add* eighthВҰ53219 dayВҰ53218, he'll take them to the priestВҰ53223 at the entranceВҰ53226 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ53227\add* tentВҰ53227 for purificationВҰ53220 \add вүҲin frontВҰ53230\add* of YahwehВҰ53231.
\v 24 ThenВҰ53233 the priestВҰ53234 should take the guiltВҰ53238 offering lambВҰ53237 and the \add вүҲcontainer\add* of oil and lift them up as a wave offering \add вүҲin frontВҰ53247\add* of YahwehВҰ53248.
\v 25 ThenВҰ53250 \add ?@the person\add* should slaughter \add &that\add* guilt offering lambВҰ53253, and the priestВҰ53256 mustВҰ53250 take some of \add вүҲthat\add* bloodВҰ53257 and put it on the lobe of the right earВҰ53263 of the person being purifiedВҰ53265, and on their right thumbВҰ53269 and right big toe.
\v 26 ThenВҰ53278 \add *he\add* mustВҰ53281 pour some of the oilВҰ53280 onto \add *his\add* left palmВҰ53285
\v 27 andВҰ53289 with his rightВҰ53292 fingerВҰ53291 he mustВҰ53289 \add вүҲflick\add* it sevenВҰ53301 timesВҰ53302 \add вүҲtowards\add* YahwehВҰ53304.
\v 28 ThenВҰ53306 the priestВҰ53307 must put some of the oilВҰ53310 from his palmВҰ53315 onto the lobe of the right earВҰ53319 of the person being purifiedВҰ53320, and on their right thumbВҰ53324 and right bigВҰ53329 toeВҰ53329вҖ”on top of the bloodВҰ53335 from the guiltВҰ53336 offeringВҰ53336.
\v 29 ThenВҰ53338 the priest will put \add all\add* the remainingВҰ53338 oilВҰ53341 from his palmВҰ53345 onto the headВҰ53350 of the person being purifiedВҰ53351, andВҰ53338 the priest \add вүҲwill thenВҰ53338 make thatВҰ53342 person right with\add* YahwehВҰ53355.
\v 30 ThenВҰ53357 he mustВҰ53357 \add вүҲofferВҰ53357\add* one of the birds (doveВҰ53368 or pigeonвҖ”whatever \add @that person\add* \add вүҲcould afford\add*)
\v 31 as a sin offering and \add вүҲthe other\add* as a burntВҰ53385 offering along with the grainВҰ53388 offering and he will make \add вүҲthatВҰ53374 person right again with\add* YahwehВҰ53394.
\v 32 \add The above\add* are the regulations for anyone who has a skin diseaseВҰ53402 \add вүҲbut who couldn't afford the regular purificationВҰ53408 offerings\add*.
\s1 Treating contaminated homes
\rem /s1 Cleansing From Mildew; Mildew in Houses; Treatment of Contaminated Houses
\p
\v 33 Then YahwehВҰ53412 told MoshehВҰ53415 and Aharon:
\p
\v 34 вҖң\add вүҲWhen\add* you enter into the land of Kanaan whichВҰ53427 I'm giving you all as a possession, and if I \add вүҲcause\add* an infection in one yourВҰ53437 homes in \add *that\add* land,
\v 35 thenВҰ53439 the homeowner mustВҰ53439 go andВҰ53439 inform the priestВҰ53445 that something like an infection has appearedВҰ53448 in their house.
\v 36 The priestВҰ53453 mustВҰ53452 order that everything be removed out of the house beforeВҰ53458 \add *he\add* comes to \add вүҲinspect it\add* \add вүҲso that\add* it won'tВҰ53465 all be pronounced as вҖҳuncleanВҰ53466вҖҷ. After \add вүҲthat's done\add*, he'll go to see the house
\v 37 and \add вүҲexamine\add* the growth. If the growth is greenishВҰ53489 or reddishВҰ53491 and seems more than surface deep,
\v 38 thenВҰ53498 the priestВҰ53499 mustВҰ53498 leave the house via the \add main\add* entranceВҰ53505 andВҰ53498 quarantine the house for sevenВҰ53511 daysВҰ53512.
\v 39 On the seventhВҰ53517 dayВҰ53516, the priestВҰ53515 mustВҰ53514 returnВҰ53514 and \add вүҲexamine itВҰ53520\add* \add again\add*, and if the growth has spreadВҰ53520 on the houseВҰ53523 wallsВҰ53522,
\v 40 thenВҰ53525 \add *he\add* mustВҰ53525 order that those infected stonesВҰ53530 be pulled out of the wall andВҰ53525 thrownВҰ53534 outsideВҰ53538 the cityВҰ53539 into a placeВҰ53542 \add that's considered\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ53543вҖҷ.
\v 41 ThenВҰ53545 \add the homeowner\add* mustВҰ53548 scrapeВҰ53548 \add вүҲall the plaster off the insideВҰ53549 walls\add* andВҰ53551 \add also\add* \add вүҲdispose of that\add* at \add &that\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ53564вҖҷ placeВҰ53563.
\v 42 ThenВҰ53566 they \add вүҲcan replace the stones that were removed\add*, andВҰ53566 \add вүҲapply fresh plasterВҰ53577\add* to the houseВҰ53580.
\p
\v 43 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the growth returnsВҰ53584 and breaksВҰ53586 out \add again\add* in the house \add even\add* after \add вүҲthe stonesВҰ53592 were replaced and the walls were replastered\add*,
\v 44 then the priestВҰ53602 mustВҰ53601 come \add back\add* and \add вүҲreexamine\add* it. If the growth has spreadВҰ53605 \add вүҲon the walls\add*, then it's a malignantВҰ53609 growth and \add @the house\add* is вҖҳuncleanВҰ53612вҖҷ.
\v 45 \add @The owner\add* must tear the house downвҖ”its stonesВҰ53621 and timber and all the mortar, must be \add вүҲcarted\add* outsideВҰ53633 the cityВҰ53634 into a placeВҰ53637 \add that's considered\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ53638вҖҷ.
\v 46 Any person that enters that houseВҰ53643 \add вүҲafter the priest had quarantined it\add*, will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53649вҖҷ untilВҰ53650 \add &that\add* eveningВҰ53652.
\v 47 Any person who lies down or eats in that house, mustВҰ53656 wash their clothesВҰ53659.
\p
\v 48 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the priestВҰ53671 \add вүҲcame back\add* after the house was replastered andВҰ53667 \add вүҲafter his inspection, find that\add* the growth \add вүҲhasn't reappeared\add*, thenВҰ53667 \add *he\add* can pronounce the house as вҖҳcleanвҖҷ becauseВҰ53689 the \add вүҲgrowth has gone\add*.
\v 49 Then he mustВҰ53694 takeВҰ53694 twoВҰ53699 birdsВҰ53700, cedarВҰ53702 wood, scarletВҰ53703 \add вүҲthread\add*, and some hyssopВҰ53705 \add twigs\add*,
\v 50 andВҰ53707 slaughter one bird \add ?вүҲso the blood runs into\add* a clay jug \add ?вүҲcontaining\add* waterВҰ53719 \add вүҲfrom a spring or creek\add*.
\v 51 ThenВҰ53722 \add ?@the priest\add* mustВҰ53722 takeВҰ53722 the live bird, along with the cedarВҰ53727 wood, the scarletВҰ53733 \add thread\add*, the hyssopВҰ53730 \add twigs\add* and the live bird, and dip them \add вүҲall\add* into thatВҰ53742 bloodВҰ53740 of the slaughtered bird (\add ?вүҲmixed with\add* the \add вүҲfresh\add* waterВҰ53743), and \add вүҲflick\add* it sevenВҰ53749 timesВҰ53750 onto the houseВҰ53748.
\v 52 \add In that way,\add* he'll purify the houseВҰ53755 with the bird's bloodВҰ53756 and the \add вүҲfresh\add* waterВҰ53758, and with the live bird and the cedarВҰ53763 \add wood\add*, the hyssopВҰ53764 \add twigs\add* and the scarletВҰ53765 \add thread\add*.
\v 53 ThenВҰ53768 he mustВҰ53768 \add вүҲrelease\add* the live bird \add to fly\add* into the countrysideВҰ53780, \add вүҲthus\add* making the houseВҰ53784 \add вүҲright with God\add*, andВҰ53768 thenВҰ53768 it'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 54 \add @The above\add* are the regulations concerning any seriousВҰ53792 skin diseasesВҰ53792 andВҰ53793 itchiness,
\v 55 as well as growths on clothingВҰ53796 andВҰ53797 \add вүҲbuildings\add*
\v 56 and swellingsВҰ53799, rashes, and bright spots \add on the skin\add*,
\v 57 \add вүҲso that you'll know how to determine what's\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ53805вҖҷ or вҖҳcleanвҖҷ. Those are the regulations for \add вүҲinfectious growths\add*.
\c 15
\s1 Dealing with bodily discharges
\rem /s1 Bodily Discharges; Unclean Bodily Discharges; Discharges Causing Uncleanness; Concerning Bodily Discharges
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ53814 told MoshehВҰ53817 and AaronВҰ53820:
\p
\v 2 TellВҰ53827 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ53826\add* that whenever any man has a dischargeВҰ53834 from his \add вүҲgenitals\add*, then he becomes вҖҳuncleanВҰ53837вҖҷ.
\v 3 He becomes вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ whether his bodyВҰ53845 secretesВҰ53844 the flow or if it's blockedвҖ”either way he's вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 4 Any bed thatВҰ53860 he was lying on during \add or after\add* the dischargeВҰ53863 becomes вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ, as does anything he sits on.
\v 5 Anyone who touchesВҰ53876 that bed mustВҰ53876 wash their clothesВҰ53879 and bathe themself in waterВҰ53881, and \add @that person\add* will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53882вҖҷ untilВҰ53883 the eveningВҰ53885.
\v 6 \add вүҲSimilarly,\add* anyoneВҰ53887 who sitsВҰ53887 on the place where he sat mustВҰ53893 wash their clothesВҰ53897 and bathe themself in waterВҰ53899, and \add @that person\add* will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53900вҖҷ untilВҰ53901 the eveningВҰ53903.
\v 7 AnyoneВҰ53905 who touchesВҰ53905 the man who had a dischargeВҰ53907 mustВҰ53908 wash their clothesВҰ53909 and bathe themself in waterВҰ53911, and \add @that person\add* will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53912вҖҷ untilВҰ53913 the eveningВҰ53915.
\v 8 If that man who had a dischargeВҰ53920 spits on some person who was вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, thenВҰ53917 \add @that person\add* mustВҰ53919 wash their clothesВҰ53923 and bathe themself in waterВҰ53925, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53926вҖҷ untilВҰ53927 the eveningВҰ53929.
\v 9 Any thing thatВҰ53934 the man who had a dischargeВҰ53937 rides on, will become вҖҳuncleanВҰ53938вҖҷ,
\v 10 and anyone who touchesВҰ53942 itВҰ53945 will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ until the evening, plusВҰ53951 anyone who \add вүҲcarriesВҰ53951 any of those things\add*, mustВҰ53945 wash their clothesВҰ53954 and bathe themself in waterВҰ53956, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ until the evening.
\v 11 Anyone the \add вүҲman who had a dischargeВҰ53967\add* touchesВҰ53964 and do didn'tВҰ53969 rinseВҰ53971 their handsВҰ53968 in water, mustВҰ53964 wash their clothesВҰ53974 and bathe themself in water, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ53977вҖҷ untilВҰ53978 the eveningВҰ53980.
\v 12 Any container thatВҰ53985 the \add вүҲman who had a dischargeВҰ53990\add* touchesВҰ53987, mustВҰ53987 be \add вүҲsmashed\add* if it's \add вүҲmade from\add* clay andВҰ53992 rinsedВҰ53997 with waterВҰ53998 if it's \add вүҲmade from\add* wood.
\p
\v 13 WhenВҰ54000 the \add вүҲman's dischargeВҰ54003 ceases\add*, he must mark off sevenВҰ54007 daysВҰ54008 for his purificationВҰ54009, and thenВҰ54000 he must wash his clothesВҰ54011 and bathe himself in waterВҰ54014, and \add after that,\add* he'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 14 ThenВҰ54018 on the eighthВҰ54019 dayВҰ54018, he mustВҰ54020 takeВҰ54020 two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ54027\add* pigeons, andВҰ54018 \add вүҲstand in frontВҰ54031\add* of YahwehВҰ54032 at the entranceВҰ54035 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ54036\add* tentВҰ54036. There he should giveВҰ54038 them to a priestВҰ54041,
\v 15 and the priestВҰ54045 mustВҰ54043 \add вүҲoffer\add* one as a sin offering and \add вүҲthe other\add* as a burntВҰ54049 offering, \add вүҲthus making the man right\add* with YahwehВҰ54054 for his dischargeВҰ54055.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲNow\add* when a manВҰ54058 has an \add вүҲemission of semen\add*, then he mustВҰ54061 bathe his entireВҰ54070 bodyВҰ54072 in waterВҰ54067, and he'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54073вҖҷ untilВҰ54074 the eveningВҰ54076.
\v 17 He mustВҰ54086 also wash all his clothing, and any leather articles on him \add вүҲthat came into contact with the semen\add* and \add @all of that\add* will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54093вҖҷ untilВҰ54094 the eveningВҰ54096.
\v 18 \add вүҲWhen a man and a womanВҰ54099 вҖҳsleep togetherвҖҷ\add*, then they mustВҰ54101 both bathe in waterВҰ54108, and they'll \add both\add* be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ until the evening.\f + \fr 15:18 \ft Note that if they had sexual relations in the evening, say 9pm, then they'd be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ all the next day and until the \+em following\+em* evening (because the Jewish вҖҳdayвҖҷ begins after duskвҖ”rather than at midnight like modern Western society counts time).\f*
\p
\v 19 WhenВҰ54114 a womanВҰ54114 \add вүҲhas her menstrualВҰ54126 period\add*, she'll be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for sevenВҰ54123 daysВҰ54124, andВҰ54114 anyoneВҰ54129 who touchesВҰ54129 her \add вүҲduring that timeВҰ54124\add* will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ54132 the eveningВҰ54134.
\v 20 Anything that she lies on or sits on \add вүҲduring that time\add* will become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 21 AnyoneВҰ54151 who touchesВҰ54151 herВҰ54152 bed mustВҰ54153 wash their clothesВҰ54154 and bathe in waterВҰ54156, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54157вҖҷ untilВҰ54158 the eveningВҰ54160.
\v 22 AnyoneВҰ54164 who touchesВҰ54164 anything thatВҰ54168 sheВҰ54170 sat on mustВҰ54170 wash their clothesВҰ54173 and bathe in waterВҰ54175, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54176вҖҷ untilВҰ54177 the eveningВҰ54179,
\v 23 \add вүҲi.e.,\add* whether it's her bed or something sheВҰ54192 sat on, anyone who touchesВҰ54196 it will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54199вҖҷ untilВҰ54200 the eveningВҰ54202.
\v 24 If a manВҰ54207 \add вүҲsleeps with\add* \add @a menstruatingВҰ54210 woman\add* and \add вүҲgets blood\add* on him, thenВҰ54204 he'll be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ for sevenВҰ54213 daysВҰ54214, and any bed thatВҰ54218 he lies on will \add also\add* become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\p
\v 25 If any womanВҰ54225 \add вүҲhas a bloodВҰ54230 flow when it's not her period\add*, or \add вүҲkeeps bleeding beyond her menstrual period\add*, all \add вүҲthose\add* days \add вүҲwill be regarded the same as her menstruation so she'll be\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ54248вҖҷ.
\v 26 Any bed thatВҰ54258 she lies on \add вүҲas long as she's dischargingВҰ54265 blood will be regarded the same as during herВҰ54264 menstruation and will\add* be вҖҳuncleanВҰ54277вҖҷ, as will anything she sits on.
\v 27 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ54282,\add* any person who touchesВҰ54284 them will be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ and they mustВҰ54286 wash their clothesВҰ54288 and bathe in waterВҰ54290, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ untilВҰ54292 the eveningВҰ54294.
\v 28 \add вүҲOnce the flow stops,\add* then \add @the woman\add* mustВҰ54300 countВҰ54300 off sevenВҰ54302 daysВҰ54303, andВҰ54296 then she'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ afterВҰ54304 that.
\v 29 ThenВҰ54307 on the eighthВҰ54308 dayВҰ54307, she mustВҰ54309 takeВҰ54309 two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ54316\add* pigeons andВҰ54307 \add вүҲgive them\add* to a priestВҰ54322 at the entranceВҰ54325 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ54326\add* tentВҰ54326,
\v 30 and he will offer one as a sin offering and \add вүҲthe other\add* as a burntВҰ54338 offering, \add вүҲthus making her right with\add* YahwehВҰ54343 from her вҖҳuncleanВҰ54345вҖҷ flow.
\p
\v 31 YouВҰ54352 two mustВҰ54347 keepВҰ54347 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ54350 peopleВҰ54350\add* separateВҰ54347 from their вҖҳuncleannessВҰ54357вҖҷ, thenВҰ54347 they won'tВҰ54354 defile my residence that's amongВҰ54362 them, andВҰ54347 cause their \add own\add* death.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲThe above\add* are the regulations for any man with a dischargeВҰ54366 or a seminal emission thatВҰ54367 makes him вҖҳuncleanВҰ54373вҖҷ,
\v 33 plusВҰ54379 any woman who is menstruatingВҰ54377 or has a bodily dischargeВҰ54379, as well as any man who sleeps with an вҖҳuncleanВҰ54390вҖҷ woman.
\c 16
\s1 The day for making things right
\rem /s1 The Day of Atonement
\p
\v 1 Yahweh spokeВҰ54393 to MoshehВҰ54397 afterВҰ54398 the deathВҰ54399 of twoВҰ54400 of Aharon's sonsВҰ54401 when they approached Yahweh \add wrongly\add* and diedВҰ54407,
\v 2 and \add *he\add* told MoshehВҰ54413:
\p Tell your brotherВҰ54418 Aharon that if he doesn't \add want to\add* dieВҰ54439, thenВҰ54409 he mustn't \add just\add* enter the \add вүҲholiest roomВҰ54427\add* insideВҰ54428 the curtainВҰ54429 at any old timeВҰ54424. The atonement lid is on the \add sacredВҰ54427\add* box, and I will appearВҰ54442 in a cloudВҰ54441 over \add *that\add* lid.\x + \xo 16:2: \xt Heb 6:19.\x*
\p
\v 3 This is \add how\add* Aharon must enter the \add вүҲsacredВҰ54452 tent\add*: \add he must acquire\add* a \add вүҲyoungВҰ54454\add* bullВҰ54453 for a sin offering, and a ram for a burntВҰ54459 offering.
\v 4 вҮ”He must bathe himselfВҰ54475 in waterВҰ54484 and then put on linen underclothesВҰ54466, followed by his sacred linen tunicВҰ54461 and tie the linen sashВҰ54473 around it. Then he must wrap the linen turbanВҰ54476 on. Those are \add all\add* sacred clothesВҰ54479.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ54493 \add @Aharon\add* mustВҰ54494 \add acquire\add* two \add вүҲyoung\add* goats for a sin offering andВҰ54490 one ram for a burntВҰ54502 offering.
\v 6 \add *He\add* mustВҰ54504 presentВҰ54504 the bullВҰ54508 as a sinВҰ54509 offeringВҰ54509 for himselfВҰ54514 to \add вүҲmake both him andВҰ54504 his householdВҰ54516 right with GodВҰ54505\add*.
\v 7 ThenВҰ54518 he mustВҰ54518 takeВҰ54518 the twoВҰ54521 goatsВҰ54522 andВҰ54518 make them stand \add вүҲin frontВҰ54525\add* of YahwehВҰ54526 at the entranceВҰ54527 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ54528\add* tentВҰ54528,
\v 8 and \add вүҲthrow dice to decide which\add* one is for YahwehВҰ54540, and one is to be the вҖҳscapegoatвҖҷ.
\v 9 ThenВҰ54545 AharonВҰ54546 mustВҰ54545 presentВҰ54545 the goatВҰ54549 that's for YahwehВҰ54554, andВҰ54545 offer it as a sinВҰ54556 offeringВҰ54556,
\v 10 \add вүҲbutВҰ54558\add* the \add вүҲchosen\add* вҖҳscapegoatвҖҷ mustВҰ54564 be kept standing there \add вүҲin frontВҰ54567\add* of Yahweh, \add вүҲbecause it'll be used to make the people right with Yahweh\add*, \add andВҰ54558 be sent\add* into the wildernessВҰ54574.
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ54576 Aharon mustВҰ54576 presentВҰ54576 the bull for his own sin offering \add вүҲto make him andВҰ54576 his householdВҰ54588 right with God\add*, thenВҰ54576 he'll slaughter the bull for the sin offering for himselfВҰ54586.
\v 12 ThenВҰ54598 he mustВҰ54598 get a panful of burningВҰ54604 coalsВҰ54602 off the altarВҰ54606 \add вүҲin front\add* of YahwehВҰ54608 as well as two handfuls of finely-ground, fragrant incenseВҰ54611, andВҰ54598 takeВҰ54598 them insideВҰ54615 the curtainВҰ54616
\v 13 where he'll put the incense on the \add вүҲcoals\add* in Yahweh'sВҰ54626 \add вүҲpresence\add*. ThenВҰ54618 the \add smoke\add* cloudВҰ54629 from the incense will cover the atonementВҰ54633 lid on the \add sacred\add* chest, andВҰ54618 he won'tВҰ54638 die.
\v 14 ThenВҰ54641 he must take some of the bull's blood, andВҰ54641 using his finger, he must flick the blood sevenВҰ54654 timesВҰ54656 onto the eastern the side of the lid and seven times onto the frontВҰ54648 of the lid.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ54662 \add @Aharon\add* mustВҰ54662 slaughter the goat for the people'sВҰ54668 sin offeringВҰ54666, and take its blood insideВҰ54675 the curtainВҰ54676, and do the same with it thatВҰ54667 he did to the bull's bloodвҖ”\add вүҲflicking\add* it onto the side and front of the atonement lid,\x + \xo 16:15: \xt Heb 9:12.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲthus\add* making the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ54698 people\add* \add вүҲright with Yahweh\add* for their uncleanness and their \add вүҲrebellion and disobedience\add*. \add вүҲThat's also for\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ54696\add* tent whichВҰ54708 is among \add @the people\add* with their uncleanness.
\v 17 \add вүҲNo one else can enter\add* the \add вүҲsacred\add* tentВҰ54720 when \add @Aharon\add* enters to make atonement in the \add вүҲsacred roomВҰ54724\add* untilВҰ54725 he leaves \add again\add*. He mustВҰ54718 make atonement for himselfВҰ54729 andВҰ54713 his householdВҰ54731, as well as for the whole \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ54735 community\add*,
\v 18 thenВҰ54738 he'll go out to the altar that's \add вүҲin frontВҰ54743\add* of YahwehВҰ54745 and make atonementВҰ54746 for thatвҖ”he mustВҰ54738 take some of the bull's blood and some of the goat's blood and put it on the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar.
\v 19 ThenВҰ54760 he mustВҰ54760 \add вүҲflick\add* bloodВҰ54764 on to it sevenВҰ54766 timesВҰ54767 with his fingerВҰ54765, thus purifyingВҰ54768 it andВҰ54760 \add вүҲremoving\add* the uncleannessВҰ54770 of the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ54771 peopleВҰ54771 from it\add*.
\s1 The goat taking the blame
\rem /s1 The Scapegoat
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲWhenВҰ54774\add* \add @Aharon\add* has finishedВҰ54774 purifying the sacred \add вүҲroomВҰ54778\add*, the \add вүҲsacred\add* tentВҰ54781, andВҰ54774 the altarВҰ54785, thenВҰ54774 he should presentВҰ54786 the live goatВҰ54789.
\v 21 \add *He\add* must place \add вүҲbothВҰ54796\add* his handsВҰ54797 on the goat's head, and confessВҰ54803 all of Israel'sВҰ54811 \add вүҲdisobedience, rebellion, and shortcomings\add*вҖ”\add symbolically\add* placing them onto the goat's head, and thenВҰ54792 he must choose a man \add вүҲthat's nearby\add* to take it into the wildernessВҰ54831.
\v 22 вҮ”Then he'll release the goat there in the wildernessВҰ54849, andВҰ54833 the goat will carry all theirВҰ54840 sins into that barren land.
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ54851 AharonВҰ54852 mustВҰ54851 enter the \add вүҲsacred\add* tentВҰ54855 and take off the linenВҰ54861 garmentВҰ54860 thatВҰ54862 he'd put on as he'd entered into the sacred \add вүҲroomВҰ54867\add* and leaveВҰ54868 them thereВҰ54869.\x + \xo 16:23: \xt Eze 44:19.\x*
\v 24 ThenВҰ54871 he mustВҰ54871 wash himself in waterВҰ54875 in a sacredВҰ54877 placeВҰ54876, put on his \add regular\add* clothesВҰ54881, and go out and make his burnt offering and the burnt offering for the people, \add вүҲthus making both himself and the people right with Yahweh\add*.
\v 25 ThenВҰ54896 he mustВҰ54899 burn the fat from the sinВҰ54898 offeringВҰ54898 up on the altarВҰ54900.
\v 26 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ54902,\add* the person who led away the вҖҳscapegoatвҖҷ mustВҰ54907 wash his clothesВҰ54908 and bathe himself in waterВҰ54913, and thenВҰ54902 he can reenter the campВҰ54920.
\v 27 ThenВҰ54922 \add the remains of\add* the bullВҰ54923 and the goatВҰ54927 from the sin offerings (whose bloodВҰ54933 was taken into the sacred \add вүҲroomВҰ54935\add* to make atonementВҰ54934) must be taken to a placeВҰ54935 outsideВҰ54939 the campВҰ54940 where they must be burntвҖ”skins, fleshВҰ54948, and dung.\x + \xo 16:27: \xt Heb 13:11.\x*
\v 28 The man who burnt them mustВҰ54955 then wash his clothesВҰ54956 and bathe his bodyВҰ54960 in waterВҰ54961, and then he can reenter the campВҰ54968.
\s1 The national purification day
\rem /s1 Observing the Day of Atonement
\p
\v 29 This will be a permanentВҰ54973 regulationВҰ54972 for you all:
\p On the 10th of the seventhВҰ54975 month \add (of TishreiвҖ”around September/October)\add*, all of you includingВҰ54982 those who are native-born as well as foreigners living amongВҰ54990 you, mustВҰ54970 humble yourselves andВҰ54970 not \add вүҲworkВҰ54984 that day\add*\x + \xo 16:29-34: \xt Lev 23:26-32; Num 29:7-11.\x*
\v 30 because on that dayВҰ54994, \add @the high priest\add* will purifyВҰ54998 you all from your sinsВҰ55001 \add вүҲto make you right with\add* YahwehВҰ55003, and you'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 31 It'll be a \add вүҲvery sacred\add* rest day for you, andВҰ55010 you all mustВҰ55010 humble \add вүҲyourselves\add*вҖ”a permanentВҰ55015 regulationВҰ55014 \add for you all\add*.
\v 32 The priest \add вүҲwho's anointedВҰ55021 and ordained to succeed\add* his fatherВҰ55030 \add as high priest\add* must \add вүҲbe the one to\add* make atonementВҰ55017, and he must be wearing his \add вүҲsacredВҰ55037\add* linenВҰ55035 clothesВҰ55034.
\v 33 He will \add first\add* \add вүҲpurify\add* the \add вүҲsacred room\add* and the \add вүҲsacred\add* tentВҰ55046, and the altarВҰ55050, and thenВҰ55039 \add вүҲmake all the priestsВҰ55053 right with Yahweh\add* and \add finally,\add* the \add вүҲentireВҰ55056 community\add*.
\v 34 That will becomeВҰ55062 a permanentВҰ55067 regulationВҰ55066 every yearВҰ55077 to \add вүҲmake all the IsraelisВҰ55071 right with Yahweh because of\add* theirВҰ55075 sinsВҰ55075.
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ55062\add* MoshehВҰ55084 did exactly as Yahweh had instructedВҰ55080 him.
\c 17
\s1 Slaughtering animals
\rem /s1 The Slaughtering of Animals; Law of holiness; Prohibitions against Eating Blood; The Sacredness of Blood; Eating Blood Forbidden
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ55088 told MoshehВҰ55091:
\p
\v 2 Tell Aharon and his sonsВҰ55100 and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ55104\add* thatВҰ55110 \add вүҲthese are the instructionsВҰ55112 from\add* YahwehВҰ55113:
\v 3 \add вүҲNo IsraeliВҰ55119 is allowed to\add* slaughter a bullВҰ55122 or lamb or goat \add either\add* inside the camp or outsideВҰ55133 \add *it\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲIfВҰ55148 they're not taken\add* to the entranceВҰ55138 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ55139\add* tentВҰ55147 to be presented as an offering to YahwehВҰ55145 \add вүҲin frontВҰ55146\add* of \add *his\add* residence, thenВҰ55136 that personВҰ55151 \add вүҲwill be held guilty\add* of its bloodвҖ”they've shed blood so they mustВҰ55150 be cut off from his peopleВҰ55159.
\v 5 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ55164\add* \add вүҲmust stop\add* sacrificing theirВҰ55168 \add вүҲanimals\add* in the countrysideВҰ55175, and \add instead\add* bring them to Yahweh at the entranceВҰ55180 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ55181\add* tentВҰ55181, \add i.e., they must\add* bring them to the priestВҰ55185 and sacrifice them as peaceВҰ55188 offeringsВҰ55188 to Yahweh.
\v 6 ThenВҰ55192 the priestВҰ55193 will splash the bloodВҰ55196 onto Yahweh'sВҰ55200 altarВҰ55199 at the tentВҰ55202 entranceВҰ55201, andВҰ55204 burn up the fat to become a \add вүҲsoothingВҰ55207 aromaВҰ55206\add* for Yahweh.
\v 7 ThenВҰ55210 they \add вүҲwon'tВҰ55210 be able to continue offering\add* their sacrificesВҰ55212 to the goat demons thatВҰ55218 they're prostitutingВҰ55220 themselvesВҰ55220 to. \add вүҲThe above\add* will be a permanentВҰ55223 regulationВҰ55222 \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ55228.
\p
\v 8 You mustВҰ55231 tell them that if an \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ55235\add* or a foreigner living amongВҰ55242 them, makes a burntВҰ55246 offeringВҰ55246 or sacrificeВҰ55249
\v 9 without bringingВҰ55257 it to YahwehВҰ55260 at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ55254\add* tentВҰ55254 entranceВҰ55253, thenВҰ55251 that person mustВҰ55257 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\s1 The law concerning the blood
\rem /s1 Eating Blood Prohibited
\p
\v 10 \add IfВҰ55287 there's\add* any \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ55269\add* or foreigner living amongВҰ55274 them, who eats blood, thenВҰ55266 I'llВҰ55280 \add вүҲoppose\add* that person andВҰ55266 remove them from \add вүҲthe community\add*\x + \xo 17:10: \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 7:26-27; 19:26; Deu 12:16,23; 15:23.\x*
\v 11 because the body's life is in the blood. I myself have givenВҰ55298 you \add @blood\add* to make atonement for your lives at the altarВҰ55302, because \add вүҲit's the blood thatВҰ55311 can atone for\add* life.\x + \xo 17:11: \xt Heb 9:22.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲThat's why\add* I told the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ55318\add* that none of them mustВҰ55326 eat bloodвҖ”\add not even\add* the foreigners that live amongВҰ55330 them may eat blood.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSo any person\add* (\add вүҲIsraeliВҰ55340\add* or foreigner living amongВҰ55345 them) who catches wild game (\add вүҲincludingВҰ55337\add* birds) to eat, they mustВҰ55347 pour its bloodВҰ55358 out and coverВҰ55359 it with soil
\v 14 because the life of \add вүҲtheir bodies\add* is the blood that's in them. \add вүҲAgainВҰ55373,\add* \add that's why\add* I'veВҰ55371 told the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ55372\add* not to eat the blood of any \add вүҲliving thing\add* because the life is in the blood, and anyone who eats it mustВҰ55390 be cut off \add вүЎfrom the community\add*.
\p
\v 15 Anyone who eats \add part of\add* a carcassВҰ55397 \add they found\add* or one that was \add вүҲkilled by wild animalsВҰ55398\add*, mustВҰ55396 wash their clothesВҰ55402 and bathe in waterВҰ55404, and they'll be вҖҳuncleanВҰ55405вҖҷ untilВҰ55406 the eveningВҰ55408, and thenВҰ55392 they'll be вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add again\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add @that person\add* doesn't wash \add their clothes\add* or bathe, thenВҰ55411 they mustВҰ55413 bear \add the punishment for\add* their own \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\c 18
\s1 Sexual relationships
\rem /s1 Unlawful Sexual Relations; Forbidden Sexual Practices; Sexual Relations
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ55422 told MoshehВҰ55425:
\p
\v 2 Tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ55431\add* that I am their godВҰ55437 YahwehВҰ55436.
\v 3 \add вүҲThey mustn't behave as if they're still thereВҰ55457 in\add* EgyptВҰ55442, nor should they \add вүҲbehave like the Canaanites that were living\add* in the land that I'm taking you all into, and don'tВҰ55447 \add вүҲemulate theirВҰ55460 customs and practices\add*.
\v 4 You all mustВҰ55467 \add вүҲimbibe my values andВҰ55468 follow my instructionsВҰ55470\add*. I am your godВҰ55476 YahwehВҰ55475.
\v 5 You all mustВҰ55478 \add вүҲfollow my instructionsВҰ55481 andВҰ55478 my values\add*вҖ”those who doВҰ55486 so will liveВҰ55489. I am your god YahwehВҰ55492.\x + \xo 18:5: \xt Neh 9:29; Eze 18:9; 20:11-13; Luk 10:28; Rom 10:5; Gal 3:12.\x*
\p
\v 6 None of you may \add вүҲever flirt with any close relativeВҰ55501 to try to get them to undress\add*. I am YahwehВҰ55508.
\v 7 YouВҰ55512 mustВҰ55512 \add вүҲnever mess with your father's naked body\add*, or your mother'sвҖ”no, she's your mother so don'tВҰ55515 \add вүҲever take advantage of herВҰ55521 nakedness\add*.
\v 8 Don'tВҰ55528 \add вүҲever mess with any of your father's wives, because their naked bodies are the realm\add* of your father.\x + \xo 18:8: \xt Lev 20:11; Deu 22:30; 27:20.\x*
\v 9 Don'tВҰ55539 \add вүҲflirt with your sister's nakedness, whether she's a full sister, a half sister, or an adopted sister\add*.\x + \xo 18:9: \xt Lev 20:17; Deu 27:22.\x*
\v 10 Don'tВҰ55562 \add вүҲflirt with your grandchildren's nakedness, becauseВҰ55565 you'd be absolutely shaming yourself\add*.
\v 11 Don'tВҰ55579 \add вүҲflirt with your step-sister's\add* nakedness, because she's your sister and herВҰ55581 nakedness \add вүҲisn'tВҰ55579 yours to enjoy\add*.
\v 12 Don'tВҰ55588 \add вүҲflirt with your aunts nakednessВҰ55584 on your father's side\add*, because \add вүҲshe's closely relatedВҰ55590 to\add* your father.\x + \xo 18:12-14: \xt Lev 20:19-20.\x*
\v 13 Don'tВҰ55599 \add вүҲflirt with your aunt's nakednessВҰ55595 on your mother's side\add*, becauseВҰ55601 \add вүҲshe's closely relatedВҰ55603 to\add* your mother.
\v 14 Don'tВҰ55611 \add вүҲflirt with your uncle's nakednessВҰ55608 on your father's side\add*, and \add вүҲkeep away\add* from his wife, because she's your aunt.
\v 15 Don'tВҰ55625 \add вүҲflirt with\add* your daughter-in-law's nakedness, because she's your son's wifeВҰ55627 and herВҰ55632 nakedness \add вүҲisn'tВҰ55625 yours to enjoy\add*.\x + \xo 18:15: \xt Lev 20:12.\x*
\v 16 Don'tВҰ55639 \add вүҲflirt with\add* your sister-in-law, because \add вүҲher naked body is the realm\add* of your brother.\x + \xo 18:16: \xt Lev 20:21.\x*
\v 17 Don'tВҰ55649 \add вүҲflirt with\add* the nakedness of \add both\add* a womanВҰ55647 and her daughter \add вүҲor her granddaughter\add*, because they're \add вүҲrelatedВҰ55665 to each other\add*вҖ”that would be perverse.\x + \xo 18:17: \xt Lev 20:14; Deu 27:23.\x*
\v 18 Don'tВҰ55674 take your wife's sisterВҰ55673 \add вүҲto be a junior wife\add* \add вүҲwhile your wife is still alive\add*.
\p
\v 19 Don'tВҰ55687 approach a womanВҰ55684 \add вүҲwho's menstruatingВҰ55685, to undress herВҰ55685\add*, because she's вҖҳuncleanВҰ55686вҖҷ.\x + \xo 18:19: \xt Lev 20:18.\x*
\v 20 Don'tВҰ55696 sleep with \add вүҲsomeone else's\add* wifeВҰ55694вҖ”your \add вүҲchild with herВҰ55703 would be\add* вҖҳuncleanВҰ55701вҖҷ.\x + \xo 18:20: \xt Lev 20:10.\x*
\v 21 Don'tВҰ55706 \add вүҲsacrifice your children\add* to MolekВҰ55710 so you don'tВҰ55706 profaneВҰ55712 your god's \add вүҲreputationВҰ55715\add*. IВҰ55717 am YahwehВҰ55718.\x + \xo 18:21: \xt Lev 20:1-5.\x*
\v 22 Don'tВҰ55723 \add вүҲhave sexual relations\add* with a man like with a womanВҰ55726вҖ”it's an abominationВҰ55727.\x + \xo 18:22: \xt Lev 20:13.\x*
\v 23 \add Men,\add* don't \add вүҲhave sexual relations\add* with any animal as that would make youВҰ55735 вҖҳuncleanВҰ55737вҖҷ. And women, don't giveВҰ55735 yourself \add вүҲsexually\add* to any animal as that's perverse.\x + \xo 18:23: \xt Exo 22:19; Lev 20:15-16; Deu 27:21.\x*
\p
\v 24 Don'tВҰ55750 make yourselvesВҰ55752 вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ in any of \add @the above\add* ways, becauseВҰ55756 all of those things were done by the \add вүҲpeople groups\add* thatВҰ55762 I'mВҰ55764 \add вүҲdriving out\add* of this land ahead of you all.
\v 25 The land had become вҖҳuncleanВҰ55768вҖҷ \add вүҲso I made them pay for their wickedness\add* andВҰ55768 \add so\add* the land will vomitВҰ55773 out its inhabitantsВҰ55777.
\v 26 \add вүҲHowever,\add* you all mustВҰ55779 \add вүҲobey my instructionsВҰ55783 and decisionsВҰ55783\add* and not \add вүҲtolerate\add* any of \add вүҲthat perverse behaviour\add*вҖ”not you who are native-born, nor any foreigner living amongВҰ55795 you all,
\v 27 because all \add вүҲthat perversity\add* was done by those living there beforeВҰ55809 you all, and the land becameВҰ55810 вҖҳuncleanВҰ55810вҖҷ.
\v 28 \add Don'tВҰ55813 think\add* that the land won'tВҰ55813 vomitВҰ55815 you all out just like it's doing to the \add вүҲpeople groups\add* that have been \add there\add* beforeВҰ55826 you,
\v 29 because everyoneВҰ55829 who does any of \add вүҲthose perversities\add* will be cut off from theirВҰ55840 \add вүҲcommunity\add*.
\v 30 \add вүҲSoВҰ55842\add* you all mustВҰ55842 carefully guard against \add вүҲpractising any of those detestable customsВҰ55848\add* which were \add вүҲpreviously\add* doneВҰ55851 \add there\add* andВҰ55842 which would make you all вҖҳuncleanВҰ55854вҖҷ. IВҰ55856 am your godВҰ55858 YahwehВҰ55857.
\c 19
\s1 Various moral imperatives
\rem /s1 Ritual and Moral Holiness; Various Laws; Laws of Holiness and Justice; Holiness in Personal Conduct
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ55862 told MoshehВҰ55865:
\p
\v 2 Tell the \add вүҲentireВҰ55871 IsraeliВҰ55874 community\add* that they mustВҰ55877 \add вүҲbe separate from others\add*, becauseВҰ55881 I, your godВҰ55885 YahwehВҰ55884, am holy \add (i.e., separated from impurity)\add*.\x + \xo 19:2: \xt Lev 11:44-45; 1Pe 1:16.\x*
\v 3 Everyone mustВҰ55890 \add вүҲrespect and obey\add* their \add вүҲparents\add*, and observe my rest days. I am your godВҰ55897 YahwehВҰ55896.\x + \xo 19:3: a \xt Exo 20:12; Deu 5:16; \xo b \xt Exo 20:8; Deu 5:12.\x*
\p
\v 4 Don'tВҰ55899 turnВҰ55901 to worthlessВҰ55904 idolsВҰ55904, andВҰ55905 don'tВҰ55899 make cast metalВҰ55906 godsВҰ55905 for yourselves. IВҰ55910 am your godВҰ55912 YahwehВҰ55911.\x + \xo 19:4: a \xt Lev 26:1; \xo b \xt Exo 20:23; 34:17; Deu 27:15.\x*
\p
\v 5 WhenВҰ55918 you all sacrifice peaceВҰ55917 offeringsВҰ55917, \add вүҲdo itВҰ55920 correctly so that you'll all be acceptedВҰ55919\add*.
\v 6 \add The meat from\add* your sacrificeВҰ55923 must be eatenВҰ55924 that same day or the next dayвҖ”anything left untilВҰ55927 the thirdВҰ55930 day must be \add вүҲthrown into the fire\add*.
\v 7 If it was to be eaten on the thirdВҰ55938 dayВҰ55937, it would be вҖҳuncleanВҰ55939вҖҷ andВҰ55934 not acceptableВҰ55942,
\v 8 and the people eating it would have to bear their own \add вүҲguilt\add* for profaningВҰ55953 Yahweh'sВҰ55952 holiness, and that person mustВҰ55946 be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\p
\v 9 WhenВҰ55959 you all harvest your \add вүҲcrops off\add* your land, you mustn't \add вүҲcut the grain right to the very\add* edge of your fieldВҰ55967, andВҰ55959 nor \add вүҲcan you all pick up any dropped stalks\add*.\x + \xo 19:9-10: \xt Lev 27:15; Deu 24:19-22.\x*
\v 10 In your \add #vineyards\add*, you must not \add вүҲpick every last grapeВҰ55977 or pick up any that fall on the ground\add*, because they must be left for the poor andВҰ55974 for the foreigners. I am your godВҰ55987 YahwehВҰ55986.
\p
\v 11 You all mustn't stealВҰ55990 or deceiveВҰ55993, or defraud any fellowВҰ55998 citizenВҰ55998,\x + \xo 19:11: a \xt Exo 20:15; Deu 5:19; \xo b \xt Exo 20:16; Deu 5:20.\x*
\v 12 and don'tВҰ56000 use my name to \add вүҲseal\add* a promise and thenВҰ56000 \add go ahead and\add* \add вүҲruin my reputationВҰ56003\add*. IВҰ56010 am YahwehВҰ56011.\x + \xo 19:12: \xt Exo 20:7; Deu 5:11; Mat 5:33.\x*
\p
\v 13 Don't oppressВҰ56015 yourВҰ56018 \add #neighbours\add* or steal from them. Don't \add вүҲfail to pay a day-labourer as they finish each day's work\add*.\x + \xo 19:13: \xt Deu 24:14-15.\x*
\v 14 Don'tВҰ56037 curseВҰ56033 a deaf person, or \add вүҲput something in front of\add* a blindВҰ56036 person \add to trip them\add*. You mustВҰ56033 \add вүҲrespect and obey\add* your godВҰ56041. I am YahwehВҰ56043.\x + \xo 19:14: \xt Deu 27:18.\x*
\p
\v 15 Don'tВҰ56050 judge unfairlyвҖ”showing partiality to the poor, or honouringВҰ56057 those who are well-knownвҖ”you mustВҰ56047 \add always\add* judge your fellowВҰ56062 citizensВҰ56062 fairly.\x + \xo 19:15: \xt Exo 23:6-8; Deu 16:19.\x*
\v 16 Don't goВҰ56066 around slanderingВҰ56067 people. Don't \add ?вүҲtake advantage of yourВҰ56074 neighbour'sВҰ56074 death\add*. I am YahwehВҰ56076.
\p
\v 17 You mustn't hateВҰ56080 your brotherВҰ56083. Certainly rebuke \add вүҲthose you interact with\add* \add вүҲso you don'tВҰ56090 get blamed for their bad behaviour\add*.\x + \xo 19:17: \xt Mat 18:15.\x*
\v 18 Don'tВҰ56099 try to get revenge against others or hold a grudge against any of your peopleВҰ56105, butВҰ56099 \add instead,\add* loveВҰ56106 your neighbourВҰ56107 as yourself. IВҰ56109 am YahwehВҰ56110.\x + \xo 19:18: \xt Mat 5:43; 19:19; 22:39; Mrk 12:31; Luk 10:27; Rom 13:9; Gal 5:14; Jam 2:8.\x*
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲFollow my instructionsВҰ56114\add*вҖ”don't crossbreed two different kinds of animals, don't sow two different crops in your fieldВҰ56121, and don't wear clothingВҰ56126 made of different kinds of thread.\x + \xo 19:19: \xt Deu 22:9-11.\x*
\p
\v 20 If a man impregnates a womanВҰ56140 who's destined to be someone else's slaveВҰ56145 and she hasn't been freed, compensationВҰ56157 needs to be \add paid\add*.\f + \fr 19:20 \ft We as modern readers don't understand all the dynamics of this seemingly complex social situation.\f* They mustn't be executed, becauseВҰ56135 she hadn't been freed.
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add @that man\add* mustВҰ56166 take a ram to YahwehВҰ56170 at the \add вүҲsacredВҰ56174\add* tent's entranceВҰ56173 for a guilt offering,
\v 22 and the priestВҰ56181 will make \add вүҲhim right with\add* YahwehВҰ56185 by means of thatВҰ56189 guiltВҰ56183 offeringВҰ56183 ram, and thenВҰ56179 he'll be forgivenВҰ56191 for his transgression.
\p
\v 23 When you all enter into the land and plantВҰ56204 various kinds of fruit trees, you mustn't eat the fruit for the first threeВҰ56214 yearsВҰ56215вҖ”it should be \add regarded as\add* вҖҳuncircumcisedВҰ56218вҖҷ \add for that duration\add*.
\v 24 ThenВҰ56222 in the fourthВҰ56223 yearВҰ56222, all that fruitВҰ56227 mustВҰ56224 be \add regarded as\add* вҖҳsacredВҰ56228вҖҷвҖ”praiseВҰ56229 offeringsВҰ56229 for YahwehВҰ56230.
\v 25 \add вүҲFinally,\add* in the fifthВҰ56233 yearВҰ56232, you can eatВҰ56234 that fruitВҰ56237 andВҰ56232 add that produceВҰ56240 to your harvest. I am your godВҰ56243 YahwehВҰ56242.
\p
\v 26 Don't eatВҰ56246 anything with the bloodВҰ56249 \add still in it\add*. Don't practice divinationВҰ56251 or witchcraft.\x + \xo 19:26: a \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 7:26-27; 17:10-14; Deu 12:16,23; 15:23; \xo b \xt Deu 18:10.\x*
\v 27 Don'tВҰ56259 \add have haircuts that\add* roundВҰ56256 off your hair at the sides, and \add men\add*, don'tВҰ56259 trim the edges of your \add #beards\add*.\x + \xo 19:27-28: \xt Lev 21:5; Deu 14:1.\x*
\v 28 Don'tВҰ56267 make cuts on yourВҰ56269 bodies \add вүҲwhen someone diesВҰ56266\add*, andВҰ56270 don'tВҰ56267 \add вүҲtattooВҰ56270\add* yourselvesВҰ56274. IВҰ56275 am YahwehВҰ56276.
\p
\v 29 don'tВҰ56278 defile yourВҰ56283 daughterВҰ56283 by makingВҰ56284 herВҰ56284 prostitute herselfВҰ56284, \add вүҲso the country\add* doesn't prostitute itselfВҰ56287 and become full of wickednessВҰ56291.\x + \xo 19:29: \xt Deu 23:17.\x*
\v 30 Keep my rest days, andВҰ56297 \add вүҲrespect\add* my sanctuaryВҰ56297. I am YahwehВҰ56300.\x + \xo 19:30: \xt Lev 26:2.\x*
\p
\v 31 Don'tВҰ56302 turnВҰ56304 to mediums andВҰ56308 divinersвҖ”don'tВҰ56302 make yourselves вҖҳuncleanВҰ56314вҖҷ by means of them. IВҰ56316 am your godВҰ56318 YahwehВҰ56317.\x + \xo 19:31: \xt Deu 18:11; 1Sam 28:3; 2Ki 23:4; Isa 8:19.\x*
\p
\v 32 Stand up for those with gray hairВҰ56321, and honourВҰ56323 the \add вүҲpresence\add* of the elderly. \add вүҲHonour and respect\add* yourВҰ56327 godВҰ56327. I am YahwehВҰ56329.
\p
\v 33 вҮ”Don't \add вүҲtake advantage of\add* \add #foreigners\add* when they stay in yourВҰ56337 landвҖ”\x + \xo 19:33-34: \xt Exo 22:21; Deu 24:17-18; 27:19.\x*
\v 34 you all mustВҰ56344 treat \add #foreigners\add* the same as native-born \add Israelis\add* and love them like you \add вүЎlove\add* yourselvesВҰ56352, becauseВҰ56353 you were all foreigners in EgyptВҰ56358 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*. I am your godВҰ56361 YahwehВҰ56360.
\p
\v 35 Don't allow injusticeВҰ56366 \add either\add* in \add вүҲjudging cases\add*, \add or by trading with rigged\add* weightsВҰ56369 andВҰ56370 measuresВҰ56368вҖ”\x + \xo 19:35-36: \xt Deu 25:13-16; Prv 20:10; Eze 45:10.\x*
\v 36 your scales and weightsВҰ56374 and measuring containers mustВҰ56381 be honest. I am your godВҰ56385 YahwehВҰ56384 who broughtВҰ56388 you all out of EgyptВҰ56391 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 37 You all mustВҰ56393 \add вүҲobey my instructionsВҰ56398 and decisionsВҰ56403\add* and \add вүҲstick to\add* them. I am YahwehВҰ56407.
\c 20
\s1 Penalties for disobedience
\rem /s1 Penalties for Violations of Holiness; Punishments for Sin; Penalties for Disobedience; Punishments for Disobedience
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ56411 told MoshehВҰ56414:
\p
\v 2 Tell the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ56419 people\add* that if any of them, or any foreigner staying in YisraelВҰ56420, gives any of their \add вүҲchildren\add* to MolekВҰ56436, thenВҰ56417 \add *that person\add* must \add вүҲdefinitely be executed\add*вҖ”the people must do it by throwing rocksВҰ56441 at them.
\v 3 \add Yes,\add* I myself will \add вүҲpersonally punish\add* that personВҰ56449 andВҰ56444 cut them off from the peopleВҰ56454 for giving their \add вүҲchild\add* to MolekВҰ56458 and so making my sanctuaryВҰ56463 вҖҳuncleanВҰ56460вҖҷ and profaningВҰ56464 my sacredВҰ56468 nameВҰ56467.
\v 4 If the peopleВҰ56473 of the land \add just\add* hides their eyesВҰ56477 from \add seeing\add* anyoneВҰ56483 offering their \add вүҲchild\add* to MolekВҰ56484 so theyВҰ56472 don'tВҰ56485 have to execute \add @that person\add*,
\v 5 thenВҰ56489 I'll \add also\add* remove that \add other\add* personВҰ56494 andВҰ56489 their clan. I'll cut them off from their peopleВҰ56509, along with anyone else who practises prostitution by prostituting themselves to MolekВҰ56507.
\p
\v 6 I'll \add вүҲtake action against\add* any person who turns to mediums or diviners to prostituteВҰ56520 themselves to them, andВҰ56511 I'll cut them off from their peopleВҰ56531.
\v 7 You mustВҰ56533 keepВҰ56533 yourselvesВҰ56533 \add вүҲseparate from those kinds of things to be\add* holy, becauseВҰ56536 I, YahwehВҰ56538, am your godВҰ56539.
\v 8 You all mustВҰ56541 \add вүҲfollow my instructionsВҰ56544\add* andВҰ56545 \add вүҲimplement\add* them. I am YahwehВҰ56548 who \add вүҲmakes you different from other people groups\add*.
\p
\v 9 Any person who cursesВҰ56556 their father or mother mustВҰ56556 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*вҖ”their bloodВҰ56568 will be on \add @their own head\add* for cursing their \add вүҲparents\add*.\x + \xo 20:9: \xt Exo 21:17; Mat 15:4; Mrk 7:10.\x*
\p
\v 10 Any man who commits adulteryВҰ56587 with another man's wife, maybe even his neighboursВҰ56583 wife, mustВҰ56573 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*вҖ”both the \add вүҲman andВҰ56571 the woman\add*.\x + \xo 20:10: \xt Exo 20:14; Lev 18:20; Deu 5:18.\x*
\v 11 Any manВҰ56590 who sleeps with any of his father's wives, has exposedВҰ56599 his father's nakednessВҰ56597. Both of them mustВҰ56592 be \add вүҲexecuted\add*вҖ”their bloodВҰ56604 is on \add @their own heads\add*.\x + \xo 20:11: \xt Lev 18:8; Deu 22:30; 27:20.\x*
\v 12 If a manВҰ56607 sleeps with his daughter-in-law, both of them mustВҰ56609 be executed. That's perversion andВҰ56607 so their bloodВҰ56618 is on \add @their own heads\add*.\x + \xo 20:12: \xt Lev 18:15.\x*
\v 13 If a man \add вүҲhas a sexual relationship\add* with another man, both of them have done something detestable andВҰ56621 both of them mustВҰ56623 be executedвҖ”their bloodВҰ56634 is on \add @their own heads\add*.\x + \xo 20:13: \xt Lev 18:22.\x*
\v 14 If a man takes both a motherВҰ56645 andВҰ56637 herВҰ56645 daughter as wives, thenВҰ56637 that's wicked. They mustВҰ56639 all be burnt \add вүҲto death\add* so that depravity won'tВҰ56652 \add take root\add* amongВҰ56656 you.
\p
\v 15 If a man \add tries to\add* \add вүҲhave sex with\add* an animal, that man must be executed andВҰ56658 the animal must \add also\add* be killed.\x + \xo 20:15-16: \xt Exo 22:19; Lev 18:23; Deu 27:21.\x*
\v 16 If a woman \add вүҲpresents herself sexually\add* to any animal, you mustВҰ56672 \add вүҲexecute\add* the woman andВҰ56670 kill the animalвҖ”their bloodВҰ56689 is on \add @their own heads\add*.
\p
\v 17 If a manВҰ56692 \add ?вүҲsleeps with\add* his sister (whether on his father'sВҰ56701 or mother'sВҰ56705 side) and they see each other's nakedness, it's a disgrace and they must be cut off from theirВҰ56721 peopleВҰ56721вҖ”he's exposedВҰ56724 herВҰ56709 nakedness and he must bear his wickedness.\x + \xo 20:17: \xt Lev 18:9; Deu 27:22.\x*
\v 18 If a man \add вүҲsleeps\add* with a womanВҰ56734 who's menstruatingВҰ56735, he's exposedВҰ56745 her nakednessВҰ56739 andВҰ56728 uncoveredВҰ56736 the \add вүҲsource\add* of her bloodВҰ56749, \add so\add* they mustВҰ56731 both be cut off from among theirВҰ56753 peopleВҰ56753.\x + \xo 20:18: \xt Lev 18:19.\x*
\p
\v 19 You mustn't expose the nakednessВҰ56755 of your sister (whether on your father's side or mother'sВҰ56757 side) becauseВҰ56762 \add that's like\add* exposing your own \add вүҲbody\add*. They mustВҰ56759 bear theirВҰ56767 wickedness.\x + \xo 20:19-20: \xt Lev 18:12-14.\x*
\v 20 A manВҰ56770 who \add вүҲsleeps\add* with his aunt, he's exposedВҰ56778 his uncle'sВҰ56777 nakednessВҰ56776. They'll bear theirВҰ56779 wickedness \add by\add* dying childlessВҰ56781.
\v 21 If a man \add ?вүҲmarries\add* his brother's wife, it's \add вүҲindecent\add*. He's exposedВҰ56795 his nakednessВҰ56793 \add andВҰ56784\add* they'll be childlessВҰ56796.\x + \xo 20:21: \xt Lev 18:16.\x*
\p
\v 22 You all mustВҰ56799 \add вүҲobey my instructionsВҰ56804 and decisionsВҰ56809\add* and \add вүҲstick to\add* them, and thenВҰ56799 the land that I'm aboutВҰ56819 to take you into, won'tВҰ56812 vomitВҰ56814 you all out.
\v 23 Don'tВҰ56825 follow the \add вүҲcustoms\add* of the \add #peoples\add* thatВҰ56829 I'll drive out ahead of you all, becauseВҰ56834 theyВҰ56840 do all of \add @the above\add* things, andВҰ56841 I detest them
\v 24 and I'veВҰ56844 told you all that you yourselves will inherit theirВҰ56850 landвҖ”I'llВҰ56852 giveВҰ56852 it to you \add вүҲto take possession of\add*. It's a land flowingВҰ56857 with milkВҰ56858 and honeyВҰ56859. I am your godВҰ56862 YahwehВҰ56861 who separatesВҰ56865 you all from the \add other\add* peopleВҰ56869 \add groups\add*.
\v 25 You all mustВҰ56871 \add вүҲdistinguish\add* between вҖҳcleanвҖҷ and вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ animals and birds. Don'tВҰ56882 make yourselves detestableВҰ56884 \add to me\add* with any animal or bird or crawling creature whichВҰ56894 I'veВҰ56896 distinguished for you all as вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ.
\v 26 You all mustВҰ56900 be вҖҳholyвҖҷ to me, becauseВҰ56903 I YahwehВҰ56906 am holy, andВҰ56907 I'veВҰ56907 set you all apart from the other \add вүҲpeopleВҰ56911 groups\add* to be mine.
\p
\v 27 Any man or womanВҰ56918 who's a medium or diviner must be executedвҖ”the peopleВҰ56929 must do it by throwing rocksВҰ56929 at them.
\c 21
\s1 Stricter instructions for priests
\rem /s1 The Holiness of the Priests; Instructions for the Priests; Rules for Priests; The Holiness of Priests
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ56936 told MoshehВҰ56939:
\p Tell Aharon's descendants the priestsВҰ56943 that they mustВҰ56946 not defile themselves amongВҰ56952 the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*, by touching anything that's not livingВҰ56948
\v 2 apart from the body of a close relativeВҰ56957 like a \add вүҲparent, child,\add* brotherВҰ56964
\v 3 or \add вүҲunmarried\add* sisterВҰ56966вҖ”the priest can become вҖҳuncleanВҰ56976вҖҷ by means of one of them.
\v 4 He mustВҰ56979 not make himself вҖҳuncleanВҰ56979вҖҷ \add if it's the death of\add* \add ?вүҲa relative only by marriage\add*.
\v 5 They mustВҰ56986 not shaveВҰ56993 their heads or trim the edges of their beardsВҰ56991 or cut their bodies \add in grief\add*.\x + \xo 21:5: \xt Lev 19:27-28; Deu 14:1.\x*
\p
\v 6 \add @ The priests\add* must stay separate for their GodВҰ57001 and they must not \add вүҲtarnish his reputationВҰ57004\add* becauseВҰ57006 they presentВҰ57014 the gifts to YahwehВҰ57010вҖ”their god's \add вүҲfood\add*
\v 7 They mustn't \add ?вүҲmarry\add* a woman who was a prostituteВҰ57019 or who has defiled herself \add some other way\add* or who is divorcedВҰ57024 from herВҰ57025 husbandВҰ57025, becauseВҰ57028 they're separated for their godВҰ57032.
\v 8 You must \add вүҲtreat\add* himВҰ57034 as \add вүҲset apart\add* because he's the one presentingВҰ57042 your god's \add вүҲfood\add*. He must be вҖҳholyвҖҷ for you, because I, YahwehВҰ57050, am holy andВҰ57034 I set you all apart as вҖҳholyвҖҷ.
\v 9 If a priest'sВҰ57055 daughterВҰ57053 prostitutedВҰ57058 herselfВҰ57057, she would be profaningВҰ57057 herВҰ57061 fatherВҰ57061 \add so\add* mustВҰ57057 be burntВҰ57065 \add to death\add*.
\p
\v 10 The priestВҰ57068 who is chief of all his brothersВҰ57070 and who had the anointingВҰ57079 oil pouredВҰ57073 over his head, and \add вүҲwho has the responsibility of\add* wearing the \add special\add* clothing, must not \add вүҲwear his hair loose\add*, and he must not tear his clothesВҰ57087 \add in grief\add*.
\v 11 He mustn't approach \em any\em* deadВҰ57101 bodyвҖ”not \add even\add* his \add own\add* \add вүҲparents\add*вҖ”he mustn't make himselfВҰ57107 вҖҳuncleanВҰ57107вҖҷ.
\v 12 \add Even for a death,\add* he mustn't leave \add his duties in\add* the sanctuary, andВҰ57109 he mustn't profaneВҰ57115 the sanctuary of his god, becauseВҰ57119 he's been consecratedВҰ57120 with the anointingВҰ57122 oil. I am YahwehВҰ57126.
\v 13 He can \add only\add* \add вүҲmarry\add* a virginВҰ57130вҖ”
\v 14 he mustn't take a widowВҰ57133 or a divorcedВҰ57134 woman, or a defiled prostituteВҰ57136. He can only \add вүҲmarry\add* an unmarried, \add вүҲIsraeli\add* girl,
\v 15 thenВҰ57150 heВҰ57152 won'tВҰ57150 profaneВҰ57152 his offspring amongВҰ57154 his relatives, becauseВҰ57155 IВҰ57156 am YahwehВҰ57157 who sets himВҰ57158 apartВҰ57158 as вҖҳholyвҖҷ.
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehВҰ57162 told MoshehВҰ57165,
\p
\v 17 Tell Aharon that \add вүҲnone of his descendants\add* who have a \add вүҲdeformity\add* should ever approach to presentВҰ57182 the food for his godВҰ57184.
\v 18 \add вүҲYes,\add* no man who has a \add вүҲdeformity\add* mustВҰ57195 approach \add to offer a sacrifice\add*, i.e., no one who's blindВҰ57197, lame, mutilated, or \add вүҲwith a swelling\add*,
\v 19 or with a broken footВҰ57212 or handВҰ57215,
\v 20 or a hunchbackВҰ57219 or dwarf, or with an eyeВҰ57225 defectВҰ57224, with a scab or rash, or anyone with a crushedВҰ57231 testicleВҰ57232.
\v 21 Any \add вүҲdescendant of\add* Aharon the priestВҰ57243 with a blemish mustn't approach to preset a gift to YahwehВҰ57250вҖ”no that person mustn't approach to present god's food.
\v 22 However, they can eatВҰ57267 those gifts for GodВҰ57261, includingВҰ57264 the sacred andВҰ57264 very sacred \add вүҲportions\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲDespite that,\add* they mustn't enter past the curtainВҰ57272 or approach the altarВҰ57277 if they have a defect on \add вүҲtheirВҰ57292 body\add*. They mustn't profaneВҰ57285 my sanctuaryВҰ57288 becauseВҰ57280 I am YahwehВҰ57291 who sets them apartВҰ57292 as вҖҳholyвҖҷ.
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ57294\add* MoshehВҰ57295 told \add all\add* that to Aharon and his sonsВҰ57301, and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ57306\add*.
\c 22
\s1 Offerings to Yahweh become sacred
\rem /s1 The Use of Holy Offerings; The Holiness of the Offerings
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ57311 told MoshehВҰ57314:
\p
\v 2 Tell Aharon and his sonsВҰ57323 thatВҰ57335 they mustВҰ57330 \add вүҲcarefully honour\add* the holy thingsВҰ57325 \add offered\add* by the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ57326\add* peopleВҰ57326, and they mustn't profaneВҰ57330 my holy \add вүҲreputationВҰ57333\add*. I am YahwehВҰ57340.
\v 3 Tell them that \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ57344, any \add вүҲof your descendants\add* who is вҖҳuncleanВҰ57364вҖҷ and approaches thingsВҰ57357 that have become holy because the peopleВҰ57360 have consecrated them to Yahweh, \add @that person\add* will be cut off from me. I am Yahweh.
\p
\v 4 Any man who's a descendant of Aharon, if he has a skin diseaseВҰ57378 or a dischargeВҰ57380, he mustn't eat any of the sacred \add >food\add* untilВҰ57384 he's вҖҳcleanвҖҷ \add again\add*. \add вүҲThe same applies if\add* he's touchedВҰ57387 any вҖҳuncleanВҰ57390вҖҷ corpseВҰ57392, anyoneВҰ57394 who's had a seminal emission,
\v 5 anyone who's touched any swarmingВҰ57410 \add >creature\add* that makes him вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ or touches \add another\add* person who makes him вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ (whatever that person's uncleanness is).
\v 6 \add No,\add* the man who's touchedВҰ57426 any of those will be вҖҳuncleanВҰ57429вҖҷ until the eveningВҰ57432 and he mustn't eatВҰ57434 any of the sacredВҰ57437 \add >food\add* until he's washedВҰ57441 his bodyВҰ57442 with waterВҰ57443.
\v 7 WhenВҰ57445 the sunВҰ57446 sets, thenВҰ57445 he'll be вҖҳcleanВҰ57447вҖҷ andВҰ57445 will be able to eatВҰ57449 any of those sacredВҰ57452 \add >offerings\add* becauseВҰ57453 that's his food.
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ57458\add* heВҰ57460 mustВҰ57460 \add вүҲnever\add* eatВҰ57460 \add вүҲan animal found dead\add* or torn \add by wild animals\add* andВҰ57458 becomeВҰ57461 вҖҳuncleanВҰ57461вҖҷ \add вүҲin that way\add*. IВҰ57464 am YahwehВҰ57465.
\p
\v 9 \add @The priests\add* mustВҰ57467 \add вүҲfollow my instructions\add* so they won'tВҰ57471 have to bear theirВҰ57482 own disobedience andВҰ57467 dieВҰ57476 from it becauseВҰ57478 they profanedВҰ57479 them. IВҰ57480 am YahwehВҰ57481 who makes them sacredВҰ57482.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲHowever,\add* no strangerВҰ57486 may eat the sacredВҰ57490 \add >food\add*, \add e.g.,\add* someone staying with the priestВҰ57492, or his hiredВҰ57493 servant.
\v 11 If the priest had purchased \add вүҲthe person\add* with \add вүҲcashВҰ57505\add*, thenВҰ57499 \add @that person\add* can eat it, plusВҰ57509 anyoneВҰ57509 that was born into \add @the priest's\add* \add вүҲhouseholdВҰ57510\add*.
\v 12 A priest's daughterВҰ57515 who \add вүҲis married by\add* \add вүҲsomeone who's not a priest\add* can \add no longer\add* eatВҰ57526 those sacredВҰ57524 \add вүҲofferings\add*.
\v 13 \add However, in the future\add* if she became a widowВҰ57533 or was divorcedВҰ57534 without having had children, andВҰ57528 if she has returnedВҰ57538 to her father's houseВҰ57541 like when she was young, thenВҰ57528 she can eat \add вүҲthe same food as her father\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ57528 no\add* strangerВҰ57549 may eat it.
\p
\v 14 If someoneВҰ57556 accidentally eats something that's sacredВҰ57560, then they mustВҰ57559 \add вүҲpay back the full value plusВҰ57556 20%\add* to the priestВҰ57566.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ57571\add* \add in summary\add*, \add @the priests\add* mustВҰ57572 not profaneВҰ57572 the sacredВҰ57575 thingsВҰ57575 \add contributed by\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ57576\add* andВҰ57571 whichВҰ57579 they've \add вүҲoffered\add* to YahwehВҰ57582
\v 16 or else they'll causeВҰ57584 themselves to bear the guiltВҰ57587 from theirВҰ57591 disobedience concerning eating sacred \add >food\add*, becauseВҰ57592 IВҰ57593 am YahwehВҰ57594 who has separated them to be sacred.
\rem /s1 Worthy and Unworthy Offerings; Unacceptable Sacrifices; Acceptable Offerings
\p
\v 17 The YahwehВҰ57599 told MoshehВҰ57602:
\p
\v 18 Tell Aharon and his sons, and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ57615\add* thatВҰ57636 any \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ57615\add* or outsider \add вүҲresiding\add* in YisraelВҰ57616, when they present their burntВҰ57640 offering to YahwehВҰ57639, whether it's for a vow or for a freewillВҰ57635 offering,
\v 19 to be acceptedВҰ57642 it mustВҰ57643 be a maleВҰ57644 with noВҰ57643 defectsВҰ57643, whether it's a cow, or a sheep, or a goat.
\v 20 Anything that has a defect mustВҰ57655 \em not\em* be presentedВҰ57655 becauseВҰ57656 it wouldn't be acceptableВҰ57659 on your behalf.\x + \xo 22:20: \xt Deu 17:1.\x*
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ57663 someoneВҰ57663\add* presentsВҰ57666 a sacrificeВҰ57667 of peaceВҰ57669 offeringsВҰ57669 to YahwehВҰ57670 to fulfillВҰ57671 a vow or as a freewillВҰ57675 offeringВҰ57675 from the herd or the flockВҰ57678, to be acceptedВҰ57681 it mustВҰ57666 \add вүҲflawless with noВҰ57679 defectsВҰ57679\add*вҖ”
\v 22 not blind or with broken \add bones\add*, and not maimed or with an oozing sore or rash or scab. You all mustn't presentВҰ57705 \add вүҲanything like that\add* to Yahweh, and mustВҰ57705 not \add even\add* offeringВҰ57708 \add вүҲany part of them\add* to Yahweh on the altarВҰ57715.
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if a cowВҰ57718 or a sheepВҰ57719 has something enlargedВҰ57720 or something stuntedВҰ57721, it can be offered as a freewillВҰ57722 offeringВҰ57722, butВҰ57718 it wouldn't be acceptedВҰ57727 for a vow,
\v 24 andВҰ57729 you all mustВҰ57734 never presentВҰ57734 to YahwehВҰ57735 any animal that's bruised or torn or cut.\f + \fr 22:24 \ft The Septuagint mentions вҖҳtesticlesвҖҷ here, which also correlates with 21:20.\f* You mustn't doВҰ57738 that in yourВҰ57736 \add вүҲcountry\add*.
\p
\v 25 You all mustn't presentВҰ57745 any of those \add animalsВҰ57752 raised\add* by foreignersВҰ57743 to your godВҰ57749 becauseВҰ57753 they've been ruined andВҰ57740 are defective,\f + \fr 22:25 \ft Could this be related to the fact that they'd been neutered (as per v24 in the Septuagint)???\f* \add вүҲso\add* they won'tВҰ57744 be acceptedВҰ57759 for you.
\p
\v 26 Then YahwehВҰ57764 told MoshehВҰ57767:
\p
\v 27 A \add newborn\add* calf or lamb or goatВҰ57776 mustВҰ57778 \add вүҲremain with\add* its motherВҰ57783 for sevenВҰ57780 daysВҰ57781вҖ”it can be offeredВҰ57789 as a sacrifice to YahwehВҰ57790 from the eighthВҰ57785 dayВҰ57784 onwardsВҰ57786,
\v 28 \add вүҲbutВҰ57792\add* you mustn't slaughter a cowВҰ57792 or a sheepВҰ57795 andВҰ57797 it's \add вүҲoffspring\add* on \add вүҲthe same\add* dayВҰ57802.
\v 29 WhenВҰ57805 you \add вүҲoffer\add* a thanksgivingВҰ57810 sacrifice to YahwehВҰ57811, it mustВҰ57807 be \add вүҲacceptableВҰ57812 as a sacrifice\add*
\v 30 and you can eat it that same dayВҰ57815 \add but\add* \add вүҲno part\add* of it should be left untilВҰ57822 the morningВҰ57824. IВҰ57825 am YahwehВҰ57826.
\p
\v 31 You all mustВҰ57828 \add вүҲrecord my instructions andВҰ57830 follow\add* them. I am YahwehВҰ57833.
\v 32 You mustn't profaneВҰ57836 the \add вүҲreputationВҰ57839\add* of my holiness, andВҰ57841 I will demonstrate my holiness among the IsraeliВҰ57843 peopleВҰ57843. I am YahwehВҰ57846 who separates you all to be sacredВҰ57840вҖ”
\v 33 who broughtВҰ57849 you all out of EgyptВҰ57852 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* to be your godВҰ57855. I am YahwehВҰ57857.
\c 23
\s1 The scheduled festivals
\rem /s1 The Appointed Festivals; Appointed Festivals; The Religious Festivals
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ57861 told MoshehВҰ57864:
\p
\v 2 TellВҰ57871 the \add IsraelisВҰ57870\add* thatВҰ57876 theyВҰ57883 mustВҰ57872 proclaimВҰ57878 Yahweh'sВҰ57875 scheduled festivals as sacredВҰ57881 assemblies \add вүҲat the given times\add*.
\s2 The rest day
\rem /s1 The Sabbath; The Sabbath, Passover, and Unleavened Bread
\p
\v 3 Work for six daysВҰ57887, then the seventhВҰ57891 is a rest day \add for\add* a sacredВҰ57896 assemblyВҰ57894вҖ”don'tВҰ57900 work on that dayвҖ”\add вүҲwherever you live\add* it's a rest day \add вүҲto honour\add* YahwehВҰ57904.\x + \xo 23:3: \xt Exo 20:8-10; 23:12; 31:15; 34:21; 35:2; Deu 5:12-14.\x*
\rem /s1 The Passover and Unleavened Bread
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲTheВҰ57911 following\add* are the scheduled festivals thatВҰ57914 you mustВҰ57916 proclaimВҰ57916 at the appointed times as sacredВҰ57913 assemblies:
\s2 Passover and flat bread festivals
\rem /s1 Passover and Unleavened Bread; Passover and the Festival of Unleavened Bread
\r (Num. 28:16-25)
\p
\v 5 The 14th of the firstВҰ57921 month \add (Nisan = March/April) each year\add* \add вүҲat twilight\add* is the \add start of the celebration to honour\add* YahwehВҰ57928 with the вҖҳpassoverВҰ57927вҖҷ.\x + \xo 23:5: \xt Exo 12:1-13; Deu 16:1-2.\x*
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ57930 the \add next dayВҰ57932\add* (the 15th) is \add the start of\add* the festivalВҰ57935 of flat bread \add to honour\add* YahwehВҰ57937вҖ”you all mustВҰ57930 eatВҰ57941 bread made without any rising agent for sevenВҰ57938 daysВҰ57939.\x + \xo 23:6-8: \xt Exo 12:14-20; 23:15; 34:18; Deu 16:3-8.\x*
\v 7 On \add &that\add* firstВҰ57944 day you'll hold a sacredВҰ57947 assemblyВҰ57945вҖ”no \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done \add that day\add*.
\v 8 For seven daysВҰ57961 you all mustВҰ57957 presentВҰ57957 offeringsВҰ57958 to YahwehВҰ57959, thenВҰ57957 the seventh day is \add another\add* sacredВҰ57966 assemblyВҰ57964вҖ”\add again\add* no \add вүҲregular\add* work may be done \add that day\add*.
\s1 The firstfruits festival
\rem /s1 Firstfruits; The Offering of First Fruits; The Festival of Firstfruits
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ57976 told MoshehВҰ57979:
\p
\v 10 Tell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ57985\add* that when you enter the land that I'm giving you all, and you harvest \add вүҲyour grain crops\add*, then you all mustВҰ57987 bringВҰ58003 a sheafВҰ58006 of the firstВҰ58007 \add part\add* of your harvest to a priestВҰ58011,
\v 11 andВҰ58013 he will wave the sheafВҰ58016 \add вүҲin frontВҰ58017\add* of YahwehВҰ58018 \add вүҲto be acceptedВҰ58019 for you\add*. That mustВҰ58013 be done the day after the rest day.
\v 12 \add вүҲThat same\add* dayВҰ58026, youВҰ58027 all mustВҰ58025 offer a year-old lambВҰ58031 \add вүҲwith noВҰ58032 defectsВҰ58032\add* to YahwehВҰ58037 as a burntВҰ58036 offeringВҰ58036,
\v 13 and the \add associated\add* grainВҰ58039 offering will be two kilograms of fine wheat flourВҰ58042 mixedВҰ58043 with \add olive\add* oil. That will be a gift to YahwehВҰ58046 with a pleasingВҰ58048 aromaВҰ58047, and the \add associated\add* drinkВҰ58049 offering will be a litre of wine.
\v 14 You all may not eatВҰ58059 any breadВҰ58055, or roastedВҰ58056 or fresh grainВҰ58056, on that dayВҰ58063, until \add after\add* you've taken the offering to your godВҰ58070. That is a \add вүҲrule that will continue throughout\add* your generationsВҰ58073 \add вүҲno matter where\add* you live.
\s1 The fiftieth day festival
\rem /s1 Feast of Weeks; The Festival of Weeks; The Festival of Harvest; The Harvest Festival
\r (Num. 28:26-31)
\p
\v 15 Then countВҰ58078 seven rest days from the day after you broughtВҰ58083 the \add вүҲbundle of grain\add* as a wave offeringвҖ”seven full weeks.\x + \xo 23:15-21: \xt Exo 23:16; 34:22; Deu 16:9-12.\x*
\v 16 Then that next dayВҰ58094 \add will make\add* fiftyВҰ58098 days, andВҰ58100 then you all mustВҰ58097 presentВҰ58100 a new grainВҰ58101 offeringВҰ58101 to YahwehВҰ58103.
\v 17 From your \add вүҲhomes\add*, \add @each family\add* mustВҰ58106 bringВҰ58106 two loaves of breadВҰ58108 bakedВҰ58116 with a rising agent, as a firstfruitsВҰ58117 \add offering\add* to YahwehВҰ58118.
\v 18 Along with the breadВҰ58123, you all mustВҰ58120 presentВҰ58120 sevenВҰ58124 \add вүҲyear-old\add* male lambsВҰ58125 \add вүҲwithoutВҰ58126 defectsВҰ58126\add*, one \add вүҲyoungВҰ58130\add* bullВҰ58129, and two rams. They will be a burntВҰ58137 offering to Yahweh, with their \add associated\add* grainВҰ58139 and drinkВҰ58140 offeringsВҰ58140вҖ”a gift with a pleasingВҰ58144 aromaВҰ58142 for Yahweh.
\v 19 You all mustВҰ58147 \add also\add* offer a male goatВҰ58148 as a sin offering andВҰ58147 two \add вүҲone-year-old\add* male lambsВҰ58154 as a peaceВҰ58158 offering.
\v 20 The priest mustВҰ58160 raise them along with the firstfruitsВҰ58166 breadВҰ58165 as a wave offering \add вүҲin frontВҰ58168\add* of Yahweh, with the two lambsВҰ58173. They will become sacredВҰ58174 to Yahweh, \add butВҰ58160\add* for the priest \add to eat\add*.
\v 21 You all mustВҰ58179 proclaimВҰ58179 a sacredВҰ58186 assemblyВҰ58184 that same dayВҰ58182вҖ”you mustn't doВҰ58194 any \add вүҲregularВҰ58195\add* workВҰ58191. That is a \add вүҲpermanentВҰ58196\add* rule that will continue \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ58200 \add вүҲno matter where you live\add*.
\p
\v 22 WhenВҰ58202 you all harvest your \add вүҲcrops\add*, don't \add вүҲreap\add* to the very edge of your fieldВҰ58211 and don't \add вүҲpick up stalks that drop on the ground\add*вҖ”they mustВҰ58209 be left for the poor and for foreigners \add without land\add*. IВҰ58221 am your godВҰ58223, YahwehВҰ58222.\x + \xo 23:22: \xt Lev 19:9-10; Deu 24:19-22.\x*
\s1 The new year festival
\rem /s1 The Festival of Trumpets; Feast of Trumpets; The New Year Festival
\r (Num. 29:1-6)
\p
\v 23 Then YahwehВҰ58227 told MoshehВҰ58230,
\v 24 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58236\add* that on the 1st of the seventhВҰ58240 month \add (Tishrei = September/October) each year\add*, you mustВҰ58243 have a \add вүҲpublic holiday\add* with a loudВҰ58247 \add trumpet\add* blastВҰ58247 announcing the sacredВҰ58250 assemblyВҰ58248.
\v 25 You all must not doВҰ58257 any \add вүҲregular\add* workВҰ58254 on that day, andВҰ58258 you all must presentВҰ58258 a fire-offering to YahwehВҰ58260.вҖқ
\s1 The day of atonement
\rem /s1 The Day of Atonement
\r (Num. 29:7-11)
\p
\v 26 Then YahwehВҰ58264 told MoshehВҰ58267,\x + \xo 23:26-32: \xt Lev 16:29-34.\x*
\v 27 вҖңThe 10th of that seventhВҰ58273 monthВҰ58272 is a dayВҰ58275 \add вүҲfor making things right\add* \add with Yahweh\add*. You all \add вүҲmustВҰ58281 hold a sacredВҰ58280 assemblyВҰ58278\add* and humble \add вүҲyourselves\add* and presentВҰ58287 a fire-offering to Yahweh.
\v 28 You mustn't do any work on that particular day becauseВҰ58299 it's the day for \add вүҲmaking yourselvesВҰ58304 right\add* in frontВҰ58305 of your god YahwehВҰ58306,
\v 29 because anyone who doesn't humbleВҰ58316 themself on that dayВҰ58318 will be cut off from their people.
\v 30 вҮ”\add In additionВҰ58323,\add* IВҰ58334 will destroyВҰ58334 anyone who works on that dayВҰ58332вҖ”removing them from their peopleВҰ58340.
\v 31 You all mustВҰ58346 not doВҰ58346 any workВҰ58344. That's a permanentВҰ58348 rule that will continue \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ58349 \add вүҲno matter where you live\add*вҖ”
\v 32 it's a \add вүҲvery strict\add* rest dayВҰ58361 andВҰ58357 you all mustВҰ58357 humble yourselves from the evening of the 9th untilВҰ58365 the next evening when \add *it\add* will finish.
\s1 The celebration in shelters
\rem /s1 The Festival of Shelters; The Festival of Booths; Feast of Tabernacles
\r (Num. 29:12-40)
\p
\v 33 Then YahwehВҰ58373 told MoshehВҰ58376:\x + \xo 23:33-36: \xt Deu 16:13-15.\x*
\p
\v 34 Tell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58382\add* that \add starting\add* on the 15th of the seventhВҰ58389 monthВҰ58388 \add (of TishreiвҖ”around September/October)\add*, there will be a celebration in shelters to \add honour\add* YahwehВҰ58395.
\v 35 The firstВҰ58398 dayВҰ58397 will be a sacredВҰ58401 assemblyВҰ58399вҖ”you all mustn't doВҰ58407 any \add вүҲregular\add* workВҰ58404.
\v 36 You all mustВҰ58411 present a gift to Yahweh \add each day\add* for seven daysВҰ58410, and then on the eighthВҰ58415 day, there'll be \add another\add* sacredВҰ58418 assemblyВҰ58424 and you'll all present a gift to Yahweh. It'll be \add a day\add* to assembleвҖ”you all mustn't do any \add вүҲregular\add* work \add that day\add*.
\p
\v 37 \add @The above\add* are the \add вүҲscheduled dates\add* to proclaimВҰ58438 sacredВҰ58441 assemblies to presentВҰ58442 a gift to YahwehВҰ58435: burntВҰ58445 offerings and grainВҰ58446 offerings, sacrificesВҰ58447 and drinkВҰ58448 offerings, on the \add вүҲappropriate\add* days,
\v 38 as well as Yahweh'sВҰ58456 rest days, and alongside all your \add regular\add* giftsВҰ58458 and vows and freewillВҰ58466 offeringsВҰ58466 thatВҰ58467 you all giveВҰ58468 to Yahweh.
\p
\v 39 \add вүҲSo indeed,\add* on the 15th of the seventh monthВҰ58475 when you have \add вүҲharvested your crops\add*, you'll all celebrateВҰ58482 Yahweh'sВҰ58487 festival for seven days with the firstВҰ58491 and eighthВҰ58494 days being rest days.
\v 40 On that firstВҰ58500 day, you'll all bring the fruitВҰ58501 from your treesВҰ58505, along with palm branches, leafyВҰ58509 branches, and willow branches from \add beside\add* the \add #creeks\add*, and you'll all \add вүҲhappily celebrate\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ58514\add* of your god YahwehВҰ58515 for sevenВҰ58517 days.
\v 41 Do that for sevenВҰ58524 daysВҰ58525 each yearВҰ58526 as a festival to \add honour\add* YahwehВҰ58523. you all mustВҰ58520 celebrate it in the seventh monthВҰ58530. That's a permanentВҰ58528 rule that will continue \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ58529.
\v 42 You all mustВҰ58536 live in shelters for sevenВҰ58537 daysВҰ58538вҖ”all you native-born \add вүҲIsraelis\add*,
\v 43 so that the \add future\add* generationsВҰ58548 will knowВҰ58547 that I made \add вүҲtheir ancestors\add* live in shelters when I broughtВҰ58556 them out of EgyptВҰ58559 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*. I am your godВҰ58562 YahwehВҰ58561.
\p
\v 44 \add вүҲSoВҰ58564\add* MoshehВҰ58565 \add вүҲpassed\add* all those \add вүҲscheduled dates\add* from YahwehВҰ58569, on to the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58572\add*.
\c 24
\s1 Oil for the lamps
\rem /s1 Taking Care of the Lamps; Pure Oil and Holy Bread; The Lamp; Oil and Bread Set Before the Lord
\r (Exo. 27:20-21)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ58577 told MoshehВҰ58580:
\p
\v 2 OrderВҰ58587 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58586\add* to bringВҰ58588 youВҰ58589 pressedВҰ58593 oliveВҰ58591 oilВҰ58590 that's pure, to \add вүҲsupply\add* \add #lamps\add* \add to give\add* continualВҰ58597 lightВҰ58594.
\v 3 \add The high priest\add* (Aharon) \add вүҲmustВҰ58604 take care of\add* \add #them\add* from eveningВҰ58607 untilВҰ58608 the morningВҰ58610 \add to burn\add* continually \add вүҲin frontВҰ58611\add* of YahwehВҰ58612. That's a permanentВҰ58615 requirement that will continue \add вүҲthroughout\add* the generationsВҰ58616.
\v 4 He will arrangeВҰ58621 the lamps continuallyВҰ58627 on the lampstand \add вүҲin frontВҰ58625\add* of YahwehВҰ58626.
\s1 The bread offered there to God
\rem /s1 The Bread for the Tabernacle; The Bread Offered to God
\p
\v 5 \add Each week\add* you mustВҰ58630 takeВҰ58630 fine wheat flour and bake twelve loaves of bread, using two kilograms of flour for each loaf.\x + \xo 24:5-6: \xt Exo 25:30.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲArrange\add* the loaves into twoВҰ58645 rows of sixВҰ58647 loaves on the pure tableВҰ58650 \add вүҲin frontВҰ58652\add* of YahwehВҰ58653,
\v 7 andВҰ58661 put pure frankincenseВҰ58659 \add вүҲwith\add* each row to be a memorialВҰ58663 portion for the breadВҰ58662 as a gift to YahwehВҰ58665.
\v 8 \add EveryВҰ58678\add* rest day \add вүҲit will be placed\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ58672\add* of YahwehВҰ58673 \add representing\add* the \add вүҲongoing\add* agreementВҰ58679 with the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58676\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲAfterwards,\add* it will belongВҰ58682 to Aharon and his sonsВҰ58684, and they mustВҰ58682 eatВҰ58685 it in a sacred area becauseВҰ58688 it's a \add вүҲvery\add* sacred part of the gifts for YahwehВҰ58694. That's a permanentВҰ58697 rule.\x + \xo 24:9: \xt Mat 12:4; Mrk 2:26; Luk 6:4.\x*
\s1 Execution for cursing Yahweh
\rem /s1 An Example of Just and Fair Punishment; An Example of Just Punishment; A Blasphemer Stoned; Blasphemy and Its Punishment
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲOnce\add* there was an Israeli womanВҰ58703 and an Egyptian man \add вүҲwho had\add* a son who \add вүҲlived among the IsraelisВҰ58711\add*, and he \add вүҲgot into a fight\add* with an Israeli man.
\v 11 ThenВҰ58720 that son of the IsraeliВҰ58724 womanВҰ58723 slanderedВҰ58720 \add &Yahweh's\add* name and cursedВҰ58728, and \add so\add* the peopleВҰ58729 took him to MoshehВҰ58733. (The motherВҰ58735 was ShelomitВҰ58736, a daughterВҰ58737 of DibriВҰ58739 from the DanВҰ58742 tribeВҰ58740.)
\v 12 They \add вүҲheld\add* himВҰ58744 in custodyВҰ58745 \add вүҲwhile waiting for Yahweh'sВҰ58751 decision\add*.
\p
\v 13 Then YahwehВҰ58755 told MoshehВҰ58758:
\p
\v 14 Take \add вүҲthat man\add* who cursedВҰ58764 outsideВҰ58767 the campВҰ58768, and \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ58764 who heardВҰ58772 him\add* must place theirВҰ58775 handsВҰ58775 on his headВҰ58778, and then \add вүҲall the people must execute him by throwing rocksВҰ58779 at\add* him.
\v 15 ThenВҰ58785 tell the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ58787\add* that anyone who cursesВҰ58795 GodВҰ58796 mustВҰ58789 bear \add the results of\add* their own wickedness.
\v 16 AnyoneВҰ58800 who slanders Yahweh'sВҰ58803 \add вүҲreputationВҰ58801\add* must be executed. The \add gathered assembly\add* must \add вүҲthrow rocksВҰ58806 at\add* them. \add It makes no difference\add* whether they're a \add вүҲforeigner staying there\add*, or a native-born \add Israeli\add*.
\p
\v 17 Anyone who \add вүҲmurders\add* another person, mustВҰ58822 \add вүҲdefinitely be executed\add*.\x + \xo 24:17: \xt Exo 21:12.\x*
\v 18 AnyoneВҰ58830 who kills \add someone else's\add* animal, mustВҰ58834 \add вүҲmake restitution with the same kind of animal\add*.
\p
\v 19 Anyone who \add вүҲinjures\add* a fellowВҰ58844 citizenВҰ58844, mustВҰ58842 have the same done to themвҖ”
\v 20 fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for toothвҖ”\add вүҲhowever they injured the other personВҰ58863, that's what mustВҰ58861 be done to them\add*.\x + \xo 24:20: \xt Exo 21:23-25; Deu 19:21; Mat 5:38.\x*
\v 21 AnyoneВҰ58868 who kills \add someone else's\add* animalВҰ58869 must \add вүҲreplace\add* itВҰ58870, \add вүҲbutВҰ58868\add* anyoneВҰ58868 who kills \add another\add* personВҰ58872 must be executed.
\v 22 There's \add only\add* one \add set of\add* regulations for \add both\add* the foreigner and the native-born \add citizen\add* becauseВҰ58882 I am your godВҰ58885 YahwehВҰ58884.\x + \xo 24:22: \xt Num 15:16.\x*
\p
\v 23 Mosheh \add вүҲpassed\add* \add all that\add* onto the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ58891\add*, andВҰ58887 they took the \add вүҲman who had cursedВҰ58896\add* \add Yahweh\add* outsideВҰ58899 the campВҰ58900 \add вүҲwhere\add* they \add вүҲexecuted him with rocks\add*. The IsraelisВҰ58891 didВҰ58907 exactly what Yahweh had commandedВҰ58909 \add them\add* via Mosheh.
\c 25
\s1 The rest year
\rem /s1 The Sabbatical Year; The Seventh Year; The Sabbath Year
\r (Deu. 15:1-11)
\p
\v 1 Then on MtВҰ58921. SinaiВҰ58922, YahwehВҰ58917 told MoshehВҰ58920:\x + \xo 25:1-7: \xt Exo 23:10-11.\x*
\p
\v 2 Tell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ58928\add* that when you all enter the land that I'm giving you, the land mustВҰ58930 \add observe\add* a \add вүҲrest year\add* for YahwehВҰ58944.
\v 3 вҮ”You can \add вүҲplant your crops\add*, pruneВҰ58952 your \add вүҲgrapevines\add*, and \add вүҲharvest\add* \add all\add* its produceВҰ58957 for six years,
\v 4 butВҰ58959 during the seventhВҰ58960 yearВҰ58959, you mustВҰ58963 \add вүҲallow the land to rest\add* \add to honour\add* YahwehВҰ58966. You mustn't \add вүҲplant any crops or pruneВҰ58972 any grapevines\add*.
\v 5 Don'tВҰ58977 \add systematically\add* harvest the self-sown \add вүҲcrops\add* or the grapes from the untrimmedВҰ58982 vines. It mustВҰ58978 be a rest year for the land.
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever, during\add* the rest year, the land \add вүҲwill provide\add* food for you and your servants, and for your hiredВҰ58998 workers and the foreigners who are living among you,
\v 7 as well as your livestockВҰ59003 andВҰ59003 the \add wild\add* animalsВҰ59004 across the land. Any produceВҰ59010 from the land can be eaten.
\s1 The restoration celebration year
\rem /s1 The Year of Jubilee; The Year of Restoration
\p
\v 8 Count off seven rest years, so seven timesВҰ59022 seven which is forty-nine years,
\v 9 thenВҰ59033 \add after that\add*, soundВҰ59035 loudВҰ59035 horn blastsВҰ59035 on the 10th of the seventhВҰ59037 month \add вүҲto announce\add* throughoutВҰ59033 the land that it's the dayВҰ59040 for \add вүҲmaking things right with Yahweh\add*.
\v 10 ThenВҰ59048 you all mustВҰ59048 \add вүҲdeclare\add* \add &that\add* fiftieth year \add вүҲto be sacredВҰ59048\add*. It'll be a \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* \add year\add* when you announce freedom for all the inhabitantsВҰ59058 of the \add вүҲcountry\add*вҖ”everyoneВҰ59064 can be free to return to their families, andВҰ59048 \add all families can be free\add* to return to their \add вүҲoriginally inherited land\add*.
\v 11 That fiftieth year will be a \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* year. You all mustn't \add вүҲplant crops\add* and don'tВҰ59081 \add systematically\add* harvestВҰ59084 the self-sown \add вүҲcrops\add* or the grapesВҰ59089 from the untrimmedВҰ59092 vinesВҰ59092,
\v 12 because it's a \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* year. You all mustВҰ59098 \add treat it\add* as sacredВҰ59097 and \add just\add* eatВҰ59103 \add вүҲwhat you take\add* \add directly\add* from the countrysideВҰ59102.
\p
\v 13 In that \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* yearВҰ59108, you all should returnВҰ59111 to your \add вүҲinherited land\add*.
\v 14 \add In the other years\add* when you buy or sellВҰ59120 from your fellow citizens, you mustn't \add вүҲcheat\add* them
\v 15 \add because the value of the land\add* \add вүҲwill depend\add* on the number of years afterВҰ59136 the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* year, \add i.e., \add* you mustВҰ59138 take into account the number of years of produceВҰ59144вҖ”
\v 16 if there's many years \add to go\add*, the price will increaseВҰ59153, and \add вүҲif the next rest year is close\add*, the price will decrease becauseВҰ59160 you're sellingВҰ59164 the numberВҰ59161 of crops.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ59167\add* don'tВҰ59167 cheat eat otherвҖ”you mustВҰ59168 \add вүҲrespect andВҰ59167 obey\add* your god, becauseВҰ59175 IВҰ59176 am your god YahwehВҰ59177.
\rem /s1 The Problem of the Seventh Year
\p
\v 18 You all mustВҰ59180 \add вүҲfollow\add* all my instructionsВҰ59183 andВҰ59180 \add вүҲmaintain\add* my \add вүҲvalues\add*вҖ”keeping them \add вүҲso that\add* you'll be able to live securelyВҰ59194 on the land.
\v 19 The land will \add вүҲyield itsВҰ59198 crops\add* and you'll all \add вүҲhave plenty to eatВҰ59199\add*, and you'll be able to live \add *there\add* securelyВҰ59202.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ59205\add* if you all \add вүҲwonder\add* what you'll eatВҰ59209 in \add &that\add* seventhВҰ59213 yearВҰ59212 when you'll neither \add вүҲplant crops\add* or \add вүҲdo organised harvests\add*,
\v 21 \add вүҲwell\add* I'llВҰ59223 \add вүҲsend\add* my blessingВҰ59226 to you all in the sixthВҰ59229 yearВҰ59228, andВҰ59223 it'll produceВҰ59233 enough for threeВҰ59234 yearsВҰ59235
\v 22 \add вүҲso\add* you all can still eat that \add вүҲstored\add* food while you \add вүҲplant crops\add* in the eighthВҰ59240 year \add вүҲto feed you all through\add* the ninthВҰ59249 year.
\s1 Returning property to the clan
\rem /s1 Restoration of Property
\p
\v 23 The land can not be \add вүҲirrevocably\add* sold, becauseВҰ59261 itВҰ59259 belongs to me and you all are foreigners and temporary residentsВҰ59268 \add вүҲon my\add* \add land\add*.
\rem /s1 Redemption of Property
\v 24 \add вүҲso\add* for all the land \add вүҲthat you take possessionВҰ59274 of\add*, \add вүҲthere mustВҰ59276 be a way to get back the family\add* land.
\v 25 \add For example,\add* if an \add вүҲIsraeli man\add* becomesВҰ59282 poor and sells off some of his \add вүҲinherited land\add*, then a close relative \add mustВҰ59282 have the right to\add* go and \add вүҲbuy back\add* that land.
\v 26 Even if he didn'tВҰ59297 have \add вүҲa relative who could do that\add*, and he prospers again \add in the future\add* and is \add вүҲable to raise enough money\add*,
\v 27 then he can calculateВҰ59308 \add вүҲthe value of the yearsВҰ59311\add* \add until the restoration celebration\add*, andВҰ59308 then \add вүҲfor that amount\add* he \add вүҲmustВҰ59308 be allowed to\add* \add вүҲbuy the land back from the personВҰ59317 he'd sold it to\add*.
\v 28 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add вүҲthe original owner wasn't able to raise enough money\add*, thenВҰ59325 that \add вүҲpiece of land that\add* was sold will remain \add вүҲunder the control of the buyer\add* untilВҰ59338 the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* yearВҰ59339 when it mustВҰ59341 be returnedВҰ59343 \add anyway\add*.
\p
\v 29 If a houseВҰ59350 inside a walled cityВҰ59353 is sold, thenВҰ59346 the right \add вүҲto buy it back\add* will last untilВҰ59357 one full yearВҰ59360 after the sale.
\v 30 If it's not boughtВҰ59387 back \add by the original family\add* within that year, then that houseВҰ59377 in the walled cityВҰ59380 will then belong permanently to the buyerвҖ”it won'tВҰ59367 \add вүҲbe returned in the restoration celebration year\add*.
\v 31 \add вүҲOn the contrary,\add* villageВҰ59395 housesВҰ59394 will be considered as part of the family land, so they'll be able to be bought back \add by the family\add*, \add вүҲotherwise they'll be returned in the restoration celebration year\add*.
\p
\v 32 The Levites' cities andВҰ59414 housesВҰ59416 will belongВҰ59421 to them permanentlyвҖ”the Levites \add вүҲmustВҰ59421 \+em alwaysВҰ59420\+em* be able to buy them back\add*,
\v 33 \add вүҲbutВҰ59424\add* \add even\add* if \add *they\add* \add ?don't\add* \add вүҲbuy them back\add*, they mustВҰ59425 be \add вүҲreturned in the restoration celebration year\add* becauseВҰ59436 the Levites' housesВҰ59437 are theirВҰ59441 \add only\add* possession among the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ59443\add*.
\v 34 \add вүҲIn additionВҰ59446,\add* they may not sellВҰ59450 the pasturelandВҰ59447 around their citiesВҰ59448 becauseВҰ59451 that's their permanentВҰ59454 possessionВҰ59453.
\s1 Assisting the poor
\rem /s1 Loans to the Poor; Redemption of the Poor and Enslaved
\p
\v 35 If \add вүҲa fellow citizen\add* becomesВҰ59461 poor and \add вүҲis unable to survive\add* beside you, then you mustВҰ59461 \add вүҲsupport\add* \add @that person\add* and \add вүҲallow him to liveВҰ59470 with you like a foreigner might\add*.\x + \xo 25:35: \xt Deu 15:7-8.\x*
\v 36 You mustn't \add вүҲcharge\add* \add @that person\add* any interestВҰ59477 \add вүҲor make a profit from himВҰ59476\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ59478\add* you mustВҰ59479 \add вүҲrespect and obey\add* your godВҰ59480, and your \add вүҲfellow citizen\add* can \add continue\add* to liveВҰ59481 with you.
\v 37 \add вүҲIf you loan him money\add*, don'tВҰ59488 \add вүҲcharge\add* interestВҰ59492 \add вүҲor make a profit from his\add* food.\x + \xo 25:37: \xt Exo 22:25; Deu 23:19-20.\x*
\v 38 I am your god YahwehВҰ59500 who broughtВҰ59504 you all out of EgyptВҰ59507 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* to give you the Kanaan \add вүҲregionВҰ59506\add* \add and\add* to be your god.
\s1 Treatment of slaves
\rem /s1 Release of Slaves
\p
\v 39 If \add вүҲa fellow citizen\add* becomesВҰ59521 poor and selling himselfВҰ59524 to you, don'tВҰ59527 \add вүҲforce him to work like a slaveВҰ59532\add*вҖ”\x + \xo 25:39-46: \xt Exo 21:2-6; Deu 15:12-18.\x*
\v 40 \add вүҲtreat him\add* like a hiredВҰ59534 worker or a temporary residentВҰ59535. He can work with you untilВҰ59538 the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* yearВҰ59540
\v 41 \add вүҲwhen he mustВҰ59545 be released\add* \add вүҲalong with\add* his children, and he can return to his family, and to \add вүҲhis clan's land\add*,
\v 42 because they are my slaves that IВҰ59566 broughtВҰ59566 out of EgyptВҰ59569 so they mustn't be sold \add again\add* as slaves.
\v 43 Don't rule harshlyВҰ59579 over \add #them\add* \add вүҲbutВҰ59580 rather\add*, \add вүҲrespect andВҰ59580 obey\add* yourВҰ59581 godВҰ59581.
\v 44 \add вүҲIf you want to have\add* male or female slaves, they you can buy them from the surrounding countriesВҰ59590,
\v 45 or else from the children or clans of the foreigners who are living among youвҖ”you all can \add вүҲownВҰ59613 them\add*
\v 46 andВҰ59615 thenВҰ59615 pass them on to your children to ownВҰ59621 as their inheritanceВҰ59615. YouВҰ59628 all can make them work indefinitely \add for you\add*, butВҰ59615 you mustn't harshlyВҰ59635 oppress your \add вүҲfellow IsraelisВҰ59626\add*.
\p
\v 47 If a foreigner living among you \add вүҲbecomes wealthy\add*, \add вүҲyet\add* your \add вүҲfellow citizen\add* becomes poor and sells himselfВҰ59647 to that resident foreigner or to a memberВҰ59652 of their clan,
\v 48 then there's always the rightВҰ59658 of redemptionВҰ59658 even after he's sold himselfВҰ59657, \add so\add* one of his brothersВҰ59663 can \add вүҲbuy himВҰ59664 back\add*,
\v 49 or his uncle or \add вүҲcousin\add* or another relativeВҰ59676 from the clan can \add вүҲpay to free him\add*. \add вүҲIn fact,\add* he might even be able to \add вүҲbuy his own way out\add*.
\v 50 He mustВҰ59686 \add вүҲwork out\add* with his master how many years from when he sold himselfВҰ59691, untilВҰ59693 the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* year, andВҰ59686 \add вүҲfigure out\add* the price accordingВҰ59701 to the wages of a hiredВҰ59702 worker for that many years.
\v 51 If there's stillВҰ59708 a lot of yearsВҰ59710 \add вүҲto go\add*, he'd need to repayВҰ59712 \add вүҲmost\add* of \add вүҲwhat he sold himself for\add*,
\v 52 \add вүҲbutВҰ59717\add* if it's only a few years \add вүҲto go\add*, \add вүҲthe price for his freedom would be proportionally smaller\add*.
\v 53 While he works for \add @the foreign master\add*, he must be treated like an annual hiredВҰ59736 worker. \add вүҲYou others must ensure that he's not treated\add* harshlyВҰ59744.
\v 54 ThenВҰ59747 even if he's not \add вүҲboughtВҰ59750 out\add*, he andВҰ59747 his children mustВҰ59750 be released in the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* yearВҰ59753
\v 55 because the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ59762\add* are my slavesвҖ”my slaves because I broughtВҰ59770 them out of EgyptВҰ59773. I am your godВҰ59776 YahwehВҰ59775.
\c 26
\s1 Obedience will lead to prosperity
\rem /s1 Rewards for Obedience; Reward for Obedience; Blessings for Obedience
\r (Deu. 7:12-24; 28:1-14)
\p
\v 1 You all mustn't make worthlessВҰ59782 idolsВҰ59782 or carvedВҰ59790 images for yourselves, or set up sacredВҰ59784 pillarsВҰ59784. In your country, you must never bow down to an \add engraved\add* stoneВҰ59789 image, becauseВҰ59796 I am your godВҰ59799 YahwehВҰ59798.\x + \xo 26:1: a \xt Lev 19:4; \xo b \xt Exo 20:4; Deu 5:8; 16:21-22; 27:1.\x*
\v 2 You all mustВҰ59804 \add вүҲobserve\add* my rest days andВҰ59805 \add вүҲhonour\add* my sanctuaryВҰ59805. I am YahwehВҰ59808.
\p
\v 3 If you'll all \add вүҲfollow my instructionsВҰ59813\add* and \add вүҲremember my rules and obey\add* them,
\v 4 thenВҰ59822 I'llВҰ59822 give you all rain \add вүҲin the proper season\add*, and the land will produce crops and the trees in the countrysideВҰ59829 will produce fruitВҰ59831.
\v 5 The \add grain\add* threshingВҰ59835 will \add вүҲcontinue until\add* the grape harvest, and the grape harvesting will \add вүҲcontinue until\add* \add вүҲit's time to plant new crops\add*, and so you'll all have \add вүҲplenty of foodВҰ59845\add* and you'll live securelyВҰ59848 \add there\add* on your land.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ59851 I'll giveВҰ59851 peaceВҰ59852 \add вүҲin your country\add* \add вүҲso that\add* you'll all sleep \add вүҲwithout being afraid\add*. I'll \add вүҲremove\add* the wild animalsВҰ59858 from your \add вүҲarea\add* andВҰ59851 there'llВҰ59855 be no \add вүҲraids or wars\add* in your \add вүҲregionВҰ59867\add*.
\v 7 You'll all \add be able to\add* chase away your enemiesВҰ59872 andВҰ59873 \add вүҲdestroy them\add*вҖ”
\v 8 fiveВҰ59880 of you will chase away a hundred, and a hundred of you will chase away tenВҰ59884 thousandВҰ59884, and you'll \add вүҲbe able to defeat\add* your enemiesВҰ59887.
\p
\v 9 I'll \add вүҲgive you all my attention\add* and \add вүҲblessВҰ59893 you with manyВҰ59895 children\add*, and I'll \add вүҲmaintain\add* my agreementВҰ59900 with you all.
\v 10 You'll all \add still\add* \add вүҲbe eating the previous year's grain\add* when the new harvest \add вүҲstarts\add*, andВҰ59903 you'll have to \add вүҲmove\add* out \add вүҲthat left-over grain\add* \add to make room for the new\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ59911 I'llВҰ59911 put my residence amongВҰ59913 you all andВҰ59914 won'tВҰ59914 \add вүҲreject\add* you,
\v 12 and I'llВҰ59920 walkВҰ59920 amongВҰ59921 you and be your godВҰ59924, and you'll all be my peopleВҰ59929.
\v 13 I am yourВҰ59944 godВҰ59933 YahwehВҰ59932 who broughtВҰ59935 you all out from beingВҰ59939 slavesВҰ59941 in EgyptВҰ59938, and I brokeВҰ59942 the \add вүҲchains off you\add* \add вүҲso that you all could walkВҰ59945 with heads erect\add*.
\s1 Punishments for disobedience
\rem /s1 Punishment for Disobedience; Penalties for Disobedience; Punishments for Disobedience
\r (Deu. 28:15-68)
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if you all won't listenВҰ59953 to me and won't \add вүҲfollow all those instructions\add*,\x + \xo 26:14-33: \xt Deu 28:15-68.\x*
\v 15 and if youВҰ59980 all rejectВҰ59966 my regulationsВҰ59965 and my \add вүҲvalues\add* \add вүҲto the point of\add* hating my commandsВҰ59979, thus breakingВҰ59980 my agreementВҰ59983,
\v 16 then this is what I'll doВҰ59988 to you all: I'll \add вүҲsend\add* suddenВҰ59994 terrorВҰ59994 to you all, and \add вүҲwasting diseases and sicknesses\add*. You'll all \add вүҲbe wasting your time\add* sowing seeds \add вүҲbecause\add* your enemiesВҰ60009 will eatВҰ60008 \add @the harvest\add*.
\v 17 I'llВҰ60011 \add вүҲtake action\add* against you, and you'll be defeatedВҰ60014 by your enemiesВҰ60016. You'll be ruled over by thoseВҰ60019 who hateВҰ60019 you, and you'll all \add вүҲrun away frightened\add* \add even\add* when no one's chasing you.
\p
\v 18 If you all \add still\add* won'tВҰ60032 listenВҰ60033 to me \add вүҲafter that\add*, then I'llВҰ60035 continue on to disciplineВҰ60036 you sevenВҰ60038 times over for your \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ60043 I'll \add вүҲsmash\add* your strong prideВҰ60046, and I'll make the sky like iron \add with no rain\add* and your land \add hard\add* like bronzeВҰ60056.
\v 20 Your \add вүҲenergy spent working\add* your land will be \add just\add* wasted \add вүҲas\add* your land won't \add вүҲproduce its crops\add*, andВҰ60058 the trees won't \add вүҲproduce any fruitВҰ60072\add*.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ60074 if you're all \add still\add* \add вүҲbeing contraryВҰ60078\add* andВҰ60074 unwilling to listenВҰ60081 to me, thenВҰ60074 I'llВҰ60083 \add вүҲsend\add* sevenВҰ60086 times more plaguesВҰ60085 accordingВҰ60087 to your \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\v 22 ThenВҰ60089 I'llВҰ60089 sendВҰ60089 in the wild animalsВҰ60093 \add вүҲto\add* make you childlessВҰ60095 and to cut back your livestocksВҰ60100, \add вүҲthus diminishingВҰ60101 your numbers\add* and \add leaving\add* your roadsВҰ60104 desolateВҰ60103.
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ60106 \add вүҲafter that\add* if youВҰ60110 all \add still\add* \add вүҲwon'tВҰ60109 accept my disciplineВҰ60110\add* andВҰ60112 \add вүҲcontinue to oppose\add* me,
\v 24 thenВҰ60116 I myself will \add вүҲoppose\add* you all andВҰ60122 \add вүҲpunish\add* you all sevenВҰ60127 times over for your \add вүҲdisobedience\add*.
\v 25 I'll \add вүҲsend armies against\add* you all to avengeВҰ60135 \add вүҲthe breaking of our agreementВҰ60138\add*. You'll be \add вүҲshut into\add* your citiesВҰ60142 \add вүҲwhere\add* I'll send diseases in for you all, andВҰ60132 \add вүҲallow your enemies to defeat\add* you.
\v 26 When I \add вүҲlimit your foodВҰ60155 supplies\add*, ten womenВҰ60158 will bake bread in one oven and \add вүҲit will be rationed\add* by weightВҰ60164вҖ”you'll all eat \add вүҲbutВҰ60156 never\add* be satisfiedВҰ60167.
\p
\v 27 In spite of \add all\add* that, if you all \add still\add* won'tВҰ60173 listenВҰ60174 to me, and \add вүҲcontinue to oppose\add* me,
\v 28 thenВҰ60180 I'll \add вүҲbe in a hostile rage against\add* you all andВҰ60185 I'll disciplineВҰ60185 you sevenВҰ60190 times \add more\add* for your \add вүҲdisobedience\add*
\v 29 and you'll \add start\add* eating your own sonsВҰ60198 and daughtersВҰ60200.
\v 30 I'll destroyВҰ60203 your \add вүҲhilltop shrines\add* and cut down you incenseВҰ60210 altarsВҰ60210, thenВҰ60203 I'll \add вүҲpile\add* your corpses on top of your idols' corpses, and I myself will detest you all.
\v 31 I'll make your citiesВҰ60226 into \add вүҲheaps of rubble\add* and I'll devastateВҰ60228 your sanctuariesВҰ60231 and \add no longer\add* smellВҰ60233 the pleasingВҰ60235 aromas \add of your sacrifices\add*.
\p
\v 32 I'llВҰ60237 devastateВҰ60237 the \add вүҲregion\add*, andВҰ60237 your enemiesВҰ60244 who live in itВҰ60246 will be appalledВҰ60242.
\v 33 ThenВҰ60248 I'llВҰ60249 scatterВҰ60249 you all amongВҰ60250 \add other\add* nationsВҰ60250 and thenВҰ60248 \add вүҲarmies will come in\add* afterВҰ60252 you and your land will become desolateВҰ60256 and your citiesВҰ60257 will become \add вүҲrubble\add*,
\v 34 and the land will enjoy all its rest \add вүҲtimes\add* while it's desolateВҰ60269 and you're all in your enemies' \add вүҲcountries\add*. The land will \add вүҲstop producing\add* and \add вүҲenjoy its times of resting\add*.
\v 35 It will rest all through its desolationВҰ60284 since it didn'tВҰ60288 get its rest times when you lived on it.
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ60295 thoseВҰ60295 of you who are left in your enemies' countries, I'llВҰ60297 make \add вүҲyou paranoid\add* \add thereВҰ60312\add*вҖ”even the soundВҰ60304 of a blowing leaf will make them run away as if someone's chasing them with a swordВҰ60310, andВҰ60295 they'll fall down even when no one's chasing them.
\v 37 They'll stumbleВҰ60315 over each other as if \add вүҲbeing attacked\add*, butВҰ60315 thereВҰ60323 won't be anyoneВҰ60322 chasing them, andВҰ60315 thenВҰ60315 you all won't have the energy to standВҰ60328 up against your enemiesВҰ60330.
\v 38 You'll die in \add various\add* countriesВҰ60333 andВҰ60332 your enemiesВҰ60337 will consumeВҰ60334 you.
\v 39 Those of you who are left will rot away amongstВҰ60340 the wickedness in your enemies' countries andВҰ60339 because of the wickedness of their ancestorsВҰ60347.
\p
\v 40 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if they confessВҰ60351 their wickedness and their ancestors' wickedness, thatВҰ60360 they've disobeyed and neglected me, and \add вүҲbeen hostile towards\add* me,
\v 41 (and that I became hostile toward them and took their into their enemies' countries,) and humbleВҰ60384 their \add вүҲundisciplined\add* heartsВҰ60385 and \add вүҲadmit their disobedience\add*,
\v 42 thenВҰ60393 I'll remember my agreements with Yakov \add (Jacob)\add* and with Yitshak \add (IsaacВҰ60402)\add* and with Avraham, and I'll remember \add &this\add* land.
\v 43 The land \add here\add* will have been desertedВҰ60419 by them and will have enjoyed its \add вүҲtimes of rest\add*, and they'll accept their wickedness becauseВҰ60426 they rejectedВҰ60429 my \add вүҲvalues\add* and they \add вүҲreally\add* detested my regulationsВҰ60432.
\v 44 \add вүҲDespite that\add*, I won't rejectВҰ60446 them in their enemies' countries, and I won't detest them enough to completely destroy them \add and\add* to breakВҰ60451 my agreementВҰ60452 with them, becauseВҰ60454 I am their godВҰ60457 YahwehВҰ60456.
\v 45 I'llВҰ60459 rememberВҰ60459 the \add вүҲearlier\add* agreementВҰ60461 with their ancestors that I broughtВҰ60464 out of EgyptВҰ60468 while all the nationsВҰ60470 watched me be their godВҰ60473. I am YahwehВҰ60475.
\p
\v 46 \add вүҲThe above\add* are the \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ60478 and values and rules\add* thatВҰ60481 YahwehВҰ60483 \add вүҲinstilled\add* between him and the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ60486\add* through MoshehВҰ60492 \add (Moses)\add* there at MtВҰ60488. SinaiВҰ60489.
\c 27
\s1 Valuations of vows to Yahweh
\rem /s1 Votive Offerings; Redeeming Gifts Offered to the Lord; Laws concerning Gifts to the Lord; Redeeming What Is the Lord's
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ60496 told MoshehВҰ60499:
\p
\v 2 TellВҰ60506 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ60505\add* that when someone makes a special vow \add вүҲto offer someone\add* to YahwehВҰ60515,
\v 3 a man between twentyВҰ60521 andВҰ60517 sixtyВҰ60526 will be valued at fiftyВҰ60530 silverВҰ60532 \add вүҲcoins\add* (according to the sanctuary standard weights)
\v 4 andВҰ60540 a woman at thirtyВҰ60542 coins.
\v 5 If it's someone between five and twenty, thenВҰ60545 it's twenty silver coins for a male and ten for a femaleВҰ60560.
\v 6 Between one monthВҰ60567 old and five yearsВҰ60572, it's five silver coins for a male and threeВҰ60581 for a femaleВҰ60579.
\v 7 For sixtyВҰ60588 years old and older, it's fifteen silver coins for a male and ten for a femaleВҰ60599.
\p
\v 8 If \add @the maker of the vow\add* can't afford the valuationВҰ60607, then \add @that person\add* mustВҰ60608 stand in frontВҰ60609 of the priest \add and give an account\add*, and then the priest \add вүҲcan set a value that they can afford\add*.
\p
\v 9 IfВҰ60637 it's an animal that they're \add вүҲpromising\add* as a gift for YahwehВҰ60632, then \add ?вүҲthat animal becomes sacredВҰ60640\add*вҖ”
\v 10 it can'tВҰ60644 be \add вүҲexchanged for a different one (either better or worse)\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ60644\add* if it does get substituted, then \add вүҲboth animals will become sacredВҰ60666\add*.
\v 11 Any вҖҳuncleanВҰ60672вҖҷ animal cannot be presented to YahwehВҰ60679, \add so if that's what was promised\add*, \add @the person\add* mustВҰ60676 take the animal to the priestВҰ60685,
\v 12 andВҰ60692 a priest mustВҰ60687 \add вүҲgive a fair valuationВҰ60694 accordingВҰ60694 to the quality of the animal\add*вҖ”the priest's \add вүҲdecisionВҰ60687 will be final\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if it's later bought back, thenВҰ60699 an extra twentyВҰ60704 percentВҰ60703 mustВҰ60702 be added to that valuationВҰ60707.
\p
\v 14 If someoneВҰ60709 dedicates their houseВҰ60715 as sacredВҰ60712 to YahwehВҰ60717, a priest mustВҰ60712 \add вүҲvalue it according to its quality\add*вҖ”the priest's \add вүҲdecisionВҰ60718 will be final\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add вүҲthat person\add* \add decides to\add* buy back their houseВҰ60737, then an extra twentyВҰ60739 percentВҰ60738 mustВҰ60734 be added to the valuationВҰ60742 andВҰ60731 then it \add вүҲcan be theirs again\add*.
\p
\v 16 If someoneВҰ60752 dedicates part of their \add вүҲfarmland\add* as sacredВҰ60751 to YahwehВҰ60753, thenВҰ60747 \add вүҲit will be valued according to how much seed\add* \add would be sown in it\add*вҖ”fiftyВҰ60761 silverВҰ60763 coins for each 130kg of barleyВҰ60760 \add seed required\add*.
\v 17 вҮ”That would be its value if itВҰ60772 was dedicated during the \add вүҲrestoration celebration\add* yearВҰ60767,
\v 18 \add вүҲbutВҰ60774 in the years following,\add* the priestВҰ60783 mustВҰ60778 calculateВҰ60780 the field'sВҰ60779 value \add вүҲdepending on\add* how many years remainВҰ60791 before the next \add вүҲrest\add* year.
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if \add @that person\add* \add decides to\add* buy back their land, then an extra twentyВҰ60808 percentВҰ60807 mustВҰ60801 be added to the valuationВҰ60811 andВҰ60798 then it \add вүҲcan be theirs again\add*.
\v 20 If \add @the person\add* doesn't buy back the field \add вүҲbutВҰ60816\add* sells it to someone else, thenВҰ60816 it can'tВҰ60818 be boughtВҰ60832 back againВҰ60833.
\v 21 ThenВҰ60835 when the field is released at the next \add вүҲrest year\add*, it will be sacredВҰ60839 to YahwehВҰ60840 andВҰ60835 the \add #priests\add* \add вүҲwill take ownership\add*.
\p
\v 22 If someone dedicates to YahwehВҰ60857 some land thatВҰ60852 they've bought (i.e., it's not part of their clan inheritance),
\v 23 thenВҰ60859 a priestВҰ60862 must calculateВҰ60859 the valuation untilВҰ60866 the \add next\add* \add вүҲrestoration celebration year\add*, andВҰ60859 it must be paid that same dayВҰ60873 вҖ”becoming sacredВҰ60875 to YahwehВҰ60876.
\v 24 In \add вүҲthat rest\add* yearВҰ60878, the land will returnВҰ60880 to the original owner who \add вүҲhas it as part of their clan inheritance\add*.
\p
\v 25 All valuationsВҰ60893 will \add вүҲbe calculated\add* using the standard weights from the sanctuaryвҖ”the \add вүҲsilver coin mustВҰ60894 weigh twelve grams\add*.
\p
\v 26 EveryВҰ60922 firstbornВҰ60905 \add вүҲdomestic animal\add* (including cows and sheepВҰ60921) \add automatically\add* belongsВҰ60908 to YahwehВҰ60909, and no person can \add claim to\add* вҖҳdedicateвҖҷ it.
\v 27 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if it's an вҖҳuncleanВҰ60927вҖҷ animal then it must be bought back by paying its valuation plusВҰ60928 an additional twentyВҰ60931 percentВҰ60930, \add вүҲbutВҰ60925\add* if it's not bought back, then it must be sold at its valuation \add price\add*.
\p
\v 28 If someoneВҰ60947 dedicates something to Yahweh that they ownВҰ60957 (e.g., a man or an animal, or a fieldВҰ60956), they can'tВҰ60958 then sellВҰ60959 it or buy it \add ?straight\add* backвҖ”everything that's dedicated \add like that\add* becomes sacredВҰ60965 to Yahweh.\x + \xo 27:28: \xt Num 18:14.\x*
\p
\v 29 Any personВҰ60973 who's dedicated for destructionВҰ60975 cannot be boughtВҰ60980 backвҖ”they mustВҰ60975 be executed.
\p
\v 30 A tenth of all the \add вүҲharvestsВҰ60990 from the crops\add* andВҰ60984 fruitВҰ60990 from the trees, belongs to Yahweh. It's sacredВҰ60994 to Yahweh.\x + \xo 27:30-33: \xt Num 18:21; Deu 14:22-29.\x*
\v 31 If someoneВҰ61001 \add really\add* wanted to buy back their tenth \add of their produce\add*, \add an additional\add* twentyВҰ61003 percentВҰ61004 mustВҰ61000 be added \add to the valuation\add*.
\v 32 Every tenthВҰ61018 animal of the \add вүҲmustered domestic\add* cattle and sheep and goats, is sacredВҰ61021 to YahwehВҰ61022.
\v 33 \add @The herder\add* mustn't pick out goodВҰ61028 or bad ones, or make substitutions. (If a substitution was made, both animals then become sacred and mustВҰ61025 not be bought back.)
\p
\v 34 \add @The above\add* are the \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ61049 and rules\add* thatВҰ61048 YahwehВҰ61050 \add вүҲgave\add* MoshehВҰ61053 at MtВҰ61058. SinaiВҰ61059 for the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ61056\add*.
